title: baked eggs
directions: Spray a large rectangular glass baking dish with Pam.
Line the baking dish with slices of bread.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over bacon and cheese layer.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Test, using clean knife.

title: great-grandma's creamed corn
directions: Melt margarine in sauce pan on stove.
Add drained corn, sugar, and pepper.
Heat.
Add flour to thicken.
Slowly add half 'n' half to cream.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: In a large pan, put your crushed crackers.
Have nuts in small pieces.
Cut candied fruit in pieces also.
Add sugar, butter, lemon extract and cinnamon.
This takes a lot of mixing together by hand.
Juice from the fruit will hold this together.
After mixing well, place in a Bundt cake pan, sprayed with Pam.
Press cake in pan firmly.
Trim top of cake with nuts/fruit.
Put in refrigerator overnight in cake pan, then you can remove from pan onto cake plate.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chunky chicken salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together except Chinese noodles.
Chill 2 hours.

title: basic bavarian
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in hot water.
Add cold water or juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in Cool Whip and fruit.
Serve in a bowl, mold, or serving dishes.
Best if made a day ahead.

title: church supper hot dish
directions: In a skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink. Drain and set aside.
In a large saucepan, saute potatoes, celery, carrots, green pepper and onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Add water:
cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add soup and ground beef: mix well.
Sprinkle half of the chow mein noodles into a greased shallow 2-qt baking dish.
Spoon meat mixture over noodles.
Cover and bake at 350 for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese and remaining noodles.
Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes longer or until heated through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: caramel cheese apple pie
directions: Melt caramels and cream over boiling water.
Keep warm. Combine flour,
sugar,
salt
and
butter.	Mix
into
crumbs. Blend oil
with
egg and water.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until dough forms.	Roll
out
to fit a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Combine apples, sugar, flour and lemon juice.
Cook about 20
minutes
until
apples are partially tender;
spread over crust.
Beat cheese, egg and sugar until smooth.
Drizzle caramel sauce
in strips over apples.
Spoon cheese mixture in between caramel
strips.
Sprinkle	with pecans.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, lemon extract, eggs and Seven-Up. Add flour, little bit at a time.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: chicken egg drop soup(stracciatella zuppa)
directions: Heat chicken broth to boiling point.
Whisk egg, cheese and parsley until well
beaten.
Stir
soup
while
adding egg mixture in a thin steady
stream.
Remove
from
heat
and let stand 2 minutes before
serving.
Season
with salt and pepper to taste. Makes 1 to 2 servings.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Heat
oven
to	400°. Empty potato slices and packet of sauce mix into 2-quart casserole.
Heat tomatoes, oregano and water
to boiling, stir in potatoes.	Arrange pepperoni on top and
sprinkle with
cheese.
Bake uncovered 30 to 35 minutes. Hamburger, browned
and
drained
can	be
used
in
place of pepperoni (use 1/2 pound very lean).

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix.
Beat together and add to cooled jello.
Whip 1 large can chilled Pet milk to very stiff.
Add to jello mixture.

title: calico bean hot dish
directions: Fry together ground beef, bacon and onions until light brown. Partially drain beans and pour into beef and bacon mixture. Put in a baking dish, add seasonings and stir well. Bake uncovered at 300° for 1 1/2-2 hours. (For a quick bake, bake at 350° for 40 minutes.)

title: easy pastry
directions: Soften butter and cream cheese with fork; work in as much flour as you can. Knead as much as you like, the dough will always roll out thin and not break. Fill with your favorite fruits or fillings. Bake just a few minutes at 350 until done. This always turns out flaky & tender.

title: one dish meal
directions: Brown beef; add all other ingredients. Heat and put into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: potato skins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Coat potatoes with oil.
Bake in oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cut potatoes in half.
Carve out some of the center.
Place potato shells under broiler for 3 to 5 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Fill potato shells.
Bake in oven for 15 minutes.
Serve with sour cream.

title: joann's not hot nachos
directions: Melt cheese, soup and onion together.
Serve with corn chips.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix oil, pumpkin and water well.
Add dry ingredients; add eggs one at a time.
Grease 3 bread pans or 2 large bread pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: millionaire shortbread
directions: Cream 8 ounces	butter	with 4 ounces sugar.
Add flour and work to a
smooth
dough.
Press into a greased Swiss roll pan (28.5 x 18.5
x
centimeters). Bake at 180°C (350° F) until pale golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: pancake syrup(from scratch)
directions: Bring sugars and water to full rolling boil and boil 30 seconds.
Cover pan and let mixture rest a minute or so, then stir in maple flavoring and vanilla.
Recover pan (covering the pan during cooking is supposed to cut down on crystallizing).

title: golden cream soup
directions: Combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onion, parsley flakes, seasoning and bouillon.
Cover; simmer 15 to 20 minutes, or until vegies are tender.
Gradually add milk to flour, stirring until well blended.
Gradually add flour and milk to hot vegies, stirring constantly until boils and thickens.
Add cubed cheese; stir until cheese melts.

title: curly noodle dinner
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Stir in seasoning pack from package of noodles, tomatoes and corn.
Break up noodles.
Stir into beef mixture.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Makes 4 to 5 main dish servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Drain whole kernel corn.
Mix with creamed corn.
Beat eggs. Add milk, sugar and flour.
Stir egg mixture and corn mixture. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes or until set.

title: sam's favorite waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a bowl; add egg and milk.
Stir until smooth and creamy batter (if batter is a little thick, add a little more milk).
Add the oil last; mix well and pour onto a preheated waffle maker.
When the light goes out, they should be ready (approximately 3 minutes).
Get your butter and syrup ready! Enjoy!

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil and cool eggs, cutting lengthwise, giving 12 egg parts. Mix egg yolks with sandwich spread until smooth.
Add more sandwich spread, if needed.
Add a little garlic, if desired.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in saucepan and cook over low heat. Let come to a bubbling boil and cook 4 minutes.
Add and blend vanilla, oatmeal and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: dirty rice
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hello dollies
directions: Layer each ingredient in order given in an 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cajun potatoes
directions: Fry bacon crisp, add white onions, bell pepper and celery. Cook veggies about 5 minutes with bacon, add potatoes and then green onions.
Cook over low heat and stir open.
Add Cajun spices to taste.
If more seasoning is desired, add a little salt.

title: quick and easy pizza dough
directions: Put all ingredients into food processor.
Blend on high until dough forms a ball.
Remove from processor and put on flour covered board.
Knead a few times until smooth, then let rest 10 to 20 minutes before spreading in pizza pans.
Add desired toppings and cheeses.
Bake at 400° to 450° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden and bubbly.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken and other ingredients.
Sprinkle chips and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: chicken sauce for cut up chicken
directions: Put cut up pieces of chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour all ingredients, after blended, over chicken.
Bake in a 350° oven until chicken is done, about 1 hour.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender for 30 seconds. Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Serve with cut up fresh fruit.

title: healthy heart carrot cake
directions: Beat egg substitute for 5 minutes.
Mix in sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Stir in carrots and pineapple with juice.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, well-greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve with low-fat vanilla frozen yogurt.

title: sour cream cheese potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes so you can grate on large holes of grater (or use frozen hash browns).
Cook onion and butter until tender.
Mix together soup, cheese and sour cream.
Pour mixture over potatoes. Top with cornflakes or potato chips.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crisp sugar cookies
directions: Gradually add sugar to Crisco and butter, creaming until fluffy.
Beat eggs one at a time.
Add sour cream and vanilla. Stir in flour that was sifted with baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Chill.
Roll out small amount at a time very thin on lightly floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° 6 to 9 minutes or until golden.
Makes 4 to 6 dozen medium sized cookies.

title: spaghetti
directions: Heat oil in a large frying pan or Dutch oven and brown cubes of meat.
When browned, add onion, garlic, spices, tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook slowly 2 or 3 hours, adding water as needed. When meat is tender, add mushrooms and liquid plus enough water to make 1 to 1 1/2 quarts of sauce.
Thicken slightly with flour and water paste.
Cook 1/2 to 1 pound spaghetti.
Pour sauce over spaghetti.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: microwave pot roast(yields 6 servings)
directions: Place roast in 3-quart casserole.
In small bowl, mix tomatoes, onion, garlic powder, cayenne and pepper.
Add cinnamon stick. Pour over roast.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes. Microwave 30 more minutes at 1/2 power.
Add remaining ingredients. Re-cover.
Microwave at 1/2 power for 30 to 45 minutes or until roast and vegetables are tender.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Serve with biscuits.

title: frozen strawberry delight
directions: Mix together and crumble onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle 2/3 of crumb mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sunshine bread
directions: Mix as listed.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 mini-loaves.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except peaches.
Let cool, then add peaches.
Pour into a 9 x 13
pyrex dish.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add oatmeal and nuts.
Shape into 2 rolls and wrap in wax paper.
Put in refrigerator and chill. Slice and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: honey lemon chicken
directions: Roll chicken in flour mixture.
Melt 1/3 cup butter and coat pieces of chicken well.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Combine honey and lemon juice and glaze chicken pieces.
Bake another 15 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix flour, salt and soda; set aside.
Mix white sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
In a large bowl, cream the butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy.

Using electric blender at low speed, beat in eggs, then dry ingredients alternating with milk until well blended. Stir in rhubarb and vanilla. Turn into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured glass cake pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hamburger spinach soup
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Add the frozen spinach; cook until thoroughly defrosted.
Do not cover.
Stir in the milk.
Add the salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Thoroughly mix the cornstarch and water.
Very slowly, add to the spinach-meat mixture.
Stir until thickened.
Serve with a dash of nutmeg over each bowl, if desired.

title: dream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, then add pineapple.
Mix cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk.
Add this to jello mixture. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish and refrigerate.
Ready to eat when set.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix together ground zucchini squash, ground onions and salt. Let stand overnight; drain, rinse and rinse again. Add remaining ingredients. Cook slowly until clear (about 30 minutes). Seal hot. One half of recipe makes 3 pints.

title: divinity lemon pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Put in one cooked pie crust or graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: easy baked chops
directions: Place chops on bottom of large casserole dish.	Combine soup, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Pour over pork chops. Bake, covered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken and broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli until barely tender; drain and arrange in 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish.
Boil chicken breasts until tender and place deboned chicken over broccoli.
Combine undiluted soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; beat until smooth and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Combine bread crumbs and butter, then sprinkle over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Melt butter and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour the milk over crust.
Spread chocolate chips and peanut butter chips on this.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: frankfurter noodle casserole
directions: Combine green pepper, onion, prepared mustard and flour. Simmer Carnation milk and salt in a saucepan over low heat to just below boiling.
Add cheese.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into small pieces and brown good.
Cut up bell peppers, onions and tomatoes into 2-inch pieces.
When meat has browned, add your peppers, onions and tomatoes.
Pour over this mushroom soup and water.
Simmer for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cook rice as directed on package when done.
Put rice on plate and cover with pepper steak ingredients.
Put soy sauce over this until taste.

title: tunnel of fudge cupcakes
directions: Mix cake by directions on box.
Fill paper lined cupcake tins 2/3 full.
Cream the cream cheese with sugar and beat in salt and egg. Stir in chips. Drop 1 rounded teaspoonful of cheese mixture into middle of each cupcake.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. These are so delicious they need no frosting!

title: venison dip
directions: Brown meat, mix in sauces.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cheeses over top; bake on 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from oven, add sour cream to top.
Bake another 5 minutes. Remove.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender; cut up and put in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Cook celery and onion in chicken broth until tender. Drain and put on top of chicken evenly.
Mix both cans of soup with milk.
Spread over chicken, celery and onions.
Mix stuffing as directed.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Any favorite brownie recipe or package mix.
Cook as directed. Two minutes before brownies are cooked, remove from oven and cover with marshmallows.
Return to oven for 2 minutes.
Mix water, chocolate and margarine together in small saucepan until melted.
Remove from heat and add confectioners sugar and vanilla. Mix well and cover marshmallows.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: potato broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until done but firm. Cook broccoli. Mix cheese and flour with water from potatoes and place in food blender and blend into a sauce. Mix with the potatoes and broccoli and serve.

title: quick drip punch
directions: In basket of coffeepot place brown sugar, cloves, allspice and cinnamon.
Plug coffeepot in and perk through.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until thickened.
Pour hot mixture into sterilized canning jar; seal immediately.
Yields 2 cups.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with the cinnamon and 1 cup of sugar.
Make a topping with 1 cup sugar, the flour and butter.
Sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix and spoon into muffin tins or on cookie sheet.
Bake in hot oven until brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, red onion, cheese and bacon in a large bowl. Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar in small bowl.
Pour dressing over ingredients in large bowl; toss well.
Serve.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Mix carrots, water and sugar; cook for 10 minutes or until tender.
Keep warm.
Reserve 1/2 cup cooking liquid.
Add butter, syrup and mustard to the 1/2 cup cooking liquid; cook 5 to 7 minutes to heavy syrup stage.
Add carrots and cook until glazed.

title: thanksgiving cake
directions: Cream butter until light.
Add sugar slowly, beating well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each, then add wafer crumbs alternating with milk.
Add vanilla extract.
Add coconut, then mix fruit, nuts and raisins into bowl with 1/4 cup flour.
Cover well and shake, dusting well with flour, then mix with batter. Pour in well-greased and papered tube pan.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 325°, then let cool.

title: ground beef t-bones
directions: Mix all ingredients lightly and shape to resemble 4 T-Bones. Place on rack of broiler pan and broil 8 minutes on one side.
Turn and broil 4 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, water, sugar and pineapple juice in large container.
Add ginger ale just before serving. Will serve 50 people.

title: baked meringue
directions: Beat egg whites, cream of tartar, salt and baking powder 10 minutes or until stiff.
Add sugar 1 tablespoon at a time, at slower beater rate.
Add vinegar.
Beat 10 to 15 minutes longer. Add extract at the end of beating time.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan, greased on the bottom only.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Place pan in oven.
Turn off oven.
Do not open door until cool, at least 3 hours.

title: onion-cheese supper bread
directions: Cook onions in small amount of oil until tender (but not brown).
Combine egg and milk. Add to biscuit mix and stir only until just moistened.
Add onions, half of the shredded cheese and the parsley.
Spread dough in an 8 x 1 1/2-inch round pan. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Drizzle melted margarine over the top.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.

title: toasted pecan caramel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix all dry ingredients and then add chocolate chips. Combine egg, milk and butter.
Stir into flour mixture.
Do not beat.
Spoon into muffin tins that have been well-greased.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: lemon lush
directions: Make a crust of butter and crumbs and press in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup of Cool Whip. Spread mixture over crust. Set aside the remaining Cool Whip for last layer. Mix pudding and milk thoroughly and spread over cream cheese mixture. Use remaining Cool Whip topping to cover pudding.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Top with more cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Put rice in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In microwave, melt butter, soup and water.
Pour over rice; stir well.
Sprinkle broccoli on top of mixture.
Add melted cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Chop.
Place in a casserole dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Mix cracker crumbs with melted margarine.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter or butter and shortening; add sugar and beat until creamy.
Add eggs; beat.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Add banana and floured nuts.
Bake about 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: loaded potato soup
directions: Microwave potatoes for 7 to 10 minutes. While microwaving potatoes, melt butter. Add flour and milk. Heat at medium heat; add sour cream, 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese, onions, salt and pepper to taste. Add potatoes; cook on medium heat for about 5 more minutes. Top with bacon bits and additional grated Cheddar cheese before serving.

title: ham potatoes au gratin
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and pepper.
Add milk all at once and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; add cheese and mayonnaise. Stir until cheese melts.
Combine potatoes and ham with sauce. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pea salad
directions: Note:
I have these slightly to dissolve the sugar.

title: san francisco chops(how to microwave)
directions: Tips:
For microwaving, the rounder the shape of the container, the better.
Oval dishes and oblong dishes with rounded corners are good shapes.
Microwave energy is attracted to square corners and food overcooks in those areas.

title: stuffed chicken shells
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
(I reduce the amount of butter.)
Mix in chopped chicken.
Spoon mixture into cooked shells.
Combine water and soup; mix well.
Spread 1/3 of soup mixture in an 8 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Arrange filled shells in dish; top with remaining soup.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: taco bean dip
directions: Mix together the bean dip, sour cream, cream cheese, onion and taco seasoning.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Serve with chips or nachos.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Boil liquid out of hominy.
Melt the oleo in a baking dish. Mix hominy and sour cream together.
Pour into baking dish.
Slice and place cheese on top of hominy mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: chili with rice
directions: Brown meat, adding chopped green pepper and seasoning mix in a large skillet over medium heat.
Stir in water, tomato sauce and beans.
Reduce heat to slightly boiling and cook 10 to 15 minutes. Add corn and cooked rice.
Cook 10 more minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve with shredded cheese, chopped onion, sour cream and salsa or eat plain with crackers.
Serves 6.

title: sausage pizza rounds
directions: Brown sausage meat and hamburg together. Drain well.
Cut cheese into cubes and mix into hot meat mixture until melted.
Add seasonings and mix well.
Mound mixture on party rye bread (may be frozen at this point).
Broil until bubbly and browned.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Mix all together and pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: sausage stuffing broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.

title: mccoy's irish meatballs
directions: Combine ground chuck, egg, pepper, onion, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls.
Brown in shortening until all sides of meat are evenly browned (approximately 10 minutes).
Add tomato sauce, water and bay leaf. Bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 hour.
Serve over spaghetti.
Serves 6.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage and cook in salted boiling water until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Pour in soup.
Add margarine.
Mix well and put half in a large greased casserole dish (13 x 9 x 2-inches). Sprinkle with half of crackers and half of cheese.
Add remaining cabbage, crackers and cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Sift together first seven ingredients.
Beat eggs until light; add sugar slowly.
Set aside.
Soak zucchini in water and salt. Drain.
Add oil to dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk and zucchini.
Add chopped nuts, vanilla and orange peel; beat.
Fold in eggs. Pour into two 9-inch cake pans, greased and dusted with cocoa powder.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: glorified grams
directions: Line jelly roll pan with graham crackers.
Mix butter and brown sugar.
Spoon over graham crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.
Break in rectangles.
Serves 60.

title: custard
directions: Beat eggs well. Add the sugar. Beat well. Pour in 2 quarts whole milk. Beat again. Put over low heat. Add 2 more quarts of milk. Stir until boils. Boil to just thick. Take off heat and add vanilla. Let cool. Refrigerate. When cold, drink.

title: orange chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken; brown in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 40 minutes, until done.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Make a sauce of butter, flour and broth.
Saute onions and green pepper in butter.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing lightly with noodles.
Put into a casserole; cook for 20 minutes at 300°.

title: party favors
directions: You will need colored paper, toothpicks and candies.

title: elegant swiss casserole
directions: Cook chicken and chop into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Top with almonds or pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can be refrigerated overnight before baking.

title: hollandaise sauce(great over veggies or eggs benedict)
directions: In a 1 quart microwave safe dish, heat 2 tablespoons of butter, uncovered, on high for 30 seconds or until melted.
Whisk in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Microwave, uncovered, on high for 1 minute; whisk lightly.
Heat 1 minute longer or until thickened.
Whisk in remaining butter until melted.

title: popcorn cake
directions: In large glass bowl, combine margarine, oil, caramels and marshmallows.
Alternate microwaving and stirring until ingredients become a pourable mixture.
Place popcorn in large mixing bowl.
Add M&M's and peanuts.
Pour sauce over and toss to mix.

title: tossed salad(greek)
directions: Break lettuce into small pieces and toss with next 8 ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste and toss again.
Place anchovies evenly around salad and sprinkle Feta cheese over top. Just before serving, pour even amounts of olive oil and vinegar over salad and toss at table.
Serve with hard bread, crackers or crusty rolls.

title: easy lemonade pie
directions: Fold in lemonade, Cool Whip and condensed milk together. Pour into pie crust.
Chill.

title: dutch potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done; let cool a little, then peel and slice into circles.
Mix vinegar and sugar; stir until mixed well. Add water, onion slices (cut in circles) and fresh parsley (cut up).
Add salt, pepper and oil.
Stir well.
Pour over potatoes and mix.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Let marinate; cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: play doh
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Boil water, oil and food coloring. Pour boiling mixture over dry ingredients.
Add hand lotion. Mix with a spoon.
Knead until smooth.
Divide into portions for coloring.
Keep in a plastic container.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Drain sauerkraut and put into the bottom of a large, oblong baking dish.
Place pork chops on top of sauerkraut.
Mix soup, water and sugar together and pour over sauerkraut.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours and until meat is nicely browned.

title: do ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes.
Mash with cream cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Put in casserole and dot with margarine.
Can be refrigerated up to 2 weeks.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and taco seasoning.
In a large bowl, cut up tomatoes, onion, black olives and cheese.
Crush Doritos into small pieces.
Combine all vegetables, cheese and Doritos in a bowl. After ground beef is ready, let stand about 15 minutes or until cool.
Drain grease.
Combine beef and French dressing in bowl with vegetables, cheese and Doritos.
Stir until French dressing is covering everything.
Chill and serve.
Great for picnics.

title: edie's family size lasagna
directions: Use a turkey roaster for this recipe.
Boil lasagna noodles until soft; drain and cool.
Mix cottage cheese and eggs together. Brown hamburger; drain off grease and add spaghetti sauce and tomato paste.
You can add oregano and garlic to your taste.
Cook for 1 hour on low heat; make sure your sauce has lots of juice.

title: baked custard
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and salt in a small mixing bowl.
Slowly stir in milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in 350° oven, after having placed dish in a larger baking pan filled with hot water, for 45 to 50 minutes until set and golden brown.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In medium bowl combine butter, 2 tablespoons peanut butter and cereal.
Press onto bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
In large bowl, combine ice cream and 2 tablespoons peanut butter.
Pour into cooled crust.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Before serving, spread whipped topping over pie.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Cook together first nine ingredients until done.
Make white sauce with gravy flour and milk so it pours well into cooking pot. Add 1 can of milk.
Blend well.
Add cheese as you desire.
Cook for another 5 minutes.
Serve hot with corn bread.

title: lettuce dressing
directions: Cut up a little bacon and fry it with a little butter.
Add flour and brown.
Dilute vinegar with water.
Add a little salt and sugar.
Stir and let cool.

title: salad dressing
directions: Beat sugar and cider vinegar together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli; cook and bone chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Place broccoli in a baking dish and cover with chicken. Make a sauce of the chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Mix sauce and pour over chicken.
Top with grated cheese.
Dot with melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook Karo, sugar and water together to hard crack stage.
Add butter, salt and Spanish peanuts; cook until golden brown. Remove from heat and add soda and vanilla.
Stir and pour out on buttered tile.
Must be tile as it has to cool rapidly. Spread until very thin.

title: carrot bars
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add carrots and applesauce.
Then stir in dry ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: capellini with crabmeat
directions: Boil water, then add capellini; cook until al dente and drain. Put all ingredients into separate saucepan, except crabmeat.
Bring to a boil, then add crabmeat.
Pour sauce over capellini and serve.

title: chow chip cherry cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add cherry filling, chocolate chips and nuts. Mix pie.
Heat oven to 325° to 350°.
Pour in greased Bundt pan. Bake 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pennsylvania beef barbecue
directions: Mix together in casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve on toasted buns.
Serves 16.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in 2-quart casserole dish. Crumble Ritz crackers over top and drizzle melted butter over the crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato salad
directions: Core and wedge 10 tomatoes and throw into a bowl.
Chop up the celery sticks, green pepper and onions.
Sprinkle parsley flakes in, add Italian dressing and stir.

title: tony g's chili
directions: Saute onions (cut up) in a very small amount of olive oil.
Add ground beef.
(If you use dried beans, cook in water in large pot for 1/2 hour or so.)
Otherwise, add beef mixture to large pot with 3 quarts of water.
Also, add the tomatoes, sugar and vinegar and beans.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours if using dried beans or cook for 1/2 hour and add canned beans and cook another 1/2 hour.
Skim off any grease and thicken with flour.
Serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Melt butter in casserole.
Add sliced mushrooms; cook for 5 minutes.
Add onion and tomatoes; cook another 5 minutes.
Add crab meat, leaving it in as large lumps are possible.
Season and heat, then add the cream, stirring gently.
Let boil 1 minute, no longer, then add parsley, chives and brandy.
Serve at once from the casserole into shallow soup plates into which one has put a spoon of cooked rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: four cheese, pasta and beef
directions: Cook pasta as package directs; drain.
In skillet, brown meat. Salt and pepper to taste; drain.
Add tomatoes.
Cook, uncovered, until slightly thickened.
Stir in onions and cream cheese.
Toss with remaining ingredients.
Cover 2 minutes to melt cheese. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit crush punch
directions: Mix water and sugar; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in fruit juices and mashed bananas.
Pour into two (2-quart) containers and freeze.

title: brown rice
directions: In a casserole dish, put melted butter, rice and soups.
Bake 1 hour at 350° (uncovered).
Stir at least once.
Can add mushrooms if desired, one can, undrained, with other ingredients.

title: mushroom london broil
directions: Cut both sides of steak into a diamond pattern 1/8-inch deep. Cook and stir onions and 1/4 teaspoon of salt in margarine until onions are tender.
Keep warm.
Mix remaining ingredients, except mushrooms.
Brush half of mixture on the steak.
Set oven to broil or 550°.
Broil beef with top 2 to 3 inches from heat until brown, about 5 minutes.
Turn meat over, brush on remaining mixture and top with mushrooms.
Broil 5 minutes longer.
Remove from oven and add onions.
Makes 4 servings.

title: honey apple muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs, yogurt, honey, butter and ginger.
Fold in apples.
Fill muffin tins about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: fiesta
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add taco seasoning to meat in skillet. Add tomatoes and simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Put cheese pieces in large bowl.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, then add rice and meat and mix well.
Cover and let cheese melt. Top with chips just before serving.

title: apple "john"
directions: Peel and core apples.
Cut into medium chunks.
Put cut apples in a 4 quart bowl and cover with biscuit dough.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until biscuits are done.
Serve warm with either or both spices and milk.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: slow-roasted tomatoes
directions: Remove tomato seeds with a spoon. Place tomatoes, cut side up, on baking sheets coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle with cheese, oregano, sugar, salt and pepper; drizzle with oil. Bake at 250° for 2 hours. Yield: 8 servings.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Mix all, except crackers, and boil until the sugar dissolves. Let cool.

title: corn muffins
directions: Sift together meal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Combine milk and well-beaten egg and oil.
Combine two mixtures stirring quickly and vigorously.
Pour into hot, greased muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter over low heat; gradually add flour, stirring continuously.
Add cream and milk; cook until slightly thickened. Add Parmesan (2/3 cup), salt, pepper, garlic and cooked chicken. Stir in mushrooms.
Mix in casserole dish with cooked spaghetti (or use mostaccioli noodles).
Sprinkle top with 1/3 cup Parmesan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli in small pieces.
Add other ingredients.
Make dressing with mayonnaise, lemon juice and sugar.
Pour over salad. Stir and serve.

title: punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add lemon juice, lime juice and pineapple juice.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Serves 25 people.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put bread in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Brown and drain sausage; pour over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spicy fried turkey
directions: Mix all ingredients, except applesauce.
Inject into bird with a cooking syringe.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Before cooking, rub applesauce over turkey.
In large fish fryer, heat peanut oil to 325° to 350°.
Drop whole turkey into hot oil.
Cook 3 minutes per pound.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Put everything in bowl and mix together.
Then place in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In heavy skillet, melt margarine.
Then add sugar, cocoa and milk.
On medium heat, cook exactly 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Add oats and coconut.
Stir until well blended and then add vanilla.
Drop onto waxed paper with spoon; let cool and eat.

title: uncooked catsup
directions: Grind all vegetables.
Place in pan with salt and let set overnight.
Squeeze vegetables and add celery seed, sugar and vinegar.
Keep refrigerated all the time.

title: cold oven cake
directions: Sift flour together 5 times.
Cream butter and shortening well.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Add flour, a little at a time, alternating with milk.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add lemon extract.
Turn batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Put in cold oven.
Light oven and set at 325°.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat the soup and gelatine.
Remove from heat.
Add cream cheese, shrimp, mayonnaise, onion and celery.
Mix together and pour in a mold.
Chill about 4 hours.

title: hush puppies(serve with fish)
directions: Grate onion on finest side of grate.
Add remaining ingredients with enough buttermilk to make thick batter.
Make batter before frying fish to allow it to rise.
Drop small spoonfuls into hot fat where fish have been fried.
Brown on both sides.

title: onion-beef-macaroni casserole
directions: Brown meat on all sides.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in Lipton soup mix, flour, tomato sauce and water. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in macaroni.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 15 minutes in a 400° oven.
Real good.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook in top of double boiler until thick.
Pour into 2 baked shells.
Top with egg whites and brown in oven at 400°.

title: gratin of tomato and zucchini
directions: Slice unpeeled zucchini into 1/4-inch pieces.
Melt butter in a large skillet and cook zucchini, stirring for 10 minutes.
With a slotted spoon, transfer zucchini to a bowl, cover and set aside. Peel and chop tomatoes and place in skillet with onion, garlic and basil.
Cook over medium heat about 15 minutes or until some of the liquid evaporates.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine tomatoes and zucchini and place in a shallow baking dish (7 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch).

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes; mix well with next 4 ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Crush Ritz crackers; combine with walnuts and butter or oleo and spread over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: icy banana shake
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Mix until well blended.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix well in large bowl. Store in jar. Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain juice from all fruit.
Mix fruit with remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: nut cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add shortening.
Add 2/3 cup milk and mix well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add 1/3 cup milk and mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350°.
Makes two 9-inch pans.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Chill 24 hours, stirring often.
Mix broccoli, bacon and onion with mayonnaise mixture.
Serve chilled.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water until crisp and tender after cutting flowerets in small, bite-size pieces.
Combine broccoli, raisins, sunflower seeds, red onion and bacon.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and lemon juice and pour over salad.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in regular bread pan.
Cover with 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Drain mandarin orange segments.
In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, lime juice, salt and nutmeg.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves. Refrigerate leftovers.
Yields 4 servings.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Place shrimp in non-metal container. Combine lemon juice, garlic powder and onion salt. Pour over shrimp. Let stand 10 minutes. Heat oil in large skillet. Add onion and green pepper; saut. Stir in curry powder. Add water slowly; simmer 15 minutes. Add shrimp and cook 15 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: simple quiche
directions: In large bowl mix all ingredients together with a whisk and pour into pie shell.
Place pie pan on cookie sheet; easy to remove and retains spills.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Cut and serve with a salad.

title: strawberry jam turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
On cookie sheet, separate dough into 4 rectangles, pinching diagonal seams closed.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon confectioners sugar.
Spoon 1/4 cream cheese and 1/4 preserves in center of each.
Brush edges with egg whites.
Fold corners to center and press.
Brush tops with egg whites.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden.

title: beef and rice
directions: Cook rice in hot oil until golden brown.
Add salt, water, bouillon cube and soy sauce.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer (it may be necessary to add more water).
All water should be absorbed at end of cooking time.
If not, remove lid and cook until water evaporates.

title: buddy bars
directions: Melt marshmallows, candy and butter.
Mix in Rice Krispies. Butter hands and spread in a shallow pan.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: huhnerbrust berliner art
directions: Put the butter in a saute pan and set over medium heat.
Roll the chicken breasts in flour and saute over medium heat.
Roll the chicken breasts in flour and saute over medium heat until almost done.
Remove and set aside in a warm spot.
Add the mushrooms to the pan and saute briefly.
Sprinkle with a scant tablespoon flour, some salt and pepper and a pinch of tarragon.
Stir and add chicken stock.
Put the chicken breasts back into the pan and let simmer until tender.
Add leeks or scallions and cook a little. Adjust seasoning to taste.
Serve with any vegetable and potato or noodle.

title: saucy grilled sandwich
directions: Combine peanut butter and applesauce in small mixer bowl; mix well.
Spread peanut butter mixture on 2 slices of toast.
Top with remaining toast slices.
Spread margarine on both sides of sandwiches.
Place on griddle or in skillet.
Brown on each side.

title: ice cream torte
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in bottom of pan.
Soften any flavor ice cream and spread on top of layer.
Use as much ice cream as you wish.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes. While still hot, take fork and punch holes in cake, then ice with following icing.

title: papa's best ever sugar cure(for 80 pounds of meat)
directions: Mix well and rub meat.
Let stand 24 hours.
Rub on remainder. Pepper to suit taste at this time, then hang up and smoke.

title: hawaiian kabobs
directions: In large bowl, combine soy sauce, oil, corn syrup, garlic, dry mustard and ginger.
Add meat; cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Drain meat, reserving marinade.
Alternate meat, green pepper and tomato on skewers.
Grill over medium-hot coals until desired doneness, allow about 15 minutes for rare.
Baste the kabobs occasionally with reserved marinade.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until almost done. Cut into small chunks. Combine all ingredients except bacon. Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes. Near end of baking time, top with fried bacon.

title: condensed cream soup
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt.
Cook until bubbly.
With wire whisk, stir in your choice of liquid, cooking until thick and smooth.

title: coconut fruit bowl
directions: Drain all fruit.
Combine fruit and coconut. Fold in Cool Whip, cover and chill.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: steak and rice
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
In a large skillet, brown meat in oil, using high heat.
Add onions.
Saute until tender and crisp. Blend soup, sherry, liquid from mushrooms and garlic salt.
Pour over steak. Add mushrooms.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour or until steak is tender.
Serve over bed of fluffy rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: spicy crackers
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large container with lid.
A large Ziploc bag will work. Add all crackers and roll, toss, fold or mix gently. Allow to rest until oil is absorbed, mixing occasionally.

title: oven fried herbed chicken
directions: Stir buttermilk well.
Dip chicken into milk.
Mix dry ingredients.
Roll chicken in dry mixture.
Place in a greased pan with cooking oil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, turning once.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon pecan fruitcake
directions: Cream together sugar and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Sift baking powder and flour.
Add to creamed mixture, small amount at a time.
Add extract, chopped fruit and pecans.
Put in well-greased and floured pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour or until cake tests done.

title: cranberry crunch salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over orange juice to soften.
Let stand 5 minutes. Combine cranberry sauce, boiling water and sugar. Stir in softened gelatin; refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Fold in cabbage, celery and nuts.
Pour into individual molds or 1 1/2-quart mold.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dip for bread(italian, french or rye)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Hollow out center of bread, then fill the center of the loaf of bread with the dip.
Break the center into pieces and place around the dip.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Mix well and place in 9 x 13-inch greased pan; bake 1 hour at 350° with no cover.
Top with potato chips the last 15 minutes.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Heat butter, cocoa and Coke together until boiling; cool slightly.
Combine buttermilk, baking soda, vanilla and marshmallows.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Combine sugar and eggs. Stir in flour and add to chocolate mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Pierce cake with fork.
Let icing seep into holes.

title: jan hagel cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly and spread on ungreased cookie sheet.
Beat egg white with fork until foamy, then brush on top of mixture on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle pecans on top.

title: guacamole salad
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except lettuce and toss to combine.
To serve, line serving platter with lettuce and top with avocado mixture.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss until all pieces are coated with vinegar and oil. Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes. (Slice wieners.)

title: chicken or turkey rolls(8-10 rolls)
directions: Cook stuffing and set aside. Stir 1/2 can milk with soup, place in microwave for 2 minutes on high. Stir again and set aside. Place 2 Tbsp. stuffing in center of slice of meat and roll up. Place rolls in skillet and cover with soup. Heat until soup bubbles.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Add next five ingredients and stir; then add last two.
Use an ice cream scoop to put cookie dough onto a large cookie sheet, about 6 to a sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 17 minutes on the highest rack in the oven.
Makes about 35 cookies.

title: toffee bars
directions: Line a cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and then pecans.
Bring to boil the butter and brown sugar. Boil for 2 minutes.
Slowly drizzle over crackers, chips and pecans.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool 15 minutes, then pull apart and refrigerate.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and add to cooked rice, undiluted mushroom soup and cheese.
Saute onions and celery in 1/2 stick butter and add to mixture.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until bubbly.
(Use casserole dish.)

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread in large bowl. Crumble slices of bread in a food processor and add to cornbread. Add chopped onion and egg and stir well. Start adding chicken broth a cup at a time until it is the consistency you like.
Salt and pepper to taste. Stir in sage a little at a time stirring well. Pour in a greased 9 x 13 or bigger dish. Bake for 30 - 45 minutes until slightly brown on top.

title: oatmeal pie(mock pecan)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Add oats last. Bake until done.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Spoon sausage over crust and sprinkle hash browns on top.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over hash browns. Beat eggs, milk and salt together. Pour over top and sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: asbury punch
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients, adding soda before serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Allow sausage and cheese to get at room temperature.
Grate cheese and mix with sausage and Bisquick.
Mix thoroughly.
Form into small balls.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mocha coffee
directions: Make simple syrup of the sugar and 2 cups coffee. Boil together.
Cool.
Add the milk.
On serving, add the ice cream and whipping cream.
Serves 50.

title: spicy snacks
directions: Combine egg white and water.
Stir in sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger.
Beat until frothy.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken breast pieces the way you like. Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for 20 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients in order given. Bake 30 minutes in greased pan (Texas sheet cake pan).

title: microwave macaroni and cheese
directions: In 2 quart microwave-safe casserole, stir soup and milk until blended.
Stir
in
cheese
and
macaroni.
Cover	and microwave on	High
for
10 minutes.	Stir at 3 and 6 minutes. Remove and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: corn medley
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until butter is melted. Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes. Stir in tomato and sugar. Cook, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: oriental chicken stir-fry
directions: In small bowl, stir together cornstarch, vegetable juice, soy sauce and ginger until smooth.

title: special mushrooms
directions: Clean and wash mushrooms, removing stems.
Cut up stems and mix with softened cream cheese and dressing mix.
Stuff mixture into mushroom caps.
Top with alfalfa sprouts.

title: forgotten dessert
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and vanilla and beat until very stiff.
Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time, and beat until very thick.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Place in oven preheated to 450°.
Put into oven and then turn oven off.
Do not open dor until morning.
Serve topped with strawberries and whipped cream, chocolate or your own idea. Delicious!

title: company shrimp casserole
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Saute peppers, onions and celery in butter.
Add to shrimp mixture.
Put in long flat casserole and completely cover with sliced lemons.
Cook, covered with foil, for about 20 minutes at 375°.
May be made ahead and frozen.
Serve with French bread, salad and dessert for a delicious company meal.

title: pick-a-chick nuggets
directions: Crack the egg; open and pour into a small bowl.
Add milk; stir with a fork.
Cut the chicken into 1-inch chunks.
Dip chunks in egg mixture.
Place chip crumbs into a bowl.
Place chicken chunks in chip crumbs; gently stir to coat chicken chunks with chip crumbs.
Place chicken chunks on a microwave-safe plate.
Sprinkle with remaining chip crumbs.
Cover with a sheet of wax paper. Place in microwave oven; set on Medium-high (70% power) for 5 minutes.
Turn halfway and cook on Medium-high for an additional 4 minutes.
Cut one chunk; if it is still pink, cook for another 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serve with toothpicks to pick up each chunk.

title: quick's baked beans
directions: Mix beans, sugar and pepper in roasting pan.
Add bacon.
Put in oven for 1 hour.
Bake at 350°.

title: have it your way squash casserole
directions: *Use any or all but do not exceed 1 cup total.

title: yum-yum dough
directions: Sprinkle chopped peanuts in greased 4 1/2 cup ring mold or 9-inch
square
baking
pan.
Combine
sugar and cinnamon. Separate
biscuit
dough
into
10	biscuits.
Dip biscuits in butter then
in
sugar mixture.
Place in baking pan with each biscuit
overlapping
another.
Tuck
raisins
in between each biscuit.
Add remaining sugar mixture and the butter.
Bake at 425° for
12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm. Makes 4 to 6 yummy servings.

title: "more casserole please"
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Cook meat, onions and bell pepper in pan only until meat loses its red color; do not brown.
Add tomatoes, chili powder and pepper.
Simmer over low heat for 10 minutes, then add corn and peas.
Place a layer of noodles in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add half of meat mixture and top with half of grated cheese.
Follow with another layer of each.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts and mixture becomes bubbly, about 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: wonder sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine ingredients and heat through.
Serve with cocktail wieners or over meatballs as an hors d'oeuvres or entree.

title: american chop suey
directions: Fry onion and celery in butter until light brown.
Add beef and water.
Let simmer 1/2 hour, then add rice and soup.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook 10 minutes longer to serve hot.

title: banana milk shake
directions: Place cold milk, ice cream, chopped banana and vanilla into blender or shaker.
Blend or shake until thick and creamy.
Serves 2.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg and orange juice. Combine ingredients until moistened.
Add nuts and cranberries last.
Pour batter into a loaf pan lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: catfish with crunch rice salad
directions: Mix soy sauce, 1 tablespoon olive oil and 1/4 teaspoon pepper in large zipper type food storage bag until blended.
Add fillets. Turn to coat.
Let marinate while preparing salad.
Cook brown rice according to package directions.
Meanwhile squeeze lime and put juice in large bowl with salt and remaining oil and pepper.
Cut tomatoes in small chunks.
Peel, seed and dice cucumber.
Slice scallions.
Add to bowl with rice and toss.
Broil catfish 4 inches from heat source, 7 to 9 minutes until fish is opaque in center. Serve with rice salad and lime wedges.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Whip whipping cream and combine with cream cheese mixture.
Line bottom of pie shell with bananas and pour mixture on top.
Add lemon juice to pie filling and cover top of pie with filling.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fudge oatmeal bars
directions: Mix together the ingredients (except filling).
Put 2/3 of mixture into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: mint julep
directions: You will also need chilled glasses.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine
and
3 teaspoons sugar in pan. Bake, do not overbake, 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: chicken wings
directions: Double this for 5 pound bag of frozen wings. Triple for 10 pounds.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Combine chicken, salad dressing mix and cream cheese in a mixing bowl.
Mix by hand well.
Shape into ball and roll in pecans.

title: grandma's baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; boil in salty water until tender.
Melt butter in 10 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Drain potatoes; save some of water.
Pepper potatoes to taste.
Roll in flour and place in baking pan.
Roll potatoes in butter to coat all sides.
Bake at 350°, turning every little bit to brown on all sides.
When brown, remove from oven and serve.
My!
They're good.

title: favorite eggnog
directions: Separate yolks and whites of eggs.
Beat yolks until thick and add sugar.
Stir this into milk and add bourbon.
Whip the cream; add and then fold the well beaten egg whites in and put into eggnog bowl.
Add the ice cream just before you serve it and break it up into small pieces and stir to mix it through the nog.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream, vanilla, flour, salt and baking powder.
In another bowl, mix brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
Layer in a Bundt or cake pan some of the batter and then some of the dry mixture.
Repeat layers.
Note: Be sure to generously grease and flour pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while still warm. Cool completely before serving.

title: zucchini cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and mix well.

Pour into a 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven and cool. In a small bowl, beat cream cheese, oleo, milk and vanilla until smooth. Add sugar and mix until smooth. (Add nuts, if desired.) Frost the cooled cake. Serves 20.

title: baptist brisket
directions: Combine in saucepan all the ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium gas flame.
Reduce to low flame and simmer 10 minutes.
Use as basting sauce when grilling brisket.

title: beef roll-ups
directions: In a saucepan, saute onions in butter.
Add carrots, potatoes, 1/2 can of soup, parsley and 1/4 tsp dill.
Cook until partially tender.
Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
If using round steak, cut into 4 or 5 pieces and flatten.
Place stuffing in center of meat.
Roll up, tuck in ends and skewer with toothpicks.
Using a skillet, brown roll-ups on all sides in shortening.
Remove excess fat.
Pour in soup, dill, tomatoes and remaining stuffing.
Simmer about an hour, but stir frequently. Add wine and simmer for 15 minutes more.

title: fancy chicken log
directions: Beat together the first 3 ingredients.
Blend in the next two ingredients and 2 tablespoons of the parsley (refrigerate the remaining parsley).
Shape mixture into a 9-inch log.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill 4 hours or overnight.
Toss together the remaining parsley and almonds; use to coat the log.
Serve with crackers.
Makes about 3 cups of spread.

title: hamburg stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburg and onion, then add soup and mushrooms; simmer about 5 minutes and put in sour cream.
Cook noodles; drain and rinse.
Put noodles on plate and cover with stroganoff (very quick meal).
This can be doubled for a family.

title: ham and cheese puff
directions: Spray small muffin pan. Unroll crescent rolls and pinch off small pieces.
Press into muffin pan, don't have to completely fill the muffin pan.

title: lemon sours
directions: Grease pan well.
Mix together flour and butter to a fine crumb.
Sprinkle evenly in 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, beat eggs and mix in brown sugar, coconut, nuts, baking powder and vanilla.
Spread this on first mixture as you take first mixture from oven.
Return to oven.
Bake 20 minutes longer.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.
Combine sour cream, green chilies, cumin and cream of chicken soup.
Spread 1/3 of the sour cream mixture on bottom of the pan, then 1/3 of the tortillas.
Spread another 1/4 of the sour cream mixture over the tortillas, then 1/2 the chicken.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the cheese. Repeat layers with the top layer being tortillas.
Cover with the remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: moist cheesy macaroni
directions: Turn oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni according to directions on box; rinse and drain.
Mix butter in macaroni until melted.
Mix egg, seasoning salt, bread crumbs, sour cream, Cheddar cheese and milk (in that order).
Pour all mixed ingredients in glass baking dish.
Top with Cheddar or Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: onion soup
directions: In a heavy skillet, cook onion in heated butter until slightly browned.
Sprinkle with flour and cook over low flame until golden, never allowing them to become dark brown.
Add consomme and water.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly with wooden spoon, then simmer for 20 minutes, uncovered.
Add milk.

title: flan(cuban)
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Melt sugar in pan on low heat.
Strain egg mixture into pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Place mixture in double pan.
Place water in bottom pan (hot water). Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Be sure water doesn't splash in egg mixture.

title: apricot bread
directions: Cut apricots into small pieces and pour hot water over them. Let soften for 30 minutes.
Drain and reserve 1/2 cup juice.
Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with orange juice and reserved apricot water.
Stir in apricot pieces and nuts.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.

title: purple cows
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender and blend until smooth. Serve at once.
Makes four 8 ounce glasses.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a greased, covered, casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: red and white frozen salad
directions: In small bowl, combine cranberries and lemon juice.
Spread in 8-inch square pan.
Whip cream.
Fold in sugar, vanilla and pecans.
Spread over cranberry mixture and freeze until firm.

title: birds eye omelet supreme
directions: Set aside topping packet.
Place 1 tablespoon water, 2 tablespoons margarine and vegetables in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil over medium heat; lower heat and simmer for 4 minutes.
Stir cheese and topping into vegetables and keep warm.
Beat eggs and salt with remaining water.
Heat remaining margarine in skillet. Add beaten eggs and cook over medium heat.
Run spatula slowly around edge to allow uncooked portion to flow under.
When omelet is set, but still glossy on top, top with vegetable mixture and cook 2 minutes longer.
Loosen with spatula; fold over and turn onto platter.
Makes 3 servings.

title: indiana peach bread
directions: Bread will be slightly heavy because of fruit content.
Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake in two greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.
May add nuts to batter.

title: exotic cheese dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill; dip it with anything you wish to use.
Substitute cottage cheese if you wish.
Keep it for a few days in the refrigerator, or
deep
freeze
it
for future use.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes and onion.
Mix flour, salt and pepper and slowly blend in milk.
Combine with the potato and onion mixture.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix and add ingredients as given.
(Dry ingredients should be sifted together.)
Bake in large tube pan about 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
(May not need to bake quite that long.) When cool, cover with caramel icing.

title: irish coffee
directions: Place the whiskey and sugar in bottom of cup and stir to dissolve sugar.
Slowly add hot coffee filling to an inch from the top.
Fill remainder of the cup with whipped cream.
Do not stir.

title: danish pancakes
directions: Beat eggs until thick & lemon colored.
Stir in milk.
Sift dry ingredients and add to egg mixture; mixing until smooth.
Drop in small amounts (1 Tbsp. for 3 inch cake) into moderate hot buttered griddle.
Spread batter to make thin cakes.
* My grandfather brought recipe from Denmark!

title: orange sherbet mold
directions: Dissolve
gelatin
in
boiling
water; cool.
Meanwhile drain oranges,
reserving syrup.
To the syrup add lemon juice and Cointreau.
Stir
into
gelatin
mixture.
Stir in orange sherbet just
until
sherbet
melts.
Add oranges.
Pour into oiled mold. Chill
several hours before serving.
Can be used as a salad
or a light dessert.
Use a 6 cup mold with sprigs of fresh
mint or chopped maraschino cherries on top to make a color contrast.

title: yeast rolls
directions: In large bowl, scramble sugar with yeast.
Add salt and mix well.
Scald milk with butter (the size of English walnut).
Cool milk until a little above warm to finger touch.
Pour over yeast, stir until dissolved.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour; mix well.
Add egg, stir and add 1 1/2 cups flour.
Allow to rise in warm spot (about 2 hours).
Knead down dough and put on floured area.
Pat down to about 5/8-inch thick and cut rolls to desired size.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise again about 30 to 40 minutes.
Cook in 400° oven about 8 to 10 minutes or until brown on top.
Top with butter.
Makes 12 to 15 (2-inch) rolls.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: coconut delight
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: Saute ground turkey in a saucepan.
Add onions and pepper; continue cooking.
Add the sugar, chili powder and cumin powder to meat mixture.
Continue to brown the meat and seasonings, then add the tomatoes and spaghetti sauce.
Cook over slow heat so the meat mixture will not scorch.
As the meat is simmering, add the beans and finish cooking in about 1/2 to 1 hour.
The longer chili cooks over a slow fire, the better the flavor develops.
Can be served over rice or spaghetti or eaten by itself.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: roux - fat free roux
directions: Place a
cast
iron skillet, containing 1 inch of flour in a 400° oven until dark brown, stirring occasionally with a wooden spoon.
Use 1/2 as much fat as flour.
Melt fat or heat oil.
Add flour
and	stir
over
medium
heat
until desired darkness occurs.
We
like
ours dark, some people like theirs medium dark.

title: sesame cheese snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Roll into 1-inch balls and coat in cheese.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix margarine, mustard, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce and onion together in bowl.
Split rolls in half.
Spread mixture on bottom half of rolls and lay them back in foil tray.
Layer the ham and Swiss cheese and replace the top of the rolls.
Spread mixture on the top.
Cut rolls into individuals.
Wrap foil around them and cook in 350° oven until cheese melts (15 to 20 minutes).

title: fresh apple cinnamon muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and salt in large bowl.
Beat egg with milk.
Stir in apple and butter.
Add all at once to flour mixture; stir just until moistened (batter will be stiff).
Fill 12 buttered 2 1/2-inch muffin cups 2/3 full.
Combine nuts, brown sugar and remaining 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over each muffin.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
Serve warm. Makes 1 dozen.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except mushrooms.
Heat to boiling. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 lb. fresh mushrooms.
Simmer uncovered for 3 minutes.
Transfer mushrooms and liquid to small bowl and cover.
Chill several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Drain and serve.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: hickles hash
directions: Cook hamburger and drain.
Chop onion and slightly saute.
Add onion and pork and beans to hamburger.
Cook for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cranberry meat balls
directions: Combine and mix first 9 ingredients; add meat and mix gently. Using about 1 tablespoon for each, shape into balls and place in shallow baking pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch, or cookie sheets with sides.
Using a knife, cut through cranberry sauce several times to break into small pieces.
Combine and mix with remaining ingredients.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until sauce melts. Pour over meat balls and bake, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven until done (30 to 40 minutes).
Yields about 65 meat balls.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix as listed.
Bake in unbaked pie shell for 45 minutes at 300° or until light brown.

title: cheddar broils
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on English muffins.
Cut into quarters; sprinkle with parsley.
Broil and serve hot.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in buttered casserole.
On top, add 1 sleeve Ritz crackers, crumbled and mixed with melted margarine.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and celery until tender in the butter.
Add potatoes and bouillon.
Cover with water just to cover potatoes; boil until potatoes are tender.
Put 2/3 of mixture into blender and puree until smooth.
Return to pot and add half and half.
Add instant mashed potatoes to thicken.
Serve cheese on side.

title: apple dessert(quick and easy)
directions: Drain apples.
Mix with fingers.
Spread 1/2 mixture in square pan, then add apples-cinnamon, then rest of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: applesauce souffle
directions: Beat all ingredients together except vanilla wafers.
Put wafers on top, mixing in gently.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Pour in one large can of peaches plus the juice.

title: chicken in a squash shell
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise and scoop out seeds.
Arrange on oiled pan.
Bake cut side down until tender (about 40 minutes.)

title: grandma's old fashioned strawberry pie
directions: Crush 1 cup berries and cook with the 1 cup water about 2 minutes.
Push through sieve.
Combine sugar and cornstarch into berry juice and add red color.
Cook and stir until clear. Arrange strawberries and pour 1st layer and arrange more strawberries and pour out 2nd layer.
Delicious.

title: do ahead beef noodle bake
directions: For variation, you can add 1/4 teaspoon garlic salt, 1/2 teaspoon oregano and/or 1 tablespoon of Parmesan cheese (1/2 in tomato sauce and 1/2 on top).

title: chip and nut pie
directions: Mix well.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in unbaked pie shell at 350°.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: In a greased 9 x 13 baking dish, layer the potatoes, vegetables and chicken.
In a bowl combine soups and broth; pour over the chicken.
Cover and bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour. Uncover, sprinkle with onions.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until heated through.

title: pork tenderloin with orange sauce
directions: Brown pork tenderloin in butter.
Remove meat.
In the same skillet, cook the onion until tender. Add orange juice, orange peel, dry sherry, sugar, salt, dash of pepper and bay leaf. Return meat to skillet.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until tender; turn meat occasionally.
When meat is tender, remove to platter and slice. Thicken the orange mixture in the skillet with 1 tablespoon cornstarch in 2 tablespoons water. Bring to a boil.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes. Drizzle the sauce over the meat before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: blt dip
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended. Garnish with 1 tsp. bacon crumbs. Serve with bread or crackers.

title: copper pennies
directions: Boil carrots until fork-tender.
Put in bowl.
Add peppers and onions.
Mix remaining ingredients and boil 3 minutes.
Pour over vegetables.
Set in refrigerator overnight or longer.
Serve cold.

title: pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan. Cream butter and sugar together well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one. Then add dry ingredients one at a time, mixing in a third of the buttermilk after each one. Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter cocoa fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine peanut butter and butter. Cook over medium heat until butter is melted and peanut butter blends in. Remove from heat. Stir in sugar, cocoa and vanilla. Spread into a buttered 8-inch square pan. Put in freezer for 30 minutes or until firm. Cut into squares. Store at room temperature. Yields 2 pounds.

title: sweet french dressing
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Makes 1 quart plus.

title: valerie's cordon bleu chicken
directions: Heat butter in skillet.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and thyme in a paper bag.
Shake chicken pieces in bag.
Brown chicken thoroughly in skillet.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Mix lemon juice, sugar, salt, wine and pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook slowly over low heat 1/2 hour or until chicken is fork-tender. Sprinkle with parsley and chives.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: country cobbler
directions: Combine butter, 1 cup sugar, Bisquick, vanilla and milk. Blend well and pour into a deep 1 1/2-quart dish.
Combine 1/2 to 3/4 cup sugar, depending on sweetness desired, with berries.
Pour over batter. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mexican dip
directions: Combine beans and taco mix; spread into quiche pan.
Layer other ingredients in the order given.
Heat and serve with taco chips.

title: chicken casserole #4
directions: Cook skinned chicken; cool and debone.
If using canned chicken or leftovers, warm chicken in 1 can of chicken broth. Cook noodles in broth.
Two to three ounces of broth should be left in the noodles.
Mix together the noodles, chicken, onion, bell pepper and soup.
Pour into casserole; top with cheese.
Cook for 25 to 30 minutes in a 325° preheated oven.
Use salt and pepper to taste.

title: pickled beets
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except beets.
Bring to a boil. Add beets, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.	Chill.

title: chicken bake
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on box.
Rinse chicken breasts and pat dry.
Mix soup with water.
Spray casserole or baking dish with cooking spray.
Place stuffing in the middle of pan.
Lay 3 chicken breasts on each side of stuffing.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour soup over chicken and stuffing.
Bake at 350°, basting with liquid in pan occasionally, for approximately 1 hour, until chicken is done.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Sift sugars together several times.
Beat into whites.
Butter a pie plate and dust with flour. Pour egg white mixture into pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Cool very slowly.
When ready to serve, top with whipped cream. Sprinkle on grated chocolate and nuts or strawberries or ice cream and sauce.

title: microwave peanut butter bar
directions: Microwave margarine in a 2-quart casserole dish on High 30 seconds.
Add brown sugar, peanut butter and egg.
Mix well. Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add peanuts.
Mix well. Pour into greased 8-inch square dish.
Microwave on Medium 5 to 7 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn after 3 minutes.
Let stand on counter to cool.
Cut into bars.

title: swedish brown cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add syrup and mix in.
Mix flour and soda.
Then add to first mixture and combine thoroughly.
Divide into 4 portions.
Make 4 ropes about 9 to 10-inches long.
Lay them across cookie sheet and press with fingers to flatten.
Bake in 300° to 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, until light brown.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Mix milk, flour and sugar.
Melt margarine in baking dish. Pour mixture in with butter.
Add fruit by spoonfuls.
(Do not stir.)
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: baked pears melba
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Arrange pears in 2 quart casserole. In	small saucepan, heat pineapple juice, sweetener and ginger to boiling.
Pour
over
pears.
Bake,
covered, for 45 minutes or until
pears
are
tender.	Spoon
warm pear halves with liquid into 6
serving
dishes.
Top each with 1 teaspoon of preserves. Makes
pear) servings with 53 calories each.

title: stir-fried beef in oyster sauce
directions: Marinate beef in soy sauce, sherry and cornstarch for 30 minutes.
Heat oil.
Cook beef until done, stirring 3 to 4 minutes.
Add sugar and oyster sauce; mix well.
Heat through. Serve with rice.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into ice cube trays.
Freeze overnight.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Nice for Christmas serving.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Place fruit on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of fruit.
Melt margarine and spread evenly on top of cake mix.
May sprinkle with coconut if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: saute broccoli
directions: Wash broccoli.
Split ends of large stalks lengthwise into halves or quarters, depending on size.
Place in large skillet. Sprinkle with water, peanut oil, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cover tightly.
Cook over very low heat (20 to 30) or until stalks are tender.
Turn broccoli several times during cooking.

title: pizza appetizer
directions: Beat the first two ingredients together.
Mix ketchup and mustard together and spread on cheese mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve with crackers.

title: blender chocolate mousse
directions: Combine coffee and chocolate morsels in container of blender. Process until smooth. Add egg yolks and crme de cacao. Process 1 minute. Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form. Fold in chocolate mixture. Spoon into individual serving dishes. Chill until set. Top with whipped cream and almonds. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Mix together sugar and peanut butter.
Gradually add Rice Krispies.
Mix together with hands until well blended.
Shape into small balls, then dip in icing made of 2 cups powdered sugar and a little bit of boiling water.
Roll in coconut.
Place on wax paper to harden.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, beating by hand.
Sift cocoa, flour and salt; add vanilla and nuts.
Bake for 35 minutes at 300°.
Add marshmallows and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely; ice as follows.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together chicken breasts, mixed vegetables, chicken broth, salt, poultry seasoning, pepper and onion flakes and put in casserole dish.
Mix buttermilk, margarine and flour.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Bake until golden brown.

title: salmon bisque
directions: In saucepan, melt butter, saute onion, green pepper and celery until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat and gradually add milk.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
