Add salmon which has been flaked and the soft bones crushed.
Stir in pimento at this time.
Simmer until serving temperature.
Makes six 8 ounce servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together and pour into greased 9 x l3 pan.
Mix together brown sugar and chopped nuts and sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: squash bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil, salt, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add squash and mix well.
Stir in flour and pecans. Pour into well-greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour or less, until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients together; put in foil baby loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Use Bugles corn chips for dipping.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook macaroni and Skroodles in boiling salt water with oil; drain.
Cook ground beef and chopped onion together; drain.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine together boiling water, oleo and oatmeal.
Stir once in a while.
Mix together sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and eggs, then add oatmeal mixture and stir well.
Sift in flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Mix thoroughly and bake at 350°.

title: jane's candy
directions: Mix dry ingredients in big bowl.
Melt chocolate in microwave. Pour over dry cereal in bowl.
Mix well until coated.
Pour on cookie sheet (may need 2 sheets), lined with waxed paper.
Let set and break into chunks.
Don't have to refrigerate.

title: she-crab soup
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter; blend in flour.
Add milk and cream; stir constantly.
Add Worcestershire, onion, mace, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper; cook and stir until bubbly. Add crabmeat and roe (crabmeat only if roe not available); heat through.
Place one-fourth of egg yolk (if not using roe) and 1 tablespoon sherry in each bowl.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: hokey pokeys
directions: Brown meats.
Pour off grease.
Add Velveeta and spices.
Mix quickly.
Spread on bread generously.
Bake at 350° until bread gets toasted, about 20 minutes.
Can be frozen in Ziploc bags. Place on cookie sheet.
Reheat as directed.

title: soft peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter and shortening. Add brown sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg. Mix thoroughly.
In a separate bowl, mix dry ingredients, then add to peanut butter mixture.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: rice krispy dessert
directions: Melt butter and sugar; pour over the Rice Krispies, walnuts and coconut.
Put 1/2 of this mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Slice the ice cream and lay on top of this mixture.
Now add the other half of the mix on top of the ice cream and press down firmly.
Place in freezer.
Cook Danish Dessert as package indicates.
Cool.
Add berries (thawed).
Top dessert with sauce as you serve it.
Add dollop of Cool Whip.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir until all is moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in all other ingredients and bake at 325°.
Makes 3 layers.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Cook spinach in small amount water, then drain.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into large greased casserole dish. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese over top just before done.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water for about 15 minutes or until tender.
Prepare rice with dried onion according to rice package. Combine cooked rice, eggs, Ricotta cheese, pimento and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir in milk.
Turn mixture into a 10-inch pie plate.
Arrange broccoli atop.
Sprinkle with cheese in center. Bake for 20 minutes or until almost set. Bake at 350°.

title: helen's salmon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and line with greased wax paper, 1 loaf pan.
Drain salmon. Discard skin and bones.
Saute onion and celery in butter until tender. Stir in bread crumbs; remove from heat.
In a bowl, blend eggs, bread crumbs mixture, milk, parsley, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Fold in salmon and lemon juice.
Bake in prepared loaf pan 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Loosen around edges by running a knife around sides of pan.
Invert salmon loaf onto platter. Carefully remove wax paper. Garnish loaf with lemon slices and celery sprigs.

title: peas with pasta shells(30 minute recipe)
directions: Defrost peas.
In large pan, heat oil and saute onion until soft.
Add garlic and cook 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and simmer about 5 minutes.
Add peas and continue to cook 5 more minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Beat eggs; add butter and then sugar.
Place bread on bottom of casserole and add pineapple, along with the juice.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
If too soupy, bake a little longer.

title: vegetable mix for sandwiches
directions: In blender half full of water, shred vegetables for 3 seconds. Drain well after shredding.
Combine vegetables with mayo; add cooled Gelatin Mixture.
This will keep overnight after made into sandwiches.
Mix will keep for several days.

title: shrimp and ham jambalaya
directions: In heavy skillet, melt 4 teaspoons butter over low heat and saute pepper, celery, onion and parsley until limp and golden brown.
Add tomatoes, garlic and bay leaf.
Stir constantly.
Add salt and Tabasco; cook until mixture begins to boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring until mixture thickens.

title: my favorite brownie recipe
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Combine dry ingredients. Add beaten eggs, then the melted margarine.
Pour into the pan the margarine was melted in.
Bake at 350° until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Do not overbake.

title: texas chili(3 alarm)
directions: Soak beans overnight in pot of water.
Bring beans to boil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium and cover; cook 1 hour. Add onions and tomatoes.
Cover; continue to cook 30 minutes. Add cooked beef, seasonings and water.
Cover; simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; let stand 1 hour.

title: avocado salsa
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except avocado.
Mix well.
Peel avocado.
Remove pit.
Chop avocado into 1/4-inch cubes.
Stir into tomato mixture.
Let stand 20 minutes before serving.
Great with fajitas.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 cups.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix the gelatin with water and stir until dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries to gelatin.
Refrigerate until it begins to thicken.
Break angel food cake into bite-size pieces.
When gelatin begins to thicken, stir in Cool Whip.
Mix well and stir in cake pieces.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: Cut up bread; place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with sausage. Mix other ingredients (except cheese) in blender; pour over the bread and sausage.
Cover with cheese.
Set in the refrigerator overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: quick rhubarb pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar 2 minutes.
Add crushed soda crackers and rhubarb.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with second crust. Brush top crust with milk before baking at 350° for 40 minutes. Best served with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together and store in airtight container.
Add 2 tablespoons of mix into an 8-ounce cup of hot water to make good hot chocolate.
Top with marshmallow.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Cook carrots, covered, about 15 minutes in a small amount of boiling salted water.
Drain carrots and place in a glass or plastic container.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil and simmer 20 minutes.
Pour over carrots and toss well.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.

title: pot roast
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper, basil and thyme.
Cover bottom of large pot with vegetable oil.
Coat all sides of roast with flour mixture.
Brown in oil.
Place onion slices underneath the roast. Add 1 cup water and wine; pour over top of roast.
Bring to boil and reduce heat to low.
Place tight lid on pot and cook until tender.
Slice when cooked and place in casserole dish.
Pour gravy over meat.
Heat in oven next day.

title: carrot soup
directions: Gently cook the carrots, together with the onion, in half of the butter.
When they are tender, add the stock or water and the rice or bread.
Season with a pinch of salt and the sugar.
Simmer for 20 minutes, then pass the soup through a sieve, adding more stock or water if the puree is too stiff.
Reheat the soup with the rest of the butter.
Serve with croutons.
Serves 4.

title: swiss bubbly
directions: Combine all
above ingredients.
Place on 4 hamburger buns or bread.
Then place on baking sheet and bake at 350° until bubbly. Serves 4 people.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine until light and fluffy. Stir in dry ingredients.
Add milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into 2-quart greased baking dish.
Spoon fruit
over batter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Pour juice over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: caramel nut marshmallows
directions: Line a baking sheet with waxed paper; set aside. Place nuts in a shallow dish. In a large microwave-safe bowl, combine caramels and water. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until melted, stirring twice. Dip each marshmallow into melted caramel, then roll in pecans. Place on prepared baking sheet. Let marshmallows stand until set. Yield: 20 servings.

title: cheap apple cake
directions: Mix Jiffy muffin mix according to instructions on box.
Grease round 9-inch cake pan (grease thoroughly).
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar into greased pan and spread evenly.
Layer apple slices on bottom of pan and then cover with muffin mix.
Bake at 400° for 22 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out and sprinkle with confectioners sugar if desired.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Fry hamburger, then drain.
Add taco mix and salsa.
Let cook on low for 15 minutes.
Crush your Fritos, then in an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish, cover the bottom with the crushed Fritos.
Add add hamburger, then cover hamburger with cheese and heat in the oven until cheese melts.

title: meat loaf(diabetic)
directions: Soak the bread crumbs in the tomato juice a few minutes, then mix all the ingredients together with your hands.
Shape into a cylinder 4 inches in diameter (so you can judge you meat exchange).
Put into a baking dish and bake at 350° about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
When you are ready to serve, mark with a knife in the center.
Then make another mark in the middle of each half and then another in each quarter.
One of these slices equals 1/8.

title: simple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: pina colada slush
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of heated pineapple juice.
Let it sit at room temperature for 10 minutes.
Add remainder of juice. Add coconut extract.
Chill in freezer.
Stir occasionally while freezing.

title: chicken hoppin john
directions: In a large fry pan, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp. Drain, crumble and reserve.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons drippings from fry pan.
In the same fry pan, place chicken and cook, turning, until brown on all sides.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Adjust temperature to low.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add rice and onion to chicken in fry pan.
Dissolve bouillon in water. Add hot sauce and stir.
Pour over chicken.
In a medium bowl, mix black-eyed peas, parsley and thyme.
Add to fry pan.
Stir gently to mix.
Cover and cook about 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with bacon.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and spoon into casserole dish. Top with Cheddar cheese and sprinkle corn flake crumbs on top. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: white sugar cookies(the best)
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flavorings and sifted dry ingredients; chill.
Roll thin; cut and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 8 minutes.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package. When done, add oleo. Stir until melted. Stir in soup and cheese. Pour into a greased casserole dish (9 x 13). Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: diet salad
directions: Place pineapple in a bowl and sprinkle jello over it.
Stir in cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: mija's mama chili
directions: Roast chilies in 400° oven for approximately 20 to 30 minutes or until skin is wrinkled, dry and puffy.
While chilies are roasting, saute garlic, onion and tomato in small amount of oil. When chilies are done, run cold water over them and peel.
Skin should peel off easily.
After peeled, cut off stem and slice open.
Remove seeds and vein (seeds will stick to vein).
Leave some of the seeds if you want the chili hotter, the more seeds, the hotter the chili.
Chop up the chilies and add to the garlic mixture.
Next, add cheese and stir until melted.
Add enough milk to make the mixture creamy.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into large bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients until smooth and blended. Bake in greased and floured 9-inch layer pans or 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: tater tot-hamburger casserole
directions: Place Tater Tots in the bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown hamburger with the onion lightly, stirring often. Spread hamburger-onion mixture and corn over Tater Tots.
Combine soups and pour over.
Bake at 350° for 30 to
40 minutes.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Toss lettuce with 8 ounces of Thousand Island or French dressing.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Add kidney beans and salt. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Just before serving, add hamburger mixture to lettuce mixture and serve pronto.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Toss well.
(Mixture should be very moist.
More water can be added if needed).
Cook in a 13 x 9-inch pan or baking dish for 30 to 40 minutes (until browned slightly on top) at 350°.

title: buster's chili
directions: Brown meat and drain off excess fat; add ingredients and cook about 45 minutes.
Serve with hot cornbread and crackers.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Season ground beef; roll into small meatballs and place on broiler pan and broil until medium rare.
While meatballs are cooking, melt jelly in chili sauce over low heat.
Add dash of salt and garlic salt.
Bring to slow simmer.
Remove meatballs from oven and drop in sauce; simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: linda thompson's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef; add onion and green pepper when meat is almost browned.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until done.
Add 1/2 cup water only.
If you want it thinner, add more water.
Let simmer.

title: darrah's divinity fudge
directions: Cook sugar, Karo, water to 248°.
Beat 1 egg white until stiff.
Pour 1/2 syrup over beaten egg white.
Cook other 1/2 syrup to 290°-300° on candy thermometer.
Pour over egg white mixture.
Beat until mixture loses gloss.
Add vanilla and nuts. Pour into lightly greased 8x8 pan.

title: broccoli dish casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
In separate pan, melt 1/2 butter, cream of mushroom soup, mushrooms and cheese.
Mix with broccoli. Pour into ungreased dish.
Saute almonds (sliced) and put on top of casserole. Bake at 350° until bubbly
(20 to 30 minutes).

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix milk, sugar, Crisco and salt.
Heat to lukewarm.
Beat eggs.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients together. Let rise.
Pinch down.
Shape into rolls and let rise.
Bake at 375 degrees.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook shells as directed on the package and drain.
In skillet, brown ground beef and green peppers.
Drain well.
Cool. Add salt, cheese, cottage cheese and spinach.
Mix well.
Stuff shells with mixture.
Place in a greased baking dish. Pour in spaghetti sauce. Cover with additional Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in cubes.
Cook eggplant and onions together in water for 20 minutes.
Drain thoroughly.
Add eggs, butter, bread crumbs, cheese and salt.
Mix well.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 1 hour or until done.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and spices.
Bring to boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Slice zucchini lengthwise in 1/4-inch slices.
Mix cottage cheese and eggs.

title: deep blue sea pops(for kids)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Spoon mixture into paper cups or pop molds.
Drop fish shaped snacks into each cup or mold. Freeze 1 hour.
Insert wooden stick and continue to freeze.
tags: bite size fish shaped fruit snacks

title: mom's refrigerated graham cracker pudding
directions: Roll graham crackers fine.
Add marshmallows, dates (cut into thirds) and nutmeats, broken into pieces, not into crumbs.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Mix cream in with all of this. Pack tightly into shape of roll or loaf.
Take a few extra crackers, crumble with rolling pin and roll loaf in it so as to coat it (like you would flour something).
Put loaf in wax paper and chill overnight.
Then slice and serve with whip cream or ice cream on top.
Serves about 6.

title: juanita's sicilian meat roll
directions: Combine bread crumbs, tomato juice, eggs, parsley, onion, carrot, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic.
Add to beef and mix thoroughly.
Pat out meat on foil or waxed paper to a rectangle, about 12 x 10-inches.
Leaving a border of an inch around edges, put the ham slices, then sprinkle the Mozzarella.
Starting at the short end, roll the meat mixture, using the foil to lift.
Seal the edges.
Place the roll, seam side down in a 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
The center will be pink because of the ham.
Place cheese wedges on top and return to oven until cheese melts.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fluffy potato casserole
directions: Put all ingredients (except onion rings) in a large bowl.
Beat at high speed until fluffy.
Put in a 9-inch square dish. Distribute onion rings over top.
Bake, uncovered, in a slow oven (300°) for about 35 minutes.
Cover with foil if onions start to overbrown.

title: christmas cutout cookies
directions: Beat eggs first.
Mix everything together.
Set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain all 3 cans of beans. Put in a large bowl. Slice onion and bell pepper. Bring vinegar, oil and sugar to a boil. Pour over beans, onion and pepper. Marinate overnight.

title: oriental vegetable casserole
directions: Drain the vegetables.
Layer half of all the ingredients in a greased casserole in the order given.
Make second layer in the same order.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: taco chicken casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in a greased baking dish.
First layer tortillas and chopped chicken.
Spoon part of tomatoes with chilies and then soup over the chicken.
Repeat with Cheddar cheese, topping each layer.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Drain fruit, reserving juices.
Bring juices to a boil in a saucepan.
Add gelatin, stirring to dissolve well and cool.
Stir in cola.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in cherries, pineapple and pecans.
Spoon into serving bowl.
Chill until set.
Makes 12 servings.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Combine the 1/4 cup syrup, the brown sugar and margarine in medium-size saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture begins to boil. Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies cereal, stirring until well coated.
Press evenly in 9-inch pie pan to form crust. Stir together peanut butter, fudge sauce and the 3 tablespoons corn syrup. Spread half the peanut butter mixture over crust.
Freeze until firm. Allow ice cream to soften slightly.

Spoon into frozen pie crust, spreading evenly. Freeze until firm. Let pie stand at room temperature about 10 minutes before cutting. Warm remaining peanut butter mixture and drizzle over top. Yields 8 servings.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Mix cup of dates with boiling water and soda; let stand until cool.
Cream shortening, honey and baking powder, then the cooled mixture and blend.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and sprinkle onto the batter in order 1/2 cup sugar, 1 package chocolate chips and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: In bowl, mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and melted butter. In casserole dish, layer broccoli first and then chicken.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Add cheese and crushed corn flakes on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa into bowl.
Blend in milk and oil.
Pour into ungreased square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch). Stir together brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa; sprinkle over batter. Pour hot water over batter.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot with ice cream.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Beat shortening at medium speed with electric mixer. Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.

title: apple bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Cream eggs, margarine and 1 cup sugar.
Stir in nuts, apples, flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and vanilla. Pour into greased bread pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture. Makes 1 loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: jello angel food desert
directions: Spray Jell-O mold with Pam.
Tear up 1 angel food cake into pieces.
Mix water and Jell-O until dissolved, stir in fruit. Pour 3/4 of mixture into mold then pour in cake.
Pour remaining 1/4 of Jell-O mixture on top.
Work or stir until all of the liquid is absorbed.
Refrigerate until set.
Serve with Cool whip in the center after removing from the mold.

title: fruit parfaits
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, stirring well.
Combine orange, banana and pineapple.
Toss lightly.
Spoon alternate layers of fruit mixture and orange juice mixture into 6 parfait glasses. Cover and chill thoroughly.
A serving amount is 1/2 cup at 87 calories.
Diabetic Exchange:
1 starch.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour in 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove.
Cool on wire rack.
Wrap in foil or plastic wrap.

title: macaroni and cheese supreme
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown hamburger with onion and celery; drain off fat.
Stir in the salt and tomato paste.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fly-off-the-plate-pancakes
directions: Resift the flour with the other dry ingredients. Beat together the egg and sour cream. Stir into flour mixture.
Add melted butter and beat until smooth. Cook on a hot griddle.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise and scoop out potato; mash.
Use 1 strip bacon per potato.
Use green onions to suit your taste.
Mix bacon, onions, sour cream, margarine and cheese together.
Add salt and pepper, if desired.
Put back into potato halves. Sprinkle more cheese on top, if desired.
Bake until heated through at 325°.
Can be frozen for later baking.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice tomatoes (approximately 1/4-inch slices).
In a mixing bowl, mix buttermilk and eggs.
Add half the salt and pepper and 1 tablespoon of flour; mix well.
Place tomato slices in the buttermilk mixture.
Preheat the oil to 350° in a heavy skillet or fryer.
Mix the remaining ingredients in a mixing bowl. Toss tomato slices in flour. Then place in oil and fry until golden brown, turning two or three times.
Cook until crisp and drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.

title: shaun's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Line pie plate with plain pastry.
Pour in filling.
Bake 45 minutes in a slow oven at 300°.
Makes a 9-inch pie.

title: chocolate fudge(to my sons james l. & robert l. martin)
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients on low heat, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon.
Bring to rolling boil, then reduce heat and boil until soft ball forms in small amount of cold water.
Set aside.

title: muffeletta mix
directions: Chop all in food processor.
Store in jars in refrigerator. Good in green salad or in sandwiches with cold cuts and cheese.

title: blueberry streusel cake
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, margarine, lemon rind and egg; beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Combine 1 1/2 cups flour and the soda; add to egg mixture at low speed.
Pour batter into a 9-inch round pan.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon flour, blueberries, cinnamon and allspice; tossing gently.
Spoon over batter, leaving 1/2-inch border.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 10 servings.

title: herbert (flo) cole's specialty
directions: Put billfold in back pocket.
Grab car keys.
Go back and get car keys to other vehicle.
Crank car and drive to the local fast food joint of your choice.
Sit in line at drive thru 15 to 20 minutes.
Go home (or to work).
Open bag.
Fuss 15 minutes because you didn't get what you ordered.
Eat it anyway.
Go to refrigerator or drink machine and get drink to replace the one you spilled on drive home (or on way to work).

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Combine evaporated milk, pumpkin, eggs, cinnamon and salt. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top of mixture.
Melt oleo and drizzle over top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350°
about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until center stops bubbling up and down.
When cold, frost with Cool Whip.

title: hamburger deluxe
directions: Mix and shape.
Wrap each patty with bacon.
Broil for 10 minutes on both sides.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in food processor until it looks like dirt. Cream other ingredients together until smooth.
Start with crushed cookies, forming layers ending with cookies.
Chill and serve.
May be decorated with green frosting, flowers and gummy worms.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until done; drain.
Saute margarine, onions and garlic.
Add flour and salt to make smooth paste.
Add milk and black pepper; cook until slightly thickened.
May need to add more milk.
Add Velveeta and sour cream; stir until melted.
Mix sauce with macaroni and pour into buttered deep casserole dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pour into a baking dish and bake for 1 hr. at 350 degrees.

title: fake lasagna
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Cook noodles and drain.
Put beef, noodles and sauce in a 9 x 13-inch pan and mix.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: monkey buns
directions: Grease an angel food cake pan with buttered flavor Crisco and set aside.
Mix together white sugar and cinnamon in small bowl. Cut biscuits into fourths and place each piece in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
When completely coated, put into angel food pan; set aside.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add hominy, cream of mushroom soup and cheese.
Put in oven.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Slice steak thinly.
Combine sugar, 2 tablespoons cornstarch, 2 tablespoons soy sauce and sherry.
Add meat and marinate approximately 1/2 hour.
Cut peppers in strips.
Combine chicken broth, 1 tablespoon soy sauce and 1 tablespoon cornstarch; set aside.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Blend salad oil and vinegar together in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Makes 2 cups.

title: wassail
directions: Put juices in an automatic percolator.
Put sugar and spices in basket.
Perk.
Serve hot.

title: sarah bing's curried ham ball
directions: Mix well and shape into a ball.
Mix 1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese and spread over ham ball.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans if desired.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Press excess liquid from zucchini.
Transfer to mixing bowl and stir in eggs, flour and salt.
Spread evenly over bottom of well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes. Remove from oven; cool.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Sprinkle zucchini with cheese. Mix olives, onions and peppers.
Sprinkle evenly over cheese.
Sprinkle with oregano and basil.
Arrange tomato slices over top and sprinkle lightly with salt.
Bake 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and zucchini is set.
Cool on wire rack 5 minutes.

title: bounty rice
directions: Saute beef until lightly browned.
Stir in tomatoes, seasonings, rice and cabbage.
Cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes or until cabbage is tender-crisp.
Stir in sour cream, onions and green peppers.
Heat and spoon into serving dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand a few minutes before serving to allow cheese to melt.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bran muffins
directions: Stir together the dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Mix cereal with milk in a bowl.
Allow to stand for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add egg and oil.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined.
Portion batter evenly into 12 greased muffin pan cups. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: weight watchers banana croquette
directions: Tear bread into small pieces.
Add egg, vanilla, sugar substitute, cinnamon and milk.
Cut banana into chunks.
Cook until lightly browned on both sides.
Serves 1.

title: chili-roni
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper in large skillet.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomatoes, water, chili mix and macaroni.
Cover; simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until macaroni is done.
Top with cheese.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat in frying pan (season to taste).
Drain off fat. Add 1 1/2 cups water and 3 or 4 beef bouillon cubes.
Thicken with flour and water to make gravy.
Add green beans.
Put in baking dish and cover with mashed potatoes, brown in oven heated to 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: no knead french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add this to flour, sugar and salt that has been sifted together.
Add enough of a second cup of water to stir up a soft and sticky dough.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk.
About 1 1/2 hours.
When dough has risen, punch down vigorously and divide into 2 round loaves.
Place in well buttered Pyrex casserole dishes, about 3 x 6-inch.
Let rise again until double.
Place in cold oven, set heat at 350° and bake 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Marinate drained shrimp overnight in shrimp sauce.
Top the softened bar of cream cheese with shrimp/sauce mixture.
Serve with crackers.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Dip chicken pieces in mixture. Arrange chicken in baking dish.
Put yams around chicken pieces. Pour remaining mixture over chicken and yams.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: mud pie
directions: First Layer (Crust): Mix the flour and pecans and press into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. Cool.

title: chicken florentine
directions: Use amounts for each serving.
Pound breast flat and dredge with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown lightly in olive oil.
In a separate pan, saute garlic, onion and chopped spinach in 1 tablespoon olive oil until wilted.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Place spinach in a small baking dish.
Top with browned breast of chicken and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanutty brownies
directions: Cream the peanut butter, margarine, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla in a large mixer bowl; beat in eggs.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in the chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: green chili
directions: Dredge meat chunks in flour seasoned with pepper.
Heat oil in large pan and brown the meat in batches.
Return all
the meat to the pan and add water to cover.
Put sliced onion on top of meat and simmer until the meat is almost tender.
Add salsa and green chilies.
Continue cooking until meat is just tender.
Add refried beans to thicken chili just before serving.
Serve with tortillas.

title: pork tenderloin(parmigiana)
directions: Marinate pork in Wish-Bone dressing overnight.
Drain.
Beat egg; add salt and pepper.
Dip tenderloin into egg mixture, then crumbs.
Brown both sides.
Be careful not to have fire too high when browning because it burns easily.
Place tenderloin in shallow pan and spaghetti sauce over meat.
I put a little sauce under the meat, also.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and top with Mozzarella cheese; cook 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and meat reaches 170° internal temperature.
Serve with spaghetti (spoon a little sauce over spaghetti), salad and garlic bread.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Mix in order listed.
Shape into balls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° about 10 to 15 minutes or until done.
(May use different flavoring and dates, coconut or add anything as desired.) Yields 24 balls.

title: alaska logs
directions: Beat eggs until stiff.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Fold into eggs.
Add dates and nuts.
Bake in two 8 x 8 x 2-inch pans, greased, at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes approximately 5 dozen cookies.
Store in airtight containers.

title: peanut double chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
Lightly grease cookie sheets or line with parchment papers.
Cream butter and sugars in large bowl until blended.

title: tally ho tomato pudding(a famous toledo recipe)
directions: Combine sugar, puree and water and cook 5 minutes.
While tomato mixture is cooking, put bread cubes in a casserole and pour butter over.
Add tomato mixture.
Bake 50 minutes in 325° oven.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cream crust ingredients together.
Put in greased 10-inch pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: Place ground beef in 10-inch skillet with oil.
Cook.
Measure instant onion flakes and sprinkle over meat.
Cover and brown. Add tomato sauce.
Add hot water and bite size spaghetti.
Add seasoning mix, salt and stir.
Cover and simmer on lowest heat for 25 minutes.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Bake graham cracker crust according to directions on package in 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Whip cold milk until stiff.
In another large bowl, cream the cream cheese and sugar.
In small boiler, bring water to a boil and add Jell-O; stir well.
Add hot Jell-O mixture to cream cheese and sugar, stirring well.
Blend whipped cream into this mixture.
Pour over baked crust and sprinkle top with graham crumbs.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Heat sugar, salt and vinegar until sugar and salt dissolves. Let cool.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Put in refrigerator. Will keep all winter.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Beat shortening at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit baking soda, salt and baking powder.

title: cherry pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Whip cream in separate bowl, then mix with mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell. Spoon cherry pie filling on top.

title: persimmon pudding(kip's own)
directions: Beat buttermilk and soda well with mixer.
Add each ingredients in order as listed, beating together after each addition.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan
at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
After it sets, middle will fall.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and oleo in a bowl, mixing well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice ice cream and press over cookie mixture.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup. Top with pecans.
Freeze until firm.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Place in unbaked pie crust.
Put top crust on; flute pie.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: quick quesadillas
directions: Place tortilla on microwave-safe plate.
Place cheese on half of tortilla.
Fold tortilla in half; cover with a paper towel. Microwave on High for 25 to 40 seconds, or until cheese starts to melt.
Let cool; cut.
Serve with salsa.
A great snack for children to make.

title: summertime chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, whisk together first 6 ingredients.
(For curried chicken salad, whisk in curry powder).
Stir in chicken, peaches, celery and green onions.
Cover and chill.
Before serving, stir in almonds, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.
Calories per serving:

title: alabama chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and marinate chicken at least 1 hour (but can be 2 to 4 days). When ready to cook, combine pancake mix and water.
Dip each piece chicken in batter and deep-fry 1 to 2 minutes or until a golden brown.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Place 1/2 of mixture in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Let congeal, spread with layer of sour cream and nuts.
Pour remaining jello on top.
Congeal and serve.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour bottoms and sides of pans.
In large bowl, blend all ingredients at medium speed for about 2 to 3 minutes. Pour batter into prepared pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Cool.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In medium saucepan, combine cornstarch, salt, dry mustard and pepper.
Stir in milk until smooth.
Add margarine, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Reserve 1/4 cup cheese for topping. Stir in remaining cheese until melted.
Add elbows.
Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 25 minutes, or until hot and bubbly. Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together and put into unbaked pie shell. Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: pineapple baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook beans with salt, bay leaf and cumin.
Simmer in a tightly covered pot for about 2 hours.
Add oil and continue cooking until beans are tender.
Add more water if necessary.
Add other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste. Pour mixture into a casserole dish and place in a 275 degree oven for one hour or so.
Can be made ahead and can be frozen.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into a 2-quart casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown meats.
Drain.
Add chili powder, cumin, salt, pepper, garlic, Tabasco, oregano and water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add cornmeal and cook 30 minutes uncovered.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and melted butter.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla, then pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then for 35 minutes or until done.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix together flour and sugar; set aside.
Place margarine, cocoa and water in saucepan; bring to boil.
Remove from heat and pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Mix well; add remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch greased pan. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Flour and brown on both sides in oil.
Dice onions, tomato soup, 1 cup water and salt and pepper to taste.
Add to meat and simmer until tender.

title: deviled crab cakes
directions: Saute onions in butter until clear.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly and form into patties or stuff into cleaned crab shells.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until browned.
May be frozen on a cookie sheet uncooked, then kept frozen in freezer bags until ready to thaw and bake.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well sugar, oil and eggs.
Add slices to flour and add to mixture.
Add water, flour, raisins and nuts to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes for large loaf pans or 55
for small pans.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out and cut.

title: easy coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar, then add eggs, sour cream and vanilla. Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to above mixture.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Put half the batter in greased and floured angel food pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the cinnamon mixture on batter.
Add 1/2 cup nuts.
Add remaining batter on top and spread the rest of the cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Blend the lemon juice and the Eagle Brand milk.
Add the strawberries and the Cool Whip and blend together.
Pour into a baked shell or a crumb crust.
Refrigerate for several hours until chilled through.
Makes a great summer dessert.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Set butter to soften.
Knead in sugar until creamy.
Add flour, mixing with fingers.
Roll dough (dough will be stiff) and cut cookies with a 2-inch cookie cutter.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Pierce each cookie in center with a table fork. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Watch carefully!
Remove just as they have a slight tint.

title: sparkling raspberry cooler
directions: In a two quart nonmetal pitcher, combine juice concentrate and
sparkling water.
Stir to blend.
Serve over ice cubes or crushed ice.

title: wall, s. d. famous chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Before serving add the shoestring potatoes.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins and boiling water until dry.
Cool before adding to batter.
Mix rest of ingredients thoroughly.
Add raisins. Roll balls the size of walnuts in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Beat eggs; add milk.
Mix all together.
Add corn and margarine.

title: mom's chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Mix in 1 1/2 qt. saucepan, pudding, sugar, milk and butter. Cook and stir to full all over boil.
Lower heat and keep stirring while it boils slowly for 3 minutes.
Take off heat.
Stir in walnuts.
Beat until mixture starts to thicken.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Put in refrigerator until cooled.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute and cook with butter until onion gets clear.
Mix with rice and consomme.
Put in casserole and bake at 350° until rice is done.

title: no fat green beans
directions: Place all ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: three way cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, then pour into greased cake pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dilled pickled okra
directions: Note:
Need 6 clean hot pint jars and lids.

title: pickled cucumbers
directions: Place thinly sliced onion and cucumbers in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over. Marinate for 24 hours before serving.

title: golden onion rings
directions: Cut onions into 1/4-inch thick.
Separate into rings.
Combine remaining ingredients, beating together just until all dry ingredients are well moistened.
Coat onion rings well with batter.
Fry a few at a time in deep hot fat (375°), stirring once with fork to separate rings.
When onions are golden, drain thoroughly on paper towels.
Just before serving, sprinkle with salt.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: You may use ham or sausage or all 3 meats.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Cook chicken.
Cool and break into small pieces.
Simmer chicken soup with spices for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Grate cheese.
Layer like lasagna.
Tear tortillas in quarters and line a 9 1/2 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Spoon half of soup mixture over tortillas.
Sprinkle half of chicken pieces over soup.
Sprinkle half of green chilies over chicken.
Sprinkle half of Longhorn cheese over chilies.
Sprinkle half of Jack cheese over the Longhorn cheese.
Do second layer the same.

title: old henry bars
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: london broil sizzler
directions: Cut both sides diamond pattern 1/8-inch deep.
Heat butter; add onion and salt.
Mix remaining.
Brush half on first side. Set oven to broil.
Place top of steak 2 to 3 inches from heat. Broil 5 to 7 minutes or until brown.
Cook top about 1 to 2 minutes longer than bottom of steak.
Turn steak; brush remaining mixture on steak.
Broil 5 minutes until brown.
Cut on slant; top with onions.
Serve.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend well and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: batter fried fish
directions: Cut fish into serving pieces.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Drop egg yolk in center.
Add water and melted fat and mix well.
Fold in beaten egg white.
Dry fish pieces and dip into batter.
Heat shortening to 365°.
Drop fish into hot oil for 4 to 6 minutes.
Drain onto paper towels.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour water over 100% Bran. Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, milk and 100% Bran. Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture. Add All-Bran and let stand overnight in refrigerator before baking. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen. Batter keeps in refrigerator for 7 weeks.

title: carrot appetizer
directions: Beat cheese.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Shape into a carrot and chill.
Use celery tops as green top of carrot.
Serve with crackers.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients and pour over chicken in 13 x 11 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Bake, covered, for 2 hours at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: strawberry tunnel cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Invert cake onto serving plate.
Cut 1/2 inch slice crosswise from top of cake; set aside.
With sharp knife, cut around cake 1 inch from center hole and 1 inch from outer edge, leaving cake walls 1 inch thick.
Remove cake from center, leaving 1 inch thick base on bottom of cake.
Reserve cake pieces.

title: raspberry almond bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and almond extract and beat.
Add flour, baking powder and salt and blend well.
Spread in ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Smooth surface.
Using a wet finger, make 5 to 7 diagonal indentations.
Fill with jam.
Bake 12 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken and yellow rice
directions: Brown onion and bell pepper.
Mix rice with onions, bell pepper, chicken, broth and water.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes.
Add sugar peas and simmer for 10 more minutes.

title: chicken and chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour soup into a 1-quart casserole dish; add milk and mix.
Add chicken, potato chips, peas and carrots.
Mix well.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top and bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: all-bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over All-Bran cereal.
Cover and set aside. In another bowl, mix sugar, eggs, buttermilk, Crisco, flour, salt and soda.
Add soaked bran and stir.
Place in covered container in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugars, butter, salt and milk to softball stage.
Add peanut butter just before removing from fire.
Do not stir.
Cool to room temperature.
Add vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Pour out into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Let cool.
Cut in squares.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Heat beans
and drain.
Fry bacon crisp.
Mix sugar and vinegar and
add to bacon grease and heat.
Slice onion on top of beans; pour liquid over.
Put bacon on top and serve.

title: munchy crunchy cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together the margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add flour and soda; stir well.
Add nuts, oats and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix softened butter, powdered sugar, peanut butter and Rice Krispies well and shape into small balls.
In double boiler, melt remaining ingredients.
Dip balls into mixture with toothpicks and put on waxed paper until dry.

title: hot party dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread and set aside.
Cut top out of bread.
(You will put top back on to cook.)
Take out middle of bread and leave empty shell.
Put mixed "stuff" inside bread shell and replace top.
Double wrap in foil.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Remove and serve hot with Fritos.

title: cashew and date cookies
directions: Combine butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to butter mixture.
Stir in coconut, cashews and dates.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 300° oven about 20 minutes, or until done.

title: bath salts
directions: Measure 3 cups Epsom salts into one bowl.
In the other bowl, mix 1 tablespoon of glycerin, a few drops of food coloring and enough of your favorite perfume or cologne to make the mixture pleasantly fragrant.
Add this mixture to the Epsom salts and mix well.
If the fragrance is not strong enough, you can add more perfume or cologne.
Put the bath salts in a decorative jar that seals tightly.
It looks lovely, and a warm bath is a wonderful way to relax a day away!

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and juice from orange slices in large mixing bowl for 3 or 4 minutes.
Fold in orange slices.
Grease and flour 3 cake pans.
Bake cake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Frost with Mandarin Orange Cake Icing.

title: bonnie's fudge
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients.
Set aside.
In heavy pan, put the Milnot, sugar and oleo.
Bring mixture to rolling boil; boil for 6 minutes (burns easily).
Pour Milnot mixture over first mixture; mix very well.
Pour into greased pan.
Makes about 4 pounds.

title: quick and easy fudge
directions: Blend together cocoa and sugar.
Add oleo and milk.
Cook on High for three minutes in the microwave.
Take out and stir well. Cook two to three minutes more.
Remove and stir well.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Stir well.
Place in buttered dish.
Cool.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter or oleo and sugar.
Alternate egg and flour and mix well.
Add flavorings.
Use lined, greased tube pan. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until done.
Test with toothpick.

title: creamy vegetable mold
directions: Prepare sauce mix according to package directions; let stand 10 minutes.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water. Stir in sauce, lemon juice and dill weed.
Beat with rotary beater until well blended.
Chill until partially set.
Put carrots in blender; cover with cold water.
Cover and blend a few seconds or until coarsely chopped.
Drain well.
Repeat with cucumber and green pepper.
Fold vegetables into jello.

title: deluxe peas and mushrooms
directions: Cook fresh peas in a small amount of boiling, salted water just until tender (10 to 12 minutes).
Or cook frozen peas according to package directions.
Drain well.
Cook mushrooms and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Add cooked peas and pimiento.
Cover; heat through.
Serves 4.

title: veal stew
directions: In a heavy casserole, brown the veal in the butter.
Add the wine, water, parsley, garlic, bay leaf and salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for two hours.
Check occasionally and add more wine and water (two parts water to one part wine) as needed.
After the two hours, mix the flour with a little of cooking liquid, then add it back into the stew.
Add the mushrooms and the onions and simmer for an additional thirty minutes.
Serve with thick slices of good, warm, crusty bread and perhaps a salad.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook for about 1/2 hour.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in large bowl and mix well with a fork.
Add shortening and mix with a fork until ingredients are crumbly.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook meat and onion; drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well and place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. If you use bacon, cut in small pieces and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion, drain.
Add tomatoes and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put into baking dish, stirring in half of the cheese.
Sprinkle remaining amount on top.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix oatmeal, flour and brown sugar.
Put in melted butter; mix until crumbly.
Put 1/2 of mixture in bottom of pan, then put cranberry sauce on top.
Cover with rest of mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Brown chicken in skillet using the butter.
Put chicken in a baking pan.
Season to taste with the red pepper, lemon pepper and salt.
Cook in the oven for 15 to 20 minutes until tender at 350°.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, Miracle Whip and cocoa.
Add dissolved soda and stir until no lumps.
Bake 45 minutes in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350°.

title: california prune cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, then eggs (one at a time).
Beat thoroughly.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture alternately with prune liquid.
Add vanilla, prunes and nuts.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven until tests done.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender.
Remove and save one cup of broth.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces and lay in bottom of greased casserole dish (9 x 13-inches).

title: mom's biscuits
directions: In a bowl, combine flour and oil well.
Make a well in the center and add milk.
Gradually stir flour in from sides until smooth and all flour is mixed in.

Turn onto floured board and add flour in as you knead until dough is soft and smooth (not sticky). Roll out into a 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a sharp knife or biscuit cutter and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serves 6.

title: ralph gragg's salsa(makes enough for all of your friends)
directions: Drain tomatoes; chop or coarsely grind tomatoes.
Add onions. Add sugar, garlic, chilies, pimentos, olives, tomato puree, salt and pepper.
Stir together and pour olive oil over top of all.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in oblong baking dish. Bake at 350° oven until cheese is melted and browned.

title: grape juice punch
directions: Add to ice in punch bowl.

title: calico bean bake
directions: While rice is cooking, pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 1/2-inch strips.
Sprinkle with paprika and allow to stand while preparing other ingredients.

title: penuche frosting
directions: Melt the butter.
Add the brown sugar.
Boil and stir on low heat about 1 minute.
Add the hot milk; stir constantly until it thickens somewhat.
Remove from heat; cool a few minutes.
While still warm, add about 1/4 cup or more confectioners sugar, depending on how thick you like your frosting to be.

title: strawberry angel food dessert
directions: Tear cake into bite-size pieces.
Place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Stir in strawberries.
Pour over cake pieces.
Refrigerate overnight. Cover with whipped topping before serving.

title: molasses cookies(overnight)
directions: Mix sugar, salt, ginger, flour and soda in sifter.
Combine molasses, shortening and milk.
Mix together and let stand (covered) in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out and cut in any preferred shape.
Bake in moderate oven, 350° to 375°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; add salt and place in casserole.
Cover with butter and cheese; add cracker crumbs.
Pour 1 stick melted butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix well. Form into balls and chill.

title: freezer pickle
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and salt.
Let stand for two hours. Combine the other ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Boil one minute. Pour over cucumbers and onions when it cools.
Stir well with a wooden spoon.
Let stand in refrigerator for three days.
Stir each day; put in containers and freeze.
Will keep well in freezer for a long time.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in wide frying pan on med. heat.
Add onion. Cook and stir for about 5 minutes until soft.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Turn up heat to high.
Cook and stir until liquid is nearly gone, about 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a 1-quart microproof bowl, mix corn syrup, sugar, salt and peanuts.
Microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and butter, continue on High for 2 or 3 minutes.
Mixture should be slightly browned.
Add baking soda and stir quickly.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet, let cool.
Break into pieces.
Makes 1 pound.
(Double cook 10 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook 7 minutes, then add rest.)

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix pineapple, cherries and marshmallows together; drain all juice off.
Beat egg yolks, butter and lemon juice together; cook until real thick (careful not to curdle).
Thin with a small amount of whipping cream (be sure all juice is drained off fruit).
Whip the whipping cream and fold into cooked mixture, then fold into salad.
Best to let stand 24 hours.

title: cole slaw
directions: Cut cabbage, carrots and green pepper; mix together.
Put the salt on top of this.
Let stand 1 hour, then squeeze out and drain. Boil the vinegar, sugar, water and celery seed together for 1 minute.
Cool, then pour mixture over the drained cabbage.
May be frozen or kept in the refrigerator for over a week.

title: recipe for a happy home
directions: Combine love and understanding.
Add courtesy, thoughtfulness and helpfulness.
Sift together thoroughly, then stir in equal amounts of work and culture.
Fold in generous amount of worship. Place in a pan well-greased with security and lined with respect for personality.
Sprinkle lightly with a sense of humor.
Allow to set in an atmosphere of democratic planning and of mutual sharing.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in oil.
Add tomato sauce and tomatoes, broken up.
This mixture should be placed in a large casserole dish (largest Corning Ware roaster).
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Drain.
Mix into tomatoes and onions.
Add seasonings.
Mix in deboned chicken and grated cheese.
Reserve some cheese for top or add more if desired.
Heat oven to 350° and bake for 15 to 30 minutes until bubbly.
It will serve 6 to 10 people.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salt water until tender; drain broccoli and corn.
Put oleo in a heavy pot with chopped onion.
Saute until tender, but not brown.
Add vegetables and soup; mix well.
Pour into a casserole dish that has been sprayed.
Cover with cheese and bake in 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: cabbage pepper relish
directions: Grate or chop well peppers, cabbage and onions.
Mix sugar, vinegar and salt.
Mix well and let come to a good boil.
Put in pint jars and seal.
Good with pinto beans.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and onions in water until tender (about 5 minutes).
Add seasonings, butter and cheese.
Cook until melted. Combine 2/3 cup water and flour, then add to soup and stir briskly. Cook until thickened.
Turn on low and add both milks.
Cook only until hot.

title: parmesan cheese straws or wafers
directions: Put knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add cheese and butter.
Process until blended.
Add flour, salt and red pepper; process about 30 seconds or until mixture forms a ball.
Stop often to scrape down sides of bowl.
Use cookie press for cheese straws or roll into 36 (3/4-inch) balls; flatten each ball with pecan half.
Brush with
milk.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes for straws, 10 minutes for rounds or until light brown.

title: luscious lemon bars
directions: Combine ingredients.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: buttered corn and peas
directions: Combine all ingredients
and simmer over a low fire for 20 to 30 minutes,
using
the
liquids
from
the corn and the peas.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with crushed up Ritz crackers and thin pats of margarine.
Bake covered 20 minutes and uncovered 5 or 10 minutes in 350° or 370° oven.

title: mushroom barley casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir; add glass of water and bake 30 to 45 minutes more (checking halfway through in case a bit more water is needed) until barley is tender.
(Great as side dish with pot roast or chicken!)

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine shrimp, eggs, pimientos, celery, green pepper and onion in a large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, salt, pepper and lemon juice; add to shrimp mixture and toss lightly.
Serve on lettuce leaves with pickle slices, wedges and stuffed olives.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Put one slice cheese on each chicken breast.
Mix a little milk with soup and pour over chicken.
Cover with dressing. Drizzle with butter.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: holiday divinity
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup, water and salt to 248°.
Cover and boil for 3 minutes.
Uncover and place thermometer in pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Grease muffin pans and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon almonds in each cup.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Blend in egg.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream. Fold in pineapple.
Spoon into pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until browned and done.
Let stand in pans 5 to 10 minutes.
Turn pans over onto platter.
Leave pans in position 5 to 10 minutes. Remove pans.
Blend together butter, powdered sugar and juice. Spread 1 teaspoon glaze over each muffin.

title: rice pudding(no baking needed)
directions: Boil rice and milk together; bring to a rapid boil.
Reduce heat to a slow simmer.
Simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Add raisins.
In a separate bowl beat eggs and sugar together; add vanilla.
Pour this mixture into rice; boil and stir for about 5 minutes.
Top with nutmeg and cinnamon.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix the ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gooey squares
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 2 eggs in large bowl and mix well.
Pat batter into the bottom of a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup chocolate chips on top.
In mixing bowl, blend cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add 2 beaten eggs and mix well.
Spread mixture on top of bottom layer. Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup of chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top will be golden.
Yields 4 dozen squares.

title: coconut monster cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Set aside.
In a large bowl of mixer cream butter.
Add sugars and beat until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients, then oats, chopped apple and 1 1/3 cup of the coconut.
Combine well.
Then drop by 1/4 cup portions onto ungreased cookie sheets. Flatten slightly.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until golden.
Cool 2 minutes on sheet, then transfer to wire rack.
Makes 14 to 15 cookies.
You can also just press dough in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, beat Eagle Brand milk and peanut butter until smooth. Add biscuit mix and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Press milk chocolate candy kiss in center of each ball immediately after baking.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onion and pepper in shortening in large skillet. Add ground beef; brown well. Add tomato juice, rice, chili powder and seasonings; stir well. Pour into casserole; cover. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spray dish with Pam.
Cook chicken and cool.
Melt butter in hot water and mix with dressing.
Put 1/2 of this mixture in the bottom of a baking dish.
Add chicken.
Combine soups and 1 can of water.
Pour over chicken.
(Take a knife and stick in the mixture.)
Add the other half of dressing.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour loaf pan.
Whisk together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda in medium bowl.
In small bowl, mix mashed bananas, milk and vanilla.
Using electric mixer, beat shortening in large bowl until creamy. Gradually beat in sugar.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat banana mixture and flour mixture into shortening.
Stir in pecans.
Transfer to prepared pan.
Bake bread about 1 hour.
Cool 5 minutes.
Place on rack to cool completely.

title: dressing for potato salad or slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients well before mixing with slaw or potato salad.

title: layer bars
directions: Mix graham cracker
crumbs and margarine.
Put in dish. Add coconut on	top
crust.
Add butterscotch chips, chocolate chips and English
walnuts.
Pour
Eagle Brand milk over this. Bake at 350°
until
brown,
about	30
minutes.
Cool
before cutting. Let get cold before taking out of dish.

title: cheese soup
directions: Add potatoes to broth in large kettle and cook over moderate heat until potatoes are tender.
Heat oil in skillet and add onion and garlic.
Stir-fry until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes to skillet and stir about ten minutes until mixture has thickened a little.
Add to potato broth mixture and cook about five more minutes.
Add cheese to hot soup and serve as cheese is melting.

title: killer kielbasa
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a greased casserole, layer kielbasa, potatoes and cheese, finishing with potatoes, but saving some cheese. Mix soup and milk; pour over. Top with reserved cheese. Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: italian beef
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot. Cook 24 hours on low or 12 hours on high. Stir often. Serve on buns or deli rolls.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour and sour cream alternately, then vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in well-greased pan at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in preheated oven.

title: raspberry jam
directions: Remove stems, wash and crush berries.
Mix well with the sugar.
Bring to a full rolling boil.
Stir occasionally before the rolling boil, then add the Certo, stirring until it boils hard for 1 minute.
Remove from stove.
Remove the foam.
Pour into hot jars and seal at once.
Fill jars 1/8-inch from top.

title: creamy fruit pie
directions: Let cream cheese stand out until room temperature.
Beat all ingredients together until smooth and creamy.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
By hand, beat eggs.
Add half and half and sugar.
Mix well.
Add baking powder and mix well.
Add corn; stir and pour into an 8 x 10-inch greased casserole dish.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: egg nog dip
directions: In saucepan, combine egg nog and cornstarch until smooth. Bring to a boil and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream.
Cool completely.

title: special k cookies
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to a boil.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add Special K cereal.
Mix and drop on wax paper.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until beef is browned.
Add the rest of ingredients except the cheese.
Mix and put in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar, pineapple, beaten eggs, vinegar and vanilla in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add coconut and mix well.
Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell and refrigerate.

title: special k bars
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup to a boil, about 2 minutes in microwave.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with melted milk chocolate chips.
Chill and cut into bars.

title: dream cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on box. Refrigerate. Mix pudding according to directions on box. Pour over cool cake. Pour cherry pie filling over pudding. Spread Cool Whip on top. Refrigerate.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat butter over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and frozen vegetables.
Pour in pastry lined pan and cook, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes at 425°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple-leek soup
directions: Melt butter (or heat oil) in saucepan.
Add leeks, stirring often, and heat 5 to 7 minutes.
Add potatoes, apples and chicken broth.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes until apples and potatoes are tender.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Fold together Cool Whip and pudding.
Add pineapple, oranges, banana and cherries.
Add cottage cheese and nuts.
Needs to set up 2 hours at least.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ground turkey, onion, egg, bread crumbs, nutmeg, allspice, thyme, salt and pepper.
Form into balls about the size of a walnut.
Heat a small amount of oil in a heavy skillet over moderately high heat.
Brown meatballs; remove from skillet.
Add enough oil to skillet to equal 3 tablespoons.
When hot, stir in 1/4 cup flour.
Continue stirring until flour is golden brown. Pour in beef broth, stirring constantly.
When gravy has thickened, return meatballs to skillet.
Reduce heat; add parsley. Simmer for 20 minutes; do not boil.
Serve over cooked noodles. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: beefy baked beans(prepare 1 day in advance)
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Add beans.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to meat and beans.
Place in casserole or bean pot and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix together first 7 items and press into a roll.
Chill overnight or longer.
Cut into slices (1 1/2-inch thick).
Roll pieces in flour and brown on both sides.
Place pieces in roasting dish and cover with 1 can mushroom soup and 1 can water.
Bake at 300°
for 1 1/2 hours.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine, then a layer of nuts, a layer of chocolate chips, and a layer of coconut. Pour the milk over evenly. Bake 25 minutes at 350°F. until light brown.

title: dutch pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place butter in round cake pan and heat in 400° oven.
Blend flour, milk and eggs in blender for 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour into heated pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
This rises with flat center.
Serve warm with topping(s) of choice.

title: pork tenderloin with grilled pineapple
directions: Combine 1/4 cup soy sauce with mustard.
Coat pork in marinade.
Chill 15 minutes or overnight.
Remove pork from marinade.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
In covered grill, arrange medium-hot coals around drip pan.
Place pork on grid over pan. Cover; grill and cook 45 to 50 minutes, or internal temperature registers 150° on meat thermometer.
Twist crown from pineapple. Cut pineapple in half lengthwise.
Cut fruit from shell with knife.
Slice fruit crosswise.
Combine marmalade with remaining 2 tablespoons soy sauce.
Last 10 minutes of cooking, arrange pineapple slices on grid over coals.
Baste pineapple and pork generously with marmalade mixture, turning once; slice pork. Serve with pineapple.

title: pecan pick-ups
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Divide into 24 sections; press into miniature muffin tins to form pastry.
Mix remaining ingredients; fill cups. Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: homemade bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Add 2 cups flour; stir well.
Now add softened yeast. Add rest of flour until stiff.
Knead 8 minutes; let rise until double in large greased bowl, about 1 1/2 hours.
Keep top of bread greased, then punch down; let rise again until double, about 45 minutes.
Divide into 2 equal parts; shape into loaves.
Let rise again until doubled.
Bake in a 350° oven until done, approximately 30 minutes.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken in a single layer on a baking dish.
Place 1 slice of cheese on each piece.
Pour soup evenly over chicken. Spread stuffing and top with pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tamale-hominy casserole
directions: Arrange tamales in a baking dish.
Remove wrappers.
Pour hominy over tamales.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in microwave on High 12 minutes.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Layer as ordered in a serving dish.
Refrigerate.
Serve with chips.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread into two graham cracker crusts. Keep refrigerated.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix beans, catsup, sugar and mustard.
Put in casserole.
Top with bacon.
Bake in slow oven until bacon is done.

title: rick's secret sauce
directions: Mix and put in spray bottle.
Spray on food while cooking.

title: skillet veal
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet, brown veal.
Cut into 1-inch squares, season with salt, stir in tomatoes, Spatini spaghetti sauce and sherry.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat, cover, simmer 10 minutes.
Add onions, mushrooms, liquid and vegetables.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Combine berries and sugar.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Stirring occasionally, stir pectin in water, bring to a boil and boil rapidly 1 minute; stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add berries and stir about 2 minutes.
Pour into jars.
Cover and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Refrigerate until gelled, seal with wax.
Store in freezer.

title: baked chili rellenos
directions: In buttered baking dish, layer chilies and cheese. Beat eggs, pepper and sour cream.
Pour over cheese and chilies.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Blend graham cracker crumbs and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture along with remaining ingredients.
Mix by hand until well moistened.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with topping while hot.

title: white raisin pie
directions: Melt butter and mix with sugar.
Add 2 beaten eggs and the pecans, then add raisins and vinegar. Pour into pie shell and bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease bread pan with shortening.
Mix sugar, bananas, oil and eggs in a bowl with a wooden spoon.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes.

title: mattie padgett's bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Mix yeast with warm water and sugar and let rise.
Blend with mixer the yeast mixture and egg mixture. To this add about half the flour.
Mix with mixer and add remaining
flour, mixing again.
Cover with foil and let stand overnight in refrigerator.	Dump bowl of dough onto floured counter and make into 6 loaves.
Roll and cut.
Preheat oven to 200°.
Turn off and let loaves set for 1 1/2 hours.
Leaving loaves still in oven, turn oven to 300° for 30 minutes.
Cover with butter immediately when taken out.

title: italian cheesecake
directions: Combine cheeses and beat until smooth.
Add sugar and eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and let cake sit in oven for 2 hours longer.
Cool and refrigerate.
Serve with raspberries, if desired.
Makes 16 servings.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Chop in food processor. Combine all ingredients. Chill for several hours.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put the bread and milk in a buttered baking dish and let stand a few minutes.
Mix the egg, sugar and salt.
Add vanilla.
Add to first mixture.
Dot the top with butter and bake at 350° until the top is brown.
Serves 4.

title: nachos
directions: Brown ground beef, drain fat and add taco seasoning mix and water. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cubed Mexican Velveeta cheese.
Simmer until all cheese is melted (10 minutes). Serve over warm nacho chips.
Top with green onions, sour cream and salsa.

title: diabetic banana special(calories: 198)
directions: Peel the banana and cut in half.
Split the one-half, which is to be used in the recipe.
Soften the peanut butter and spread in between the two slices of banana.
Press two halves together. Place in dessert dish and sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Pour over it the evaporated milk, which has been slightly beaten.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt in a saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring gently, until sugar dissolves. Cook over medium heat, without stirring, to hard-ball stage, 254°.
Remove from heat and stir in margarine and vanilla. Place popped corn in a large pan. Pour hot syrup over top,
stirring well with a wooden spoon. Grease hands with margarine and shape mixture into balls. Place on wax paper to dry. Wrap in plastic and store in cool, dry place. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Place potatoes into a greased 9 x 12 pan.
Put in butter and sprinkle with basil and garlic powder.
Cover pan with aluminum foil and bake at 4450 degrees for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Put 1 cookie roll in 11 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla and place on top of cookie roll in pan.
Slice the other cookie roll and put on top of cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions and garlic in fat.
Stir in ground beef, mushrooms, salt, pepper and paprika.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add 3 tablespoons flour mixed in 1 cup bouillon and simmer 10 minutes. Stir in 1 cup sour cream.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chicken enchiladas(low-fat)
directions: Cube chicken and, over low heat, cook in Teflon skillet.
Add 1/2 chopped onion, garlic and cumin.
Cover.
Cook on low, stirring occasionally, until tender.
Remove to large bowl.

title: fettucini with feta and shrimp
directions: Steam and clean shrimp; set aside.
Dice Feta and set aside. In a large skillet, melt butter and olive oil together with chopped clove of garlic.
Chop the basil and saute it with the oil and butter.
Add tomatoes to butter/oil mixture and let cook for 15 minutes.
At this time you can add the red and white pepper and Tabasco to your own taste.
The spicier the better!
Five minutes before serving, add shrimp and Feta; stir.
You do not want to totally melt the Feta.
