You want it to be in chunks on the pasta. Pour over fettucini and sprinkle with Parmesan.
By the way, cook the fettucini first according to directions.
You may want to cut the tomatoes in half when adding to the skillet.

title: julie's hot spinach dip
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Excellent to use with crackers, fondue dip or use your imagination.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put in a 2-quart casserole.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with margarine.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: beef goulash
directions: Roll beef in bread crumbs. Brown well in oil.
Add onion and garlic.
Stir and cook a few minutes.
Add tomatoes, water, bay leaf, paprika, salt and pepper. Stir well to loosen browned bits. Cover and simmer about 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender. Stir occasionally.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Refrigerate, covered, for 24 hours.
Drain.
Add the sugar, dissolved in the vinegar.
Store in fridge indefinitely, or put in containers and freeze.

title: dancer's delight
directions: Arrive 15 to 20 minutes before start of dance.
Choose table and mix with others.
Write down songs or dances on DJ's request list.
Get ready to have fun.

title: microwave pecan pie
directions: Prick pie shell well and brush with vanilla flavoring for added color.
Cook pie shell in microwave on slow cook for 5 to 6 minutes, if frozen.
If fresh, cook 6 to 7 minutes.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Combine ingredients in medium size bowl and microwave until soft enough to dip chips.

title: fannie mae fudge(this is the real recipe)
directions: Mix sugar, milk, vanilla and butter in heavy pan.
Bring to boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Lower fire.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Add chocolates, one at a time.
Pour into a jelly roll pan that has been greased with butter.

title: cherry winks
directions: Blend all ingredients together, then roll the cookie mixture in the crushed corn flakes. Put cookies on cookie sheet and place the halved cherries in the center of cookie; bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg, parsley, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper; gently shape into 1-inch balls. Cook meatballs in shortening in 12-inch skillet until brown. Remove meatballs from skillet; drain fat.
Heat chili sauce and jelly in skillet, stirring constantly, until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs and stir until coated.
Simmer uncovered 30 minutes. Serve hot in chafing dish.
Makes 5 dozen meatballs.

title: emmy's lasagna soup
directions: Cook and stir beef and onion until brown.
Drain.
Stir in sauce mix, broth, corn, tomatoes and cheese, breaking up tomatoes. Heat to boiling.
Stir in noodles and zucchini.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
If too thick, thin with tomato juice.

title: barb's zucchini relish
directions: In a very large bowl, pour salt over all vegetables and mix well; let stand at least 3 hours.
Stir occasionally and after at least 3 hours, rinse well.
In a large pot, cook together almost to a boil the vinegar, sugar and spices.
When almost boiling, add vegetable slices and once again, bring almost to boil.
Pour into prepared, sterilized jars.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients and set aside.
Cream next 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Add oatmeal mixture, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan 55 minutes at 350°.
After cake is cool, top with topping mixture.
Broil 2 minutes or until topping bubbles.

title: horn of plenty
directions: Mix together Jell-O, orange or pineapple juice and whole cranberry sauce and chill in mixing bowl.
Cut and dice apple, celery stalks and walnuts.
Fold in above ingredients to Jell-O mixture.
Put in favorite mold and chill until firm.
Great with Thanksgiving dinner.

title: perfect pickles
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Fit cucumbers into 2 (1-quart) jars.
Pour in enough of vinegar mixture to cover cucumbers. Tighten lids and refrigerate at least 1 week before serving to develop flavor.
These delicious pickles can be kept refrigerated for up to 3 months.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli according to directions and drain.
Combine ingredients.
Place in a greased casserole dish and cover with crushed Ritz crackers and pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, melon, celery, cashews and scallions.
Add ginger to yogurt.
Pour yogurt over mixture and mix well.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Dice stew meat, then add potatoes and onions.
Cook in boiling water until meat is tender.

title: marinated black-eyed peas
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, garlic, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour in drained peas.
Cover and refrigerate 2 or 3 days.

title: spread for cocktail rye
directions: Mix well. Spread on rye bread.
Top with slice of cucumber and sprinkle of dill weed.

title: chipped beef fondue
directions: Mix ingredients and stir until smooth.
Serve in fondue bowl over heat.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quaker prize winning meat loaf
directions: Heat oven 350 degrees.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly but firmly.
Press into 8 x 4 inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour or until meat is no longer pink and juices run clear.
Drain.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving. 8 servings.

title: dewberry pie
directions: Spread berries evenly in pie shell.
Mix sugar and cornstarch and sprinkle over berries.
Add lemon juice and nutmeg.
Cover with top crust.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and continue baking 45 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs, mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Beat well, then add milk, corn and vanilla.
Add margarine last and beat well. Preheat oven to 350° and bake approximately 30 minutes or until pudding does not shake.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine crabmeat, eggs, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Mix lightly.
Add enough flour to make the crab mixture easy to handle and shape into patties.
Fry in vegetable oil, browning both sides (they will fry fairly quickly).

title: too good to last
directions: Mix flour and sugar together in a large bowl.
Add all dry ingredients; mix and set aside.

To the beaten eggs, add the oil, vanilla, pineapple and bananas. Add the dry mixture. Stir just enough to mix well. Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 or 60 minutes or until cake begins to pull away from pan. Cake is better when a day or so old.

title: apea cake
directions: Mix flour, sugars, Crisco and Karo like pie dough.
Combine milk, baking soda and vinegar.
Add to dough mix.
Shape into 3 cakes.
Put into 8-inch greased and floured cake tins.
Make design on top with fork.
Sprinkle with granular sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: brown rice #1
directions: Brown rice in butter.
Pour into casserole dish.
Pour soup and broth.
Cover with tinfoil.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour at 400°.

title: onion quiche
directions: Saute onions in margarine until crystalline.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Place in a prepared Pet-Ritz shell.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°, then at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat with onions and seasoning; add spaghetti sauce and water.
In lightly greased casserole dish, layer noodles (uncooked) twice, 1/3 meat, 1 cup cottage cheese, 1 cup cheeses and end up with meat and cheese on top.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.

title: easy caramel icing
directions: Boil constantly 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Beat a little and frost your cake.

title: clam chowder
directions: Mix.
Cook in crock-pot.
Cook on low at least 6 hours.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches. Place apple slices in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican rice
directions: In large skillet, saute rice in oil until brown.
Add remaining ingredients and 2 1/4 cups water over and simmer 20 to 25 minutes until rice is tender.

title: oyster stew
directions: Blend flour, seasonings and 1/4 cup water in a 3-quart soup kettle.
Add undrained oysters and margarine.
Simmer over very low heat for 3 to 4 minutes, until edges of oysters curl, stirring gently.
Add hot milk; remove from heat and cover.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Reheat briefly.
Top servings with pats of butter. Serve with oyster crackers.
Makes enough for 8.

title: tuna buns
directions: Mix all ingredients lightly.
Fill rolls.
Wrap in foil.
Put in oven at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: hot lettuce dressing
directions: Chop bacon and fry until crisp.
Beat egg.
Add remaining ingredients to egg in a saucepan.
Add bacon and a little bacon fat.
Heat through.
Serve over greens.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In saucepan melt butter.
Blend in flour and cheese.
Add milk. Cook and stir until mixture boils, using wire whip.
Stir in cooked and drained broccoli.
Add seasonings:
salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Place in 1-quart casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marshmallows crunchies
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt butter in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows.
Stir constantly until marshmallows are melted and mixture is well blended.
Remove and stir 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and stir in Rice Krispies.
Press into pan with fingers moistened with water.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: orange cream pie
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar and flour.
Add orange and lemon juices, orange rind, beaten egg and butter.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly; chill thoroughly.
Add 1/2 pint heavy cream, whipped.
Slit angel food cake into 3 layers.
Top each slice with whipped cream mixture and place together.
Cover sides with whipped cream mixture and garnish with mandarin orange slice, if desired.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: my mother's pie dough
directions: Sift flour and salt together and cut in lard.
Add vinegar, water and egg all at once.
Mix together.
Can be put in refrigerator and used as needed or divide into balls and make crusts.
This recipe makes 2 (2-crust) pies.
To make 3 (2-crust) pies, use 4 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 extra on other ingredients.

title: super crispy fried chicken
directions: Mix salt, pepper and baking soda into buttermilk.
Dip chicken parts into buttermilk mixture, then press into flour.
Get as much flour as possible to stick to chicken.
Place each floured piece into hot oil.
Stir flour to keep loose.
Cook until well done. Drain on paper towels.
This breading is equally good on pork chops and keeps them moist on the inside while crispy on the outside.

title: chili weenie beanies
directions: Cook dry beans as usual.
When done, add chili powder.
Cut wieners in 1/2-inch lengths and add to beans.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: tomato pie
directions: Place tomatoes on bottom of pie shell.
Mix mayonnaise, cheese, chives and basil.
Place on top of tomatoes.
Sprinkle top of pie with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly and brown.
Pie serves 6.

title: osgood pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks until light colored.
Add sugar and butter, then other ingredients, adding the stiffly beaten egg whites last.
Bake in uncooked pastry shell in a 350° oven.

title: swedish bread pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in pan of water at 325°.

title: mazetti
directions: Saute ground meat, green pepper and onion; brown and drain. Cook egg noodles.
Mix all ingredients.
Top with grated Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Cook ground beef until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain off grease.
Spoon beef into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese.
Combine Bisquick, milk, and eggs; beat until smooth.
Pour mixture over casserole, covering evenly. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: creamed hamburger and cabbage
directions: Cook beef in skillet until no longer red, breaking up meat. Spoon off most of the grease. Add onion and cabbage.
Cook until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and simmer about 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: ritzy chicken
directions: Combine crackers and margarine, reserving 1 cup.
Spread the rest in 13x9x2 pan.
Spread the boiled chicken cubes over top of the Ritz layer.
In separate pan, combine soup, sour cream and chicken broth.
Pour this mixture over the chicken layer, sprinkle the cup of reserved crumbs on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 25- 30 mins.

title: egg souffle casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Butter each slice.
Place 1/2 of bread, butter side down, in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with a layer of cheese.
Mix together onion, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt, eggs and milk.
Pour 1/2 on bottom layer.
Sprinkle with meat.
Layer remaining bread on top.
Cover with layer of cheese.
Pour remaining liquid on top.

title: hearty beef stew
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven or baking dish, layer the first 12 ingredients; pour tomato juice over all. Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours, stirring occasionally, or until the meat and vegetables are tender. Remove bay leaves before serving. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: mother's icebox rolls
directions: Combine cold water, sugar and salt.
Add shortening to boiling water, then add to cold water.
Add eggs and dissolved yeast cakes.
Add 3 heaping cups sifted flour, beating well.
Add 4 to 5 more cups flour, beating as you add each cup.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes.
Put in refrigerator to rise at least several hours.
Can be kept several days.
Make out rolls and put in warm place to rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: party mix
directions: Mix oil, dressing and dill weed.
Mix cereal, crackers, nuts and pretzels.
Pour oil mixture over crackers and mix well.
Store in covered container.

title: corn casserole
directions: In skillet, fry bacon until crispy.
Remove and set aside. Pour 1/8 to 1/4 cup bacon drippings over bread crumbs; set aside. Discard all but 2 tablespoons of remaining drippings; saute onions and green peppers until tender.
Stir in corn and bacon.
Spoon into a 1 quart baking dish; sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.

title: unstuffed cabbage in a pot
directions: Cook and drain beef. Add all other ingredients, except rice. Simmer for 5 minutes. Add rice. Cover and cook until rice and cabbage are done.

title: stuffed filet of sole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place crackers in plastic bag.
Roll with rolling pin to crush crackers.
Melt butter.
Add wine and boil for about 15 minutes.
Cook scallops or shrimp in boiling water for about 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain and add garlic, parsley, 1/2 cracker crumbs and 1/2 of wine mixture.
Mix well and place 1 tablespoon mixture on piece of filet.
Roll and fasten with toothpick.
Place rolls in buttered pan.
Put remaining crumbs on fish and pour wine mixture on top.
Bake for about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saut onion in oleo. Add all other ingredients. Remove from heat and pour into casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; beat in eggs.
Blend in syrup and flour; stir in nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: bacon wraps
directions: Cut bacon slices into three pieces.
Make stuffing according to package directions.
Roll bacon slice around a small spoonful of dressing and stick a wooden toothpick through the bacon.
Bake on cookie sheet until bacon is crisp.

title: peaches - cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together (except soda pop) and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Roll into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes.
While warm, dig out flat sides with melon scoop (takes patience).
Fill with any nut filler. Place 2 cookies together.
Dip in red soda pop, then sugar.
Add green stem.

title: onion rings
directions: Dip onion rings in this and deep fat fry with Wesson oil.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer until smooth.
Pour into freezer.
Makes one gallon.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and it is ready to serve.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, soup, onion, water chestnuts and approximately 1/2 cup of cheese.
Place in greased large casserole dish. Sprinkle approximately 1 cup of grated cheese over vegetable layer.
Crush crackers and mix with 1 stick melted butter. Sprinkle over cheese layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thick.
Place 1 ham slice and 1 cheese stick on each chicken piece.
Tuck in sides of each and roll up, pressing to seal well.
Skewer or tie securely.
Coat in flour and brown in oleo.
Place in an 11 x 7-inch baking pan.

title: artichoke cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, put in a deep baking dish.
Sprinkle on top 1/4 to 1/2 cup more Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Toss lightly.
Serve as salad or "lite" dessert.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hobo chili
directions: Saute onions and butter until tender.
Add ground beef.
Cook until brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, El Paso sauce and chili powder.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Then add beans and simmer another 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Mix potatoes, orange juice and vanilla.
Add other ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook meat for 6 to 7 minutes, or until well done.
Stir occasionally.
Layer beef, beans, taco sauce, chillies and cheese in microwavable dish.
Cook 6 minutes at 70%.
Serve with chips.

title: artichoke chicken salad
directions: Mix artichoke liquid with mayonnaise.
Add 1/4 teaspoon curry powder.
Add to preceding combined ingredients.
Store in refrigerator overnight or day before used.
Serves a lot.
Keeps well.

title: bacon appetizer crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat cream cheese, bacon, Parmesan cheese, onion, parsley and milk in small mixing bowl until well blended.
Separate dough (crescent rolls).
Spread mixture evenly across dough.
Roll up starting with short end.
Place on greased cookie sheet; brush with egg and water mixture.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: triple bean casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and drain.
Crumble. Cook onion in drippings until tender, but not brown.
Drain.
In 2 qt. casserole, combine all ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 375 degrees for 40 minutes.
Uncover, bake 20 - 25 minutes more or until desired consistency is reached.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand several hours before serving.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Add chicken.
Simmer 45 minutes in uncovered skillet on medium heat.
Turn chicken every 15 minutes.

title: apple or peach pie
directions: Put fruit in bottom of pan. Cut bread in three pieces.
Cover fruit.
Mix sugar, flour, oleo and egg.
Pour over fruit and bake at 325° until brown.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes three (9-inch) layers.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Find a platter.
Smear beans all over platter.
Then take the avocado dip and smear that all over beans.
Take sour cream and taco seasoning and mix together until it tastes spicy, then put that on top of the avocado dip.
Take the chopped onion and spread them on top of the sour cream.
Take the chopped tomato and put them on the onion.
Take shredded cheese and put all over top so you cannot see dip.
Take sliced olives and place over dip and get some chips and dig in.
Add salsa, if desired.

title: green beans with onions
directions: Put onions into small amount of boiling salted water in saucepan. Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes or until onions are tender.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions in melted butter with sugar and nutmeg.
Cook until onions are transparent, but not browned.
Dissolve beef stock base in boiling water.
Add onions and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Add sherry and bring back to a boil.
Spoon into ovenproof serving dishes; add croutons and Parmesan cheese.
Place under broiler for 10 minutes.

title: onion and mushroom sauce(serve with yellow tail snapper fillet)
directions: Saute minced garlic in margarine until golden brown.
Add scallions and onion and cook until soft.
Add remaining ingredients, except white wine and mushrooms, and simmer 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms and white wine; simmer about 5 minutes. Pour over cooked fish.
Serves 4.

title: sausage balls
directions: Blend all
ingredients	and
make
into teaspoon balls; bake in 400° preheated oven about 17 minutes.

title: randy's favorite oatmeal
directions: Boil all ingredients together except cinnamon and brown sugar. Sprinkle with cinnamon and very little brown sugar.

title: mincemeat spareribs
directions: Put ribs, meat side up, in pan. Add water and a little salt. Cover pan with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Drain. Combine mincemeat, broth and vinegar.
Pour over ribs.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 45 minutes. Baste occasionally with juices. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash and cut up squash.
Boil until tender; drain and mash. Add everything except 1/2 of the margarine. Melt remaining margarine.
Pour mixture in casserole dish; pour melted margarine over top and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: beef and mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir together well. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 12 hours, or on high for 5 to 6 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: date nut cake
directions: Cook until soft the hot water, chopped dates, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream sugar; add oil or shortening, egg, flour and vanilla.
Then add date mixture and nuts.
Bake at 350°.

title: enchiladas las palmas
directions: Saute beef and onion in a skillet pan until cooked. Drain grease.
Mix in 1/3 cup Las Palmas enchilada sauce.
In a skillet, heat 1 can (10 ounce) sauce. Dip each tortilla in sauce until well coated.
Lay tortilla in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Fill with 3 tablespoons of meat and roll.
Place seam side down, side by side, in same dish.
Cover rolled enchiladas with remaining sauce. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 8 tortillas, 4 servings.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine eggs, sugar, butter, flour and pineapple.
Mix in bread cubes.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with topping, if desired. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: diabetic apple muffins
directions: Sift flour, sweetener, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl. Combine egg, milk, vanilla and shortening. Add this mixture to flour mixture. Blend until flour is moistened. Do not overmix; batter should be lumpy. Fold in minced apples.

title: cauliflower and carrot pickles(do chua)
directions: In a medium bowl, cover the cauliflower with water and add 1 teaspoon of the salt.
Soak for about 15 minutes.
In a separate bowl, do the same with the carrots.
Drain the vegetables.
Put them in a deep glass jar or ceramic container with a lid.
In a medium bowl, mix together the sugar, vinegar and 1 1/2 cups warm water and let the sugar dissolve.
Pour over the vegetables and let them stand at room temperature for 3 days.
The pickles will keep in the refrigerator for up to 1 month.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: date bars
directions: Mix in order given; add flour (sifted with baking powder and salt), dates and nuts.
Spread on greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut in bars and roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: mushroom crust quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter a 9-inch pie plate. Melt 3 tablespoons butter in skillet over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and stir until tender, about 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cracker crumbs.
Press into bottom and sides of plate.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in skillet.
Add onions and stir to soften, about three minutes.
Sprinkle over crust.
Top with Jack cheese.
Blend cottage cheese, eggs and paprika in processor.
Pour over cheese.
Bake about 35 minutes until tester inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chit-chat
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: italian skillet chicken
directions: Coat each chicken breast in cheese, then flour.
Salt and pepper to taste.
In skillet, cook chicken in oil over medium-high heat until done.
Remove to serving platter and keep warm.

title: finger jell-o
directions: Add 1 cup water to flavored gelatin mixture, then mix both bowls together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate, then cut into squares or shapes.
Terrific for kid's school lunches or summertime treats, because this doesn't melt fast.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit well; reserve pineapple juice.
Mix all fruit. Mix pudding mix and pineapple juice until smooth.
Add to fruit, tossing to coat all fruit.
Chill.

title: freezer corn
directions: Cut corn off cob and mix together with rest of ingredients and freeze. To cook corn, put butter in a pan and boil about 10 minutes (if still frozen when you start).

title: deep dish mexican pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In medium bowl combine biscuit mix, cornmeal and water; mix well.
With floured hands, pat dough on bottom and up sides of greased 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and seasoning mix in small bowl.
Spread into bottom 9 inch pie plate.

title: custard pie
directions: In a large bowl mix ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Preheat oven to 450° and bake for 10 minutes.
Turn heat down to 350° and bake 30 minutes more.

title: susan's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together; shape into a loaf.
Bake in a bread pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together oleo and shortening.
Add sugar; beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Combine flour and soda, sift 3 times.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour in 9 inch round pans and bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until done. Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: date pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour together.
Fold in cream, dates and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 1 hour at 300°. Bake on low rack in oven.

title: cola chicken
directions: Place chicken in large frying pan or electric cooker.
Add salt and pepper.
Combine catsup, cola and Worcestershire sauce; blend well.
Pour over chicken.
Simmer for 1 hour, turning chicken once during cooking time.
Serve with rice.

title: pistachio fluff - for diabetics
directions: In food processor, combine cottage cheese and 1 cup yogurt. Cover and process until smooth.
Place remaining yogurt in large bowl.
Add pudding mix; whisk for 2 minutes or until slightly thickened, then add cottage cheese mixture and mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until serving.
Makes 14 servings.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Step 1:
combine vinegar, sugar, egg, pineapple juice, flour. Heat until it thickens.
(Chill it.)

title: saucy shrimp and pasta
directions: Thaw shrimp, if frozen.
Peel and devein shrimp.
Rinse; pat dry with paper towels.
Set aside.
In a large saucepan, stir together tomatoes, cornstarch, snipped parsley, sugar, Italian seasoning, and ground red pepper.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in shrimp.
Return to boiling; cook for 1 to 3 minutes more or until shrimp are opaque.
Serve shrimp mixture over hot cooked spaghetti.
Garnish with fresh parsley sprigs, if desired.

title: chicken ratatouille
directions: Heat oil.
Saute chicken, onion and carrots until brown.
Add diced green pepper, eggplant and squash.
Cook about 5 minutes, then add seasoning and tomatoes.
Cover and cook about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover and cook 15 minutes more to absorb liquid.
Sprinkle on lemon juice.
Serve hot or cold.
Good over rice or noodles.

title: punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and sparkling water and stir gently in large glass jar or bottle.
Pour over large block of ice in punch bowl and spoon sherbet over top.
Makes 110 punch cups.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Form a ball and roll in pecans.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: crunchy bananas
directions: Sprinkle sesame seed on a tray or cookie sheet.
Roll each banana half in sesame seed, pressing gently to make sure they stick.

title: mow mow jean sweet bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray a 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: camp breakfast
directions: In large skillet, fry bacon crispy.
Dice and fry potatoes. Break bacon into small bits as potatoes fry.
Crack eggs into bowl (don't break).
When potatoes are nearly finished, put bacon bits into them and stir.
Pour eggs over all and simmer until done. Divide and eat.
Serves 6 or more.

title: veal parmigiana
directions: Pound veal until tender and thin (or have butcher tenderize). Dip meat in egg.
Roll in mixture of bread crumbs and Parmesan. Brown meat on both sides until golden brown.
Lay in shallow baking dish.

title: cake with crunchy marshmallow topping
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Arrange 24 regular sized marshmallows on top and bake as directed.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chocolate oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Place milk and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on buttered cookie sheet.
Chill until firm.
Super chunky peanut butter is best.
Chunky can be used with almost as good results.
Extra chocolate gives it richer and better flavor. Mixing is easier if you add peanut butter to hot sugar and milk mixture first.
Then add other ingredients.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix moist ingredients and add to dry ingredients, stirring only until moistened.
Do not beat.
Fold in nuts and pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: ham casserole
directions: Add sauteed pepper to ham-soup mixture.
Place in greased casserole.
Make baking powder biscuits with 1/2 cup grated cheese added, before adding milk.
Top casserole with biscuits and brown. Quick dinner.
Serve with green vegetable.

title: chicken pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in a large pan over low heat. Blend in
flour,
salt, pepper and thyme.
Cook over low heat, stirring
until
smooth
and
bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in chicken
broth
and
milk.	Heat
to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and
stir
minute.	Stir
in
chicken
and vegetables. Pour
into	pastry	shell.	Cover
with top crust which has slits cut
in
it.
Seal and flute. Cover edge with 2-inch strip	of foil
to prevent excessive browning.
Remove foil the last 15 minutes of baking. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: Rinse chicken and its giblets with cold water.
In 5-quart saucepot over high heat, heat chicken, giblets, celery, carrot, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and water to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove chicken to large bowl; refrigerate 30 minutes or until easy to handle.
Remove and discard chicken bones and skin.
Cut meat and giblets into bite-size pieces; set aside.
Skim fat from broth; measure 1 3/4 cups for reserve. (Cover and refrigerate remaining broth and vegetables for soup another day.)

title: cherries and nuts salad
directions: Prepare according to directions on Jell-O package.
When Jell-O is set, whip it.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in mold and set.

title: sugar cream cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine.
Pour into bowl.
Add cake mix and 2 eggs.
Pat into pan.
In a separate bowl, mix cream cheese (soft), 2 eggs and powdered sugar with mixer.
Pour over first mixture and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend all the ingredients until smooth; chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.
It's yum-yum good!

title: bell pepper fajitas
directions: Saute sliced bell peppers and onions in butter until tender. Add milk and shredded cheese.
Lower heat.
Stir until melted. Wrap in tortilla.
Enjoy.

title: cold peach soup
directions: Puree 5 peaches with sugar in blender.
Add sour cream, lemon juice, sherry and orange juice.
Blend until smooth.
Transfer to covered dish and refrigerate until well chilled.
Garnish each serving with sliced peaches.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onion together. Drain. Add the chili mix and tomatoes.
Cook for 15 or 20 minutes on low heat. While other mixture is cooking, boil the noodles.
Drain.
Add powdered cheese and 1/2 stick butter.
Mix everything together.
Now grate 4 cups cheese. Set oven to 350°.
Butter the whole casserole dish. Cover the dish with 1 cup of grated cheese.
Pour 1/3 of the mixture.
Repeat in layers until you have 1 cup of cheese to put on top.
Cook about 30 minutes until cheese is a little brown on top.
Serves 8.
Best when served hot.

title: angela's ham and vegetable quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prick bottom and sides of pie shells; bake for 5 minutes, then take out.
Sprinkle bottom of pie shells with Swiss cheese first, then ham, broccoli and cauliflower.

title: beijing chicken
directions: Rinse chicken pieces and pat dry with paper towels.
Place in large, plastic bag.
Combine teriyaki sauce, sherry, ginger, fennel, orange peel and honey; pour over chicken.
Press air out of bag.
Tie top securely.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight, turning bag occasionally.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cover chicken breasts with water and bring to a boil. Turn off heat and let set, covered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until done. Cut or shred into small pieces. Saute onion in oleo over medium heat until tender. Add green chilies and saute for 2 minutes. Add cream cheese and chicken. Put 1/2 cup chicken mixture in each tortilla and roll up. Place each tortilla seam side down in a greased or sprayed baking dish. Sprinkle cheese evenly over tortillas. Pour whipping cream over all. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: waffle cookies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add softened shortening and flour.
Bake in waffle iron and drop by tablespoons.
When completely cooled, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes approximately 6 dozen soft, delicious cookies.

title: garlic soup
directions: Simmer until potatoes are done.
Very good.

title: spanish rice
directions: Rinse squash and then slice.
Salt and pepper.
Roll in flour and deep fry.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease a loaf pan.
Mix the bananas and eggs together in a large bowl.
Stir in the flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add the walnuts and blend.
Put the batter in the pan and bake for one hour.
Remove from the pan to a rack. Serve still warm or cooled, as you like it.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, set aside.
Heat buttermilk to lukewarm; then add shortening (oil) and sugar.
Add dissolved yeast to this and add egg and 1 cup flour with soda and salt. Beat firmly.
Add remaining flour until dough is soft.
Place dough in warm place and let rise until doubled.
Roll out dough and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place rolls on greased cookie sheet and let rise in pans.
Bake rolls at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Butter tops of rolls when coming out of the oven.
Yields 2 dozen (1 pan).

title: nut rolls
directions: Blend butter and flour together until crumbly.
Add egg yolk and sour cream.
Mix ground walnuts, granulated sugar and cinnamon together.
Mix with a spoon until all is combined (very sticky). Form into ball.
Place on floured wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
Make four small balls out of the large.
Roll each one out separately and sprinkle on about 4 tablespoons of the sugar and walnut mixture.
Spread out and pat down.
Cut into 16 pieces and roll from the outside to the center.
Bake about 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Total yield:

title: momma's supper
directions: You will need an oblong casserole dish.

title: vienna cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 9-inch layer pans. Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together. Combine liquids together.
Mix the creamed mixture alternating with flour and milk.
Beat after each addition until batter is smooth, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour in prepared pans.
Bake for 40 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center of each cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan a few minutes.
Turn out onto wire rack. Cut each layer in half.
Fill with your favorite jam.
Cover top and sides lavishly with vanilla icing.
Serves 16.

title: easy lunch meat bread
directions: Prepare bread according to package directions to make dough or defrost dough if using frozen.
Stretch dough out to form a rectangle approximately 9 x 13, on a floured surface.
Lay lunch meat on bread, leaving a border.
Cover with a layer of cheese. Sprinkle on spices, if desired, very good when using an herb bread mix and omitting spices.
Roll up jelly roll style, sealing edges and placing seam side down on a baking sheet.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven or until golden brown.
Serve warm or cold.

title: tuna cheese burgers
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Spread mustard on buns. Spread mix on buns.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini italian
directions: Wash zucchini.
Grind, onion, pepper and zucchini in food chopper.
Add crumbs, oil, cheese and egg.
Mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle a little cheese on top.
Bake in casserole for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: herbed vegetable toss(cooking light)
directions: Place a steamer basket in a large saucepan.
Add water to just below basket.
Bring water to boiling.
Peel a strip around the center of each new potato.
Add potatoes and carrots to steamer basket.
Cover and steam for 20 to 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove vegetables from steamer and sprinkle with oil or melted margarine and rosemary or thyme.
Toss lightly to coat.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Bake corn bread (directions on box; dice to bite-size pieces). Cook chicken with lots of broth.
Dice chicken to bite-sizes. Cut onion and celery.
Tear bread into bite-size pieces.
Chop eggs.
Add seasonings and mix all together.
Bake in casserole dish at 350°.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press rolls on bottom and halfway up sides of 9 x 13 pan. Bake as directed on pan or until lightly brown. Prepare gravy and cook sausage. Pour gravy over rolls. Sprinkle sausage over gravy. Add cheese. Bake in oven for 10 minutes.

title: brownie candy cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place 30 (2-inch) foil cupcake liners in small muffin pans.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together until beaten thoroughly and forms a creamy, smooth cake batter.
Makes 2 layers.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool on wire rack.

title: bill's cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well. Add flour 1/3 at a time, alternating with 1/3 of buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: zesty oil-free salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate for all flavors to blend.
Yields 3/4 cup.
Each 3 tablespoons contains only 3 calories and no fat.

title: dream cupcakes
directions: Make cupcakes according to directions on box.
Cream cheese and sugar.
Add egg and salt.
Stir in chocolate pieces and coconut.
Fill cupcake 2/3 full and put spoonful of cheese mixture in center.
Bake according to directions on box.
Frost, if desired, with white icing.

title: dad's omelet(actually a souffle)
directions: *I use oregano, garlic salt, pepper and sometimes a dash of lemon.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Finely chop onions, celery, garlic and bell pepper; makes for a much better gravy.
Heat oil in a heavy pot (cast-iron is ideal). Fry onions until just golden brown; add next 3 vegetables and cook for about 5 to 7 minutes, then add seasoned shrimp.
Cover tightly and let simmer on a low fire for 20 minutes.
Stir well.
You may add cornstarch now to thicken gravy.
Add parsley and green onions just before serving.
Serve hot over cooked rice.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine crumbs, milk, eggs, sugar, salt and fat.
Mix well. Add vanilla and raisins or nuts.
Turn into a greased baking tin or bowl.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 35 to 40 minutes or until firm.
Serve with whipped cream, if you want.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine chocolate, flour and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla and mix well.
Add margarine and cook slowly until thick. Pour into baked pie shell when cool.
Top with meringue.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients, then cut in Crisco.
Add milk and yeast mixture.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: cool-rise rolls
directions: In a large bowl, mix 2 cups flour, salt, sugar and yeast.
Add margarine (softened) and water; beat 2 minutes.
Add 2 eggs and 1/2 cup flour; beat 1 minute.
Add enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn onto floured board and knead 10 minutes.
Let rise 20 minutes.
Make into dinner rolls or cinnamon rolls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water and set aside to cool.
Wash and stem cranberries. Quarter and core apple and orange.
Select orange with thick skin but don't remove peel. Put all fruit through food blender.

title: dill pickles
directions: Scrub cucumbers. Pack loosely in hot qt. jars. Leave 1/2 in. head space for each jar. Add dill and mustard seed and a pinch of alum. Make a brine by combining water, vinegar, and salt. Bring to a boil and slowly pour hot brine over cucumbers. Leaving 1/2 in. head space; adjust lids. Process in boiling water baths for 20 minutes. Start time as soon as jars are placed in water.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease generously bottoms only of 2 loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Blend all ingredients on low speed for 1 minute, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed 1 minute. Pour into pans.
Bake until wooden pick comes clean, approximately 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Top with bread crumbs rolled finely and dotted with oleo. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: orange dream ice cream
directions: Mix together Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk and pineapple.
Pour in churn, then fill remainder with orange Crush to line; freeze.

title: watermelon cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Cream margarine; add sugar gradually and cream thoroughly. Add flour alternately with milk. Beat egg whites and add to batter. Divide batter into 2 parts. To one part, add red food coloring and well floured raisins. Grease melon mold or Bundt pan. Put a layer of white batter in the bottom, the red in the center and a layer of white on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes. Frost with green icing.

title: party meatballs
directions: Combine first 8
ingredients.
Roll into small meatballs.
Bake on cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 350°.
Slowly melt the grape jelly and chili sauce in large saucepan.
Add meatballs and cook for 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Debone and deskin.
Cut chicken into small pieces, then add soup, sour cream and poppy seed.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix crackers and melted butter together and sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sunday rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the warm water; let sit 5 minutes, until bubbly.
Mix the hot water, honey, oil and salt until honey is dissolved.
Add eggs; stir well.
Add yeast.
Add flour; mix well. If dough is to be used immediately, add 1/2 cup more flour. Shape into any type rolls.
Allow to rise.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 425°.
Yields 2 dozen rolls.

title: vegetarian supper combo
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat until hot. Add onions, bell pepper, carrot, rice and lentils; cook and stir 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender and liquid is absorbed, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: bagels(water doughnuts)
directions: Mix the oil, sugar and salt with the hot water. When it cools to lukewarm, add the yeast to dissolve.
Beat the egg until frothy. Add it to the liquid and then mix in the flour.
Knead the dough and shape into doughnuts.
Cover and set to rise on a floured board. When the bagels begin to swell, drop them, one at a time, into briskly boiling water and cook until they rise to the top and are light.
Place on baking sheets and bake in
a 400° oven until crisp and golden, about 15 minutes.
Makes about 30 bagels.

title: potato filling
directions: Prepare instant potatoes for 8 to 12 servings as directed on the box.
Add a little more milk than called for.
Brown onion and celery in butter.
Cube bread slices and add to onion and celery. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix bread mixture with potatoes. Put in casserole dish and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple jelly ii
directions: Put apple juice, cinnamon sticks and cloves into kettle. Heat just until boils. Remove from heat. Allow to sit for 1 hour. Strain the juice to remove the cinnamon sticks and the cloves. Return juice to pan and add lemon juice. Add pectin. Stir and bring to a boil. Add sugar all at once. Stir and return to a full rolling boil. Boil for 1 minute. Makes about 6 cups. Seal in jars with 2-piece lid and ring. Water bath for 10 minutes.

title: corn freezing tips
directions: Mix well, put in container and freeze.
Blanching is not required.
Thaw and pour off excess water before cooking.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Grease and flour 4 round cake pans. Preheat oven to 325°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook to hard boil stage.
Stir in 2 cups raw peanuts.
Cook until peanuts and syrup are light brown in color.
Add vanilla and soda.
Pour into greased pan while mixture is foaming.
Let harden; break into pieces.

title: quick candied sweet potatoes
directions: Pare sweet potatoes. Halve lengthwise.
If the potatoes are large, halve them again.
Place in skillet.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Boil briskly, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Turn potatoes. Boil another 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer until tender and glazed, about 20 minutes.
Baste often, turn once.
May have to add more hot water if the water gets low.

title: banana bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside. In mixer bowl, cream sugar and shortening with electric mixer until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, and milk, beating smooth after each addition.
Add flour mixture and banana alternately to creamed mixture, beating until smooth after each addition.
Fold in nuts. Turn into lightly greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 65 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool. For easier slicing, wrap and store overnight.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pineapple-almond punch
directions: Freeze the large can of pineapple juice in ice cube trays. When ready for punch, put tea bags in boiling water; let stand for 10 minutes.
About 1/2 hour before serving, put pineapple cubes in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, except for ginger ale.
Stir punch, then add ginger ale.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and chill.
Some can be frozen in mold to put in punch bowl.

title: greek bread
directions: Mix and layer over each half of bread and let sit overnight in the refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: mcdonald's big mac "secret sauce"
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt the butter in a 9 x 13-inch glass or metal pan.
Mix the 4 cups sliced peaches with 1/2 cup sugar and let set while making the batter.
Mix the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour the batter mixture over the melted butter in the pan.
(Don't mix.) Pour peaches over batter.
(Don't mix.)
Bake at 325° for glass pan or 350° for metal pan for one hour.

title: strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt and fruit into whipped topping, blending well. Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Remove from freezer and place in refrigerator 30 minutes or longer before cutting.
Store any leftover pie in freezer.

title: inside-out ravioli casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Add onion, garlic, salt, spaghetti sauce, spinach liquid (drained from thawed spinach) plus enough water to make 1 cup.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Combine spinach (drained) with macaroni, cheese, bread crumbs and eggs. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch (or larger) baking dish. Top with meat sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: date and bacon rolls(microwave)
directions: Microwave bacon until half done (3 to 4 minutes).
Mix together peanut butter and curry.
Stuff each date with peanut butter mixture and wrap half of a slice of partially cooked bacon around each date.
Spear with a toothpick.
Place on pie plate and microwave on High until bacon is crisp (4 to 6 minutes).
Give 1/2 turn twice during cooking.
Serve warm.

title: pumpkin cupcakes
directions: Combine butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift in dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in pumpkin.
Fill 2 1/2-inch greased cupcake tins 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt the margarine; dump in remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat soup.
Add sour cream and 1 can green chiles.
Add chicken.
On the opened tortillas, place some grated cheese in the middle.
Add 2 spoonfuls of the chicken mixture and roll up.
Keep some chicken mixture and cheese for spreading on top of the enchiladas.
Place enchiladas in dish and spread balance of chicken mixture on top along with rest of cheese and chiles.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broiled pink grapefruit
directions: Preheat broiler.
Cut grapefruit in half.
Loosen sections with a grapefruit knife.
Discard seeds.
Put grapefruit in a shallow baking dish, cut side up.
In small bowl, beat together butter, sugar and nutmeg until smooth.
Dot butter mixture evenly on top of grapefruit halves.
Broil about 4 inches from heat until topping is melted, bubbly and slightly browned (3 to 5 minutes).
Easy and quick - a Southern favorite!
Try it at the Arsenic and Old Lace Bed and Breakfast in Eureka Springs, AR!

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Cut bread into 3 strips each.
Place bread strip on 1/2 slice bacon; sprinkle with cheese.
Place olive at one end; roll up. Secure with toothpick.
Place in deep baking dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Add chopped onion, then milk and egg. Mix thoroughly. Drop mixture by small spoonfuls into boiling oil. When done, the hush puppies will float. Drain them on paper towels.

title: ginny's vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables.
Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine; do not drain.
Mix well the soup with milk and put in casserole.
Add to onion mixture and blend.
Add all vegetables and mix.
Top with cheeses.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease. Pour corn and peas over hamburger. Let simmer. Sprinkle cheese over top. Pour in cornbread mix. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: pineapple-pear preserves
directions: Keep pears in water with Fruit Fresh while preparing them. Rinse and drain.
Put in a large enameled pan or pot; add more Fruit Fresh and sugar to coat all slices thickly.
Slice all lemons very thin; seed, then add to pears.
Add crushed pineapple. Soak this mixture overnight.
Next morning, cook over medium heat until pears are beginning to "clear" at thick part and are barely fork-tender.
While cooking, may sprinkle with cinnamon if desired, to taste.
Cook about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Jar in hot jars and with hot seals.
Should yield 8 to 10 pints.
Enjoy!

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
Pour 1/2 the batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Melt caramels with milk and butter over low heat.
After baking the cake, pour caramel mixture over cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour remaining 1/2 batter over this.
Sprinkle with any remaining nuts and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs with 1 stick of butter and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 7 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: baked mushrooms
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, onion, garlic, herbs, salt and pepper. Add mushrooms and, basting frequently, marinate for 3 hours.
Drain and saute in butter over high heat for 1 minute.
Reduce heat to low; cook for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Transfer to a buttered baking dish; sprinkle bread crumbs and cheese over mushrooms.
Broil until top is browned.
Serve as a first course or vegetable accompaniment to meat or fowl.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baby rabbit formula
directions: Add egg yolk to milk and water.
Feed 1 to 1.5 teaspoons per feeding; mother rabbit may not feed but 4 to 6 times per day, but try every 3 hours, from 6:00 a.m. to 10:00 p.m.
After the rabbit gets teeth: rabbit pellets, fruit, carrot, grass, V-8 juice.
If bunny will not eat from shock, .5 to 1.0 mg cortison two times a week for a 4 ounce rabbit (about 1/2 cup in volume).
Keep at 80°, furry nest material.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook beans, chicken, Ro-Tel, onion, garlic, salt and pepper together in a crock-pot until beans are tender and chicken is done.
(Water should be at least 2 inches over top of ingredients; you may have to add more during cooking.)
Add sliced smoked sausage.
Remove chicken, debone and tear into pieces.
Place cooked rice, beans and sausage mixture and chicken in a large stock pot.
Add grated cheese; heat on low until everything is hot and cheese melts.
Stir to prevent sticking.
(You may have to add a little water if it is too dry.)

title: deluxe chicken salad
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients, except the shoestring potatoes.
Put in refrigerator.
Just before serving, stir in the shoestring potatoes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together and bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° until done.

title: saucy chicken roll-ups
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place chicken breast or thigh boned side up between 2 pieces of plastic wrap or waxed paper.
Working from center, gently pound chicken with rolling pin or flat side of meat mallet until about 1/4-inch thick.
Repeat with remaining chicken breasts and thighs.
Place 1/2 ham slice on each piece of chicken; sprinkle with pepper.
Roll-up jelly roll fashion; place in 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pound cake
directions: Cream together peanut butter, Crisco oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk and flour, mixing well.
Take out 1 1/2 cups of batter and add cocoa, mixing well.
Pour other batter in a greased and floured tube pan. Pour cocoa batter on top and swirl through it several times. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Dump in undrained pineapple and pie filling.
Push it around until almost even.
Next, sprinkle cake mix to cover fruit.
Then sprinkle nuts over mix.
Cut butter into cubes and put on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning and sour cream. Slowly add to soft cream cheese. Add shredded cheese. Leave some cheese out to sprinkle on top of dip.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; dice stems.
Boil sausage for 2 to 3 minutes; remove skin.
Saute onions, celery and stems in butter.
Put sausage in blender or finely chop and add to saucepan with onions, celery and mushrooms.
Mix Parmesan cheese, walnuts and bread crumbs in large bowl.
Add other sauteed ingredients to bowl.
Cool slightly, then stuff caps.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes until slightly brown.

title: sophie mueller's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Cream softened butter with sugar until light in color and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, then flour all at once.
Add milk.
Beat until smooth, about 45 seconds.
(Overbeating after the flour will make a tough cake.)
Pour immediately into prepared Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Do not open door while baking.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Cook oatmeal according to package directions.
Add milk, eggs, honey and oil and stir into batter.
Add dry ingredients.
Fry on lightly greased griddle until golden brown on each side.

title: fruit cocktail torte
directions: Combine in bowl, flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients.
Then fold in 1 cup drained fruit cocktail.
Pour in greased pan and sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and margarine and press in pan.
Mix egg, cream cheese and sugar.
Spread on top of other layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: country-style chicken soup
directions: In a 4-quart or large slow cooker, combine chicken, onion, carrot, celery, parsley, bay leaf, thyme, salt, pepper and water. Cover and cook on low 7 to 8 hours or until tender.

title: creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip as directed on other side of envelope; add pumpkin, milk, instant pudding and spices.
Mix slowly with rotary beater just until blended, about 1 minute.
Pour into pie shell. Chill at least 2 hours.
Can garnish with more toppings.
Can omit the spices and use 3/4 teaspoon pumpkin pie spice.

title: happy hour mushrooms
directions: Twist out stems from mushrooms.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine; brush over mushroom caps, coating thoroughly.
Stir together remaining margarine, garlic and cheese until well blended.
Add wine, soy sauce and crumbs; blend well.
Place mushrooms, cavity side up, on a large rimmed baking sheet.
Evenly mound filling in each mushroom, pressing it in lightly.
Broil about 6-inches from heat until bubbly and light brown.
Serve warm.

title: hello dolly
directions: Melt butter in oblong pan; sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over bottom of pan.
Then sprinkle nuts, chocolate drops, butterscotch drops and coconut over crumbs.
Pour milk on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
While cooling, sift powdered sugar on top.

title: nondairy strawberry ice cream
directions: In a blender, whip the milk substitute for 2 minutes.
Turn off blender and add sugar, vanilla, egg yolk and strawberries. Whip for 30 seconds; put into a bowl and freeze for 30 minutes. In a small bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into ice cream and refreeze in a plastic covered container.

title: seafood stuffed mushrooms
directions: Chop mushroom stems fine.
Combine all ingredients, except mushroom caps.
Fill mushroom caps and place on "sprayed" cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Note: Separate eggs; save egg whites for meringue.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Serve with crackers and/or veggies.

title: lemon chiffon sponge cake
directions: Into large bowl, beat egg whites well.
Add sugar slowly while beating.
Fold yellows into whites; beat yellows and add lemon juice freshly squeezed and orange squeezed just once.
Add vanilla.
Fold in flour slowly.
Place in tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
To cool, turn upside down on rack.
Good with strawberries, whipped cream or ice cream or lemon sauce on top.

title: pineapple cheese torte
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, powdered sugar, almonds and margarine. Pat on bottom of a 12 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: super bowl brunch
directions: Lightly butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Lay rolls in the bottom and flatten.
Mix eggs, salt, pepper and milk to suit your taste (like an omelette); pour mixture over rolls.
Drop meat into egg mixture and sprinkle cheese on tops.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, until firm.

title: fudge
directions: Bring to a boil and let boil 9 minutes the sugar, evaporated milk and margarine. Stir occasionally. Add Marshmallow Creme, chopped nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla. Stir until chips are melted. Spread in a buttered 9 x 13 pan.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Brown bacon in frying pan.
Remove bacon.
Combine with lettuce and onion.
Combine vinegar, water and bacon fat.
Heat to boiling.
Add seasonings and sugar.
Combine with lettuce mixture. Serve at once.

title: hot punch
directions: Combine juices.
Using automatic drip coffee maker, put cloves,
cinnamon
and
brown sugar in filter of coffee maker. Pour juices through coffee maker.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove meat from bones.
Season with a little salt and pepper.
Mix together soup, broth and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and mix well.
Put mixture in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: broiled beef("pulgogi")
directions: Cut the beef into thin slices about 3-inch square by 1/8-inch thick.
(This can be done at the meat department.)
Marinate the beef in the remaining ingredients for over 1 1/2 hours. Traditionally, the meat is broiled at the table on a grill over charcoal, gas ring or hot plate.
You can also use a frying pan or oven broiler.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix together until smooth.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes small.
Cook in enough water to cover.
When tender, add margarine, salt, pepper and chicken soup.
Heat to eat.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Marinate 3 to 4 pounds country-style spareribs overnight in a baking dish.
Mix all ingredients well before pouring over the spareribs.
Next day, bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours (or until done) at 350°.
Baste occasionally with sauce.

title: quiche
directions: Cook pie crust for approx. 5 minutes at 400.
Mix next 7 ingredients together and set aside.
Saute onions and celery in margarine or butter.
Saute mushrooms in butter or margarine.
Mix all ingredients together and pour in pie crust.
Cook at 350 for 1 hour.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown the hamburger, green pepper and onion; drain.
In crock-pot, place meat mixture with the beans, then stir.
Add the barbecue sauce (do not stir).
Set on low for 2 hours, then stir and serve.

title: easy potato bake
directions: Mix potatoes, sour cream, cheese and soup.
Spoon into greased 13 x 9 baking dish.
Toss crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake in preheated oven at 375 degrees for 1 hour. 12-16 servings.
tags: frozen Southern style hash brown potatoes

title: rocks(cookies)
directions: Mix together thoroughly the first three ingredients.
Sift together the next four ingredients.
Stir the two mixtures together.
Add the raisins and nuts.

title: pistachio yummy
directions: Set cream cheese out so it becomes room temperature.
Put oleo into a 9 x 13-inch pan and put in the oven at 200° to melt.
After melted, put flour and chopped nuts into pan.
Press to make crust. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until crust looks light brown. Remove and let cool to room temperature.

title: rotel dip
directions: Heat until cheese melts. Serve hot.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly the shortening, margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned. Cool slightly before moving from baking sheet.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and milk; mix well.
Pour over melted butter; do not stir.
Spoon peaches on top of batter and pour remaining syrup from peaches over the top.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup sugar and dust with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: virginia pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add 3 eggs.
Sift baking powder and flour together and add to egg and sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Add the remaining egg.
Beat into the batter just a little to mix.
Pour mixture into pan and set in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Place in cold oven and set temperature to 275°.
Bake for 1 hour.
Turn temperature up to 300°; bake 40 minutes.

title: crunchy beef bake casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Brown ground beef/sausage; drain fat.
Combine all ingredients except French fried onions.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; top with French fried onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: Layer Doritos in bottom of dish.
Place shredded chicken on top.
Then layer the grated cheese on top of chicken.
Saute onion and green chilies in some butter.
Add both cans of soup and sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pepper hash
directions: Chop fine peppers and onions and cover with boiling water. Drain and put in kettle with brown sugar, vinegar and salt to taste.
Boil one hour.
Seal in jars.
This is Grandmother Webster's recipe.

title: "gazpacho" congealed salad
directions: In large bowl, mix the first 7 ingredients with oil and vinegar.
Toss and mix with salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in consomme and let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Thoroughly mix gelatins, then dissolve in boiling water.
Cool and chill until mixture is thick.
Combine vegetables and gelatin mixture.
Pour into a large 3-quart oiled mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold, garnish and cut into squares to serve.

title: cranberry apple mold
directions: Heat cranberry sauce and apple sauce.
When real hot add Jell-o and stir until dissolved.
Chopped walnuts can be added. Pour in mold and chill.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In large microwave-safe bowl, mix sugar and cocoa, sifted makes fudge smoother.
Place sticks of butter in middle of bowl. Pour milk over all.
Do not stir.
Heat on High for 6 minutes or until butter is melted.

title: lemon basil grilled chicken
directions: Combine oil and next 7 ingredients in shallow baking dish. Add chicken, turning once to coat both sides.
Refrigerate for 30 to 35 minutes, turning once.

title: potato and onion soup
directions: Combine potatoes and onions in a large saucepan.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Cook until tender.
Mash all or part of vegetables through a sieve if a smooth soup is desired.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla on medium speed until well blended.
Gradually add chocolate and mix well.
Stir in apricots and nuts.
Spread into greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill several hours.
Cut into squares.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: white cucumber pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in salt overnight.
Drain and place cucumbers in jars.
Put 3 tablespoons of sugar on top of cucumbers.
Fill jars with vinegar and water mixture.
Seal jars and place in pot of water, deep enough to cover the jars by 2 inches.
Boil for 10 minutes; take jars out immediately.

title: 7 layer delight
directions: On bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish, place graham crackers.
Pour melted butter over crackers and mash down.
Pour layer of chocolate chips and pour 1/2 can of condensed milk over chips. Pour layer of nuts and layer of peanut butter chips.
Pour remaining can of condensed milk and top with coconut flakes.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: special k bars
directions: Melt together the last 3 ingredients.
Bring to boil the sugar, syrup and peanut butter.
Remove and add vanilla.
Add Special K.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour the melted butter and chips on top.

title: mama renny's queso dip
directions: Mix first in saucepan: milk, butter and flour.
After you mix these together, add the cheese and Ro-Tel. Make sure you cut up the cheese in cubes to help it melt quicker. You can add more cheese to make it thicker, if needed.

title: frozen strawberry pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and beat until dissolved.
Add strawberries.
Whip cream and fold into strawberry mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze.
Makes 2 pies.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in double boiler.
Beat egg yolks and add.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serve with a slice of banana and whipped cream.

title: tomato potato salad
directions: Slice tomatoes and put them on one end of large platter.
Peel potatoes (leave unpeeled if you wish) and steam them until tender. Drain completely; slice them and put on other end of platter. Slice onions and place in tomatoes and potatoes.
Pour Italian dressing over all while potatoes are still warm.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water.
Bring pineapple and sugar to a boil.
While still hot, add cream cheese. Add to Jell-O and cool, then add whipped cream and nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter (reserve 1 tablespoon) until smooth.
Add the next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture into the center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners to top center of each chicken mixture; twist slightly and seal edges. Brush tops with reserved butter; dip in crouton crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until white.
Cut chicken into little square pieces.
In bowl, mix the soup and mayonnaise and add a little juice from the lemon.
Put broccoli in the bottom of a baking dish.
Mix the cut-up chicken with the soup/mayonnaise mixture and pour over broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs, if desired.
Cover and cook in a 350° oven for about an hour.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well by hand.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix by hand.
Bake in a greased 8 1/2 x 13 x 2-inch pan for 1 hour at 325°,

title: heather heffner's reunion casserole
directions: Brown beef, sausage and onion. Drain fat. Stir in 1 cup cheese, green pepper, corn, soup, sauce, olives, garlic and noodles. Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Place mixture in pan. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: wonder brownies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Add oil, cocoa and vanilla.
Grease and flour large 15 1/2 x 6 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 40 (2-inch) squares.

title: prune cake
directions: If you use self-rising flour, leave out the salt.

title: spicy lasagne roll-ups
directions: Heat olive oil in a heavy 10-inch skillet over moderate heat for 1 minute.
Add the onion, basil, marjoram, bay leaf, half of the garlic and 1/4 teaspoon of the pepper.
Cook, uncovered, until the onion is soft (about 5 minutes).
Remove 2 tablespoons of the mixture and set aside.

title: easy custard pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or test with a knife when inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, flour, cornstarch and sugar.
Mix with 1/4 cup milk. Add rest of milk and cook until thick.
Let cool.
Pour into 1 baked 9-inch pie shell.
Beat egg whites for topping.

title: hot mocha(serves 1)
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender on medium speed.

title: golden puffs(donut holes)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together well, then mix all ingredients until thoroughly blended. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls in hot oil (375°).
Fry until golden brown, about 3 minutes.
Drain.
Dip in sugar or powdered sugar after cooking, if you like.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen puffs.

title: blender custard pie
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour into a 10-inch pie plate that has been buttered.
Bake at 350° until center is firm.
Before baking, you may sprinkle the top of pie with cinnamon or nutmeg.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Preheat skillet for 10 minutes with one tablespoon oil.
Put mixture into pan.
Make dents in it and put in butter.
Bake.

title: banana split cake(make 24 hours ahead)
directions: Combine crumbs and 1 stick melted margarine; line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine 2 sticks margarine, sugar, eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat at high speed but not less than 15 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Slice bananas over top.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: beef bean casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion and stir until tender.
Pour in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with beans.
Prepare muffin mix.
Spread batter over beans.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until corn bread is lightly browned.

title: whole wheat banana biscuits
directions: Combine 1 cup flour and the next 6 ingredients.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in banana and yogurt.
Add milk; stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; let rest 5 minutes. Knead dough 4 times.
Add enough of remaining flour to prevent dough from sticking to hands.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 16 biscuits.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box; put in cocoa and food coloring and mix all together and bake as directed.
Let cool, then put on icing.

title: garden deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs crosswise in slices.
Scoop out yolks into a small bowl.
Mash well.
Set egg whites aside.
Stir cheese spread, mayonnaise, onion, pimientos and mustard into yolk until smooth and well blended.
Top each Triscuit wafer with an egg white slice.
Spoon yolk mixture onto egg whites.
Garnish with parsley and tomatoes, if desired.
Makes 48 appetizers.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Mix and beat for 4 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: mashed potato kichla
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar; beat some more.
Add potatoes, shortening and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add all dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Roll out and cut into pieces.
fry in oil and roll in powdered sugar.

title: corn bread surprise muffins(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly oil muffin pans.
In medium bowl, combine thoroughly the first five ingredients.
Place egg whites in a 2 cup measure.
Add milk to measure 1 1/4 cups.
Beat with fork.
Stir in applesauce.
Heat pans for 1 minute in oven.

title: viking stew
directions: Boil fish
fillets (any mixture of firm white fish like red snapper,
halibut
or
Ling
cod)
in
water
while dicing potatoes.
Cool
the
fish
fillets.
Boil the potatoes in the fishy water
until
tender, with onion and diced bacon.
Drain water so 6
to
8 cups remain.
Add 1 quart half and half, 1/4 pound shrimp, deboned cooked fish pieces, 2 or 3 cans of clams in their
juice and seasonings to taste.
Mix flour with some milk and
add for thickening.
Simmer gently to heat through. Serve with sourdough bread.

title: super bread bowls
directions: For each bowl, combine 4 rolls to make a smooth ball.
Place on baking sheet sprayed with PAM.
Brush with 1 egg.
Cover loosely with PAM-sprayed plastic wrap.
Let rise until double in size. Remove wrap and bake at 350 degrees 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool; slice off top.
Hollow out bread & fill with hot soup or chili.
Serve with the top crust for dipping.

title: egg salad(sandwich)
directions: Peel cooled boiled eggs. Mash eggs and add ingredients. Cut crusts from white or wheat bread as preferred. A slice of each is good. Spread bread lightly with "Benecol" margarine. Spread egg mixture over "Benecol" margarine side evenly and to sides of bread. Top with other slice of bread. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate. Happy eating.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Mix in tuna, Veg-all, onion and soup. Add milk to make creamy.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients to soft stage.
Spread onto flour tortillas and make into rolls.
Refrigerate overnight or until serving time.
Slice.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli halfway and drain good.
Now mix all of the ingredients, easy so you don't mash the broccoli.
Grease a baking dish and pour into the dish.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: banana-strawberry quick serve dessert
directions: Wash and hull whole strawberries.
Combine berries with frozen banana slices and honey or sweetener, if desired, in a food processor.
Process until the consistency of soft serve ice cream. Garnish with additional strawberry slices.
Serve immediately. Makes 3 servings.
Under 80 calories each.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush cookies to a fine texture with rolling pin.
Sprinkle half on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together milk and pudding; set aside to thicken.
Beat together margarine, sugar and cream cheese until creamy.
Add thawed whipped topping and pudding to cream cheese mixture; stir well.

title: children's 7-layer jello
directions: First Layer:
Mix 1 package Jell-O, 1 envelope gelatin and 1 cup hot water.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill for 20 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Melt butter on stove in boiling water.
After butter starts to boil, remove from heat.
Add eggs (beaten) one at a time.
Mix well.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 450° or 25 minutes at 325°.
Let cool.
Fill with whipped cream.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Grease a large casserole dish; mix all ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.
