Freezes well and can be prepared ahead of time.

title: banana drop cookies
directions: Mix.
Sprinkle on cookies before baking.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: egg and sausage strata
directions: Line greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with bread cubes; set aside. In skillet brown sausage, onion and green pepper; drain.
Stir in pimento and sprinkle over bread.
In large bowl mix eggs, milk, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt, pepper and oregano.
Pour over sausage mixture in pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake covered at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center is clean.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Wash berries.
Add sugar and enough water to cover berries. Bring to boil.
Mix shortening and flour until mealy.
Add enough water to make like biscuit dough.
Roll out thin; cut in strips about 1 inch.
Drop several strips in boiling berries.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Put remaining strips crisscross on top.
Put a little sugar and a little butter on top.
Bake at 375° until crust is brown.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle one package of onion soup mix in bottom of casserole dish.
Top with rice.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Pour soup over chicken.
Add additional liquid if necessary.
Bake until chicken is done at 350°.

title: catfish stew
directions: Cook fish until tender; add potatoes and onions. Fry bacon in frypan until crisp. Add bacon and drippings to other ingredients. Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and hot sauce to taste. Cook until all is tender.

title: beef vegetable casserole
directions: Brown the meat in a skillet with the margarine, adding meat slices a few at a time and browning on both sides.
Season with salt, pepper and marjoram; transfer to a 3 to 4-quart casserole. Add vegetables.
Add soup to the skillet to loosen pan drippings; add 2 cans of water to this.
Pour over the meat and vegetables. Cover tightly and bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: city chicken
directions: Mix egg and crackers together.
Roll squares of pork and veal into egg and cracker mix; fry until brown.
Take meat off after brown, then add to long casserole dish and add 1 can of mushroom soup or chicken mushroom soup with 1 can of milk or water.
Put into heated oven at 350° and bake for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: pineapple millionaire pie
directions: Cream together powdered sugar and butter with mixer.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Spread mixture evenly into baked pie shell, then chill.
Blend powdered sugar with whipped cream.
Fold in pineapple and pecans.
Spread this mixture on top of base mixture and chill.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: wheat bread
directions: Heat the
milk, butter, brown sugar and salt to 120° to 130°. Test
with
a
thermometer
to make sure it's the right temperature.
In
a
large
mixing
bowl,
put
cups of the all-purpose flour and all of the yeast.
Add the milk mixture; beat with
an electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds while scraping sides
of
the
bowl,
then
beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
With
a wooden spoon, stir in all of the whole wheat flour and
as
much of the all-purpose flour as you can.
Turn the dough
out
onto a floured countertop,
using remainder of the all-purpose
flour.
Knead to make moderately stiff dough that is smooth
and
elastic, about 8 minutes.
The dough may stick to your fingers, so sprinkle some flour on hands before you start kneading.

title: barbecue burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients well in large bowl.
Make into about 6 to 8 patties.
Place on hot charcoal grill.
Cook until desired doneness.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Marshmallow Cream.
Mix until well blended.
Serve with fresh fruit or cheese cubes, if desired.
Makes 2 cups.

title: rich pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Combine cake mix and butter.
Press into bottom of ungreased 10-inch spring-form pan.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Cream the cheese and butter in mixer or food processor; add flour.
Mix well.
Put through cookie press with star tip.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Store in tight container or freeze.

title: ham loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slightly beat eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except honey.
Mix well.
Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Top loaf with honey.

title: coca cola cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together, egg, 1/2 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and butter.
Sprinkle over apples in dish to form crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Add bread cubes and toss together.
Combine tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper.
Place half the tomato mixture in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with
half the bread mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Put under broiler 2 to 3 minutes to brown the top.

title: coconut oatmeal drops
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening, eggs, vanilla and lemon extract.
Add rolled oats, flour, coconut, soda, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: salad with a twist
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches on bottom of 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg, teasing with fork until mixture is crumbly.
Spread over peaches.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: corn bread(good 'n easy)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Bake in 350 degree oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 25 meatballs.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with water and stir until dissolved.
Add mayonnaise and cottage cheese.
Chill until thickened.
Add vegetables and chill until firm.

title: grandmommy's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup of warm water.
Sift flour and sugar together; mix Crisco, water and yeast together.
Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Let rise until double with cover on.
Punch down; put in refrigerator until ready to use.
Roll out on floured board; cut with a biscuit cutter.
Place a pat of butter on half of roll; fold over like a fried pie. Place in greased muffin pan; let rise.
Bake in a 425° oven until browned.

title: chicken breast bake
directions: Wrap the chicken breasts in the dried beef.
Mix the remaining ingredients; spread mixture over chicken.
Add parsley.
Bake at 200° for 4 hours, uncovered, in a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Serve over rice cooked in chicken broth.

title: crab bites
directions: Spread on English muffins and boil.
Cut into 4's!

title: perfect divinity
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan combine the first four ingredients. Cook and stir until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to a boil. Cook to hard ball stage without stirring.
Remove from heat.

title: cheese burger pie
directions: Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir in beef and onions into pan.
Drain and stir in salt and pepper.
Pour into plate.
Beat the Bisquick, eggs and milk until almost smooth. Pour into plate.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Top with lettuce and pickles. Serve.

title: bubble bread
directions: Arrange ingredients in order given in thoroughly greased Bundt pan.
Set in oven overnight.
In the morning, turn on oven and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: molasses walnut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, cream (by hand) oil, sugar, molasses and egg. In another bowl, mix the flour, cinnamon, soda, ginger, cloves and salt. Add the flour mixture to the molasses mixture and blend well. Add chopped walnuts. Roll dough in a ball the size of a walnut and flatten thin on a greased cookie sheet. Bake in a moderate oven until crispy approximately 10 minutes.

title: crock-pot italian 3 cheese meatballs
directions: Mix ground chuck, egg, cracker crumbs, salt, pepper and minced onion.
Form into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Saute in fat until browned. In crock-pot, layer 1/3 Ragu, 1/2 meatballs, 1/2 Cheddar and Mozzarella and 1/3 sauce.
Repeat with second layer of meatballs, Cheddar and Mozzarella cheeses and sauce.
Top with Swiss cheese. Simmer about 2 hours on low.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter; add molasses, sugar, eggs, vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients; stir after each 1/2 cup only enough to blend.
Fold in 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Pour into well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Cut in squares.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli, chopped onions and chicken broth in medium/large kettle on stove top until broccoli is tender.
Reduce heat and add melted butter, flour, milk, salt, pepper and grated cheese gradually until all cheese is melted and stir the whole time to keep from sticking to pan.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Great with cornbread.

title: soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease baking sheet; set aside. In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
With pastry blender or two knives cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add raisins; stir in yogurt, egg and 1/2 cup water until well combined.
Form dough into ball with 6-inch base. Place on prepared baking sheet.
With knife or scissors, cut a cross into top of loaf.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely on wire rack for 1 hour.
Preparation, 10 minutes.
Bake, 45 minutes.
Cool, 1 hour.
Ready to serve in 2 hours.

title: low-fat vegetable soup(quick and zesty)
directions: In a large pot, bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Add noodles. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings, 1 cup each. (Can be cooked in crock-pot on low for 2 to 3 hours.)
Add noodles 30 minutes before serving.

title: m&m's fudge-filled bars
directions: Heat oven
Grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix oats, flour, nuts, brown sugar, baking soda and
salt in
large
bowl.
Stir
in
margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumbly mixture. Press remaining
mixture
in
pan.
Bake
minutes.
Heat shortening in
quart
saucepan over low heat until melted. Stir in 1 cup of the candies; press candies with back of spoon until
candies break into pieces.
Cook and stir until chocolate
is melted (pieces of candy coating will remain).
Remove from
heat.
Stir in
milk.
Spread
over
baked
layer.
Mix reserved
crumbly mixture and remaining candy.
Sprinkle over chocolate
mixture; press
lightly.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Cool. Cut into bars.
Makes about 49 bars, 2 1/4 x 1 1/2-inches.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix flour, yeast, salt and dry milk in large bowl.
Add eggs, melted lard and 3 cups warm water.
Add sugar.
Mix real well.
If too dry, add 1/2 cup water.
Cover and let rise in bowl.
Then roll out on floured dough board.
Don't roll too thin.
Cut with biscuit cutter and let rise.
Bake at 425°.
Makes 40 rolls, more or less.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until light brown.
Add salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Add the sherry wine and simmer for a few minutes. Add beef consomme and chicken broth.
Cook for approximately 20 minutes.
Let boil for 10 minutes.
Ladle into 6 French onion soup bowls.
To each bowl, add 1 crouton and 1/2 teaspoon Parmesan cheese.
Lay 1 slice of Provolone cheese over each bowl and cover with this layer of Parmesan cheese.
Bake in broiler (or oven) until cheese is bubbly and brown.

title: kalderetang kambing
directions: In a large pot, put goat meat, ginger and enough water; boil it until tender.
Discard liquid and ginger and put goat meat aside.

title: deep dish taco bake
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain well.
Add taco seasoning, sauce (or salsa), kidney beans, corn and half of cheese.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish; sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in Pyrex dish (9 x 9-inches).
Place pieces of cheese on each piece of chicken.
Stir together undiluted soup and wine.
Spoon over chicken; sprinkle stuffing mix on top.
Drizzle and bubble.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Cover for first 20 minutes.
Perfect for a ladies bridge luncheon.

title: south st. louis gooey butter cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and margarine.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs, cream cheese and almond flavoring. Pour over cake layer.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bell peppers and jalapenos should be finely chopped.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange dream salad
directions: Add orange jello to hot orange juice.
Soften cream cheese. Add whipped cream or Dream Whip and drained, crushed pineapple. Mix thoroughly with the cream cheese.
Then add the jello and orange juice mixture (which should be cool).
Add miniature marshmallows and pecans.
Then chill.

title: hickory steak and beans
directions: Put meat in 5-quart crock-pot.
Add 6 ounces barbecue sauce and mix well.
Cook on high for 1 hour, then turn to low for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours.
Drain off all but 1 cup liquid.
Add rest of barbecue sauce and 1/2 of the jar of beans.
Mix and cook on high for 1/2 hour.
Freeze rest of beans for next time.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: bean soup *(old indian recipe)
directions: Cook beans in water for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until beans are done.

title: aunt nellie's dressing
directions: Bake cornbread as directed on package.
Use 2 big baking pans with 3 packages in each pan.
Boil potatoes and onions together and mash.
Add all other ingredients to crumbled cornbread.
Bake in 2 separate pans for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Combine everything in a casserole dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon cream cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pan.
In bowl, beat butter, cream cheese and 1/3 cup confectioners sugar until fluffy. Mix in 1 cup flour.
Flour fingers.
Press dough in pan and bake for 20 minutes until set.
In bowl, mix eggs, granulated sugar, zest, 3 tablespoons flour, baking powder and lemon juice.
Pour over crust.
Bake for 25 minutes, until set.
Cut into squares. Dust with confectioners sugar.
Makes 25 squares.

title: corn relish
directions: Place corn in large saucepan.
Add enough cold water to cover. Heat to boiling.
Boil uncovered 3 minutes.
Drain water from corn; cool.
Cut enough kernels from corn to measure 5 cups.
Mix sugar, flour, salt, mustard and turmeric in pan; stir in vinegar. Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Add corn and remaining vegetables. Simmer uncovered 25 minutes.
Immediately pack mixture in hot jars, leaving 1/4 headspace.
Wipe rims or jars.
Seal and process in boiling water bath 15 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 pints relish.

title: lemon-lime salad
directions: Make the jello, using 1 cup of water. Add marshmallows. Let them melt

and cool the mixture. Add pineapple and cream cheese and mix well, then add whipped cream and mix well. Pour in molded deep dish and put in refrigerator (or "icebox," as my grandmother wrote on the recipe). When it is chilled/molded, cut into squares. Serves 12. Must do ahead (for chilling).

title: savory potato gratin
directions: Saute onions in butter in a large skillet until soft and transparent.
In a shallow baking dish sprayed with cooking spray, arrange layers of potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle with garlic and seasonings in between layers for best flavor.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Add whipping cream and sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake for another 10 to 20 minutes, until potatoes are tender and gratin slightly browned.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cover first 8 ingredients with water; simmer with lid off for 2 hours.
Add the margarine, lots of pepper, the Worcestershire and Tabasco; cook another hour.
Serve with hot, cooked rice. Doubled makes 6 quarts for freezing.

title: shamrock salad
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan and 3 ounce packages of Jell-O.

title: stra-ba-nut ice cream
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer at medium speed until frothy. Gradually add sugar, beating until thick.
Stir in condensed milk and vanilla.
Combine strawberries, bananas and pecans. Fold in whipped topping.
Add fruit mixture to egg mixture.
Stir gently. Pour into freezer can of 1 gallon.
Add enough milk to fill can 3/4's full.
Freeze.
Let ripen at least one hour.

title: irma's quick quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In blender container, combine eggs, milk, butter, biscuit mix, salt and pepper.
Blend for a few seconds.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese, bacon, onion and herbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Allow at least 10 minutes cooling before cutting or cool and chill to carry on picnic.

title: nags head
directions: In a pot, stir eggs, sugar and butter.
Heat until butter is melted. Cool the mixture. Add the pineapple and juice.
Fold in Cool Whip, then layer mixture with vanilla wafers.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Refrigerate leftovers.
You can use peaches, strawberries or any other fruit.

title: biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening until it resembles coarse meal. Stir in yeast and buttermilk.
Mix well and turn onto floured surface.
Knead 1 to 2 minutes.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out.
Place on lightly greased sheet.
Brush with melted butter. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Brush again with butter after removal.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: apple delight
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add dry ingredients.
Add chopped apples, nuts and vanilla.
Bake
in 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish at 375°.
Don't overcook!

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Sift the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together. Add butter, sugar and eggs. Beat until light and fluffy.

title: microwave caramel cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Divide into 3 glass pans that are lined with wax paper.
Microwave each layer 4 1/2 minutes.
Cool before icing.

title: kifta(syrian flat meat loaf)
directions: Mix ingredients well and spread in pan.
Bake in hot oven, over 450°, until browned.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix 1 quart buttermilk with vanilla pudding until thick. Fold in Cool Whip.	Fold in well drained fruit.
Mix and chill.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Dip chips into broth.
Line cake pan bottom and sides with chips.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour into cake pan. Put chips on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: seven layer delight
directions: Brown hamburger meat with 1/2 cup chopped onions.
Drain. Add taco seasoning.
In serving dish layer, in order, refried beans, hamburger meat, guacamole dip, sour cream, chopped lettuce, tomatoes, and cheese.
Add salsa if desired.
Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight before serving.

title: string beans
directions: Take off the point and butt of the bean.
Wash and break as small as you can and lay in cold water until ready to use.
Put on to cook in cold water.
When this boils, pour it off and add other boiling water and a piece of salt pork.
Cook 1 hour.
Season and send to the table hot.

title: taco party wings
directions: Combine taco seasoning, cornmeal, salt and parsley flakes in plastic bag.
Shake wings a few at a time until coated.
Place in single layer in greased shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Turn wings and bake 10 minutes more or until tender.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In a large oblong or square container, place the ingredients in layers, beginning with the lettuce and ending with the bacon. Mix 1 pint of Hellmann's mayonnaise with 2 tablespoons of sugar and spread over top.
Cover.

title: buttermilk chicken
directions: Dip chicken in 1/2 cup buttermilk, then roll in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place chicken in pan and bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake 15 minutes.
Blend 1/2 cup buttermilk, 1/2 cup sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix well.
You may add whatever kind of vegetables you like.

title: powder puff cookies
directions: Mix and sift together the flour, cream of tartar and soda. Blend powdered sugar, Crisco and egg;
mix well.
Add vanilla and walnuts;
roll into balls.
Press with fork.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes at 325°.

title: potato casserole
directions: *Let thaw 1/2 hour.

title: pecan pie(no crust)
directions: Cream the sugar, margarine and eggs, beaten well.
Add a sprinkle of flour and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Spray 9-inch pan with Pam.
Pour mixture in pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: garlic potato(microwave)
directions: You will need a deep casserole dish.

title: smoky bacon wraps
directions: Cut bacon strips in half crosswise.
Wrap one piece of bacon around each sausage link and secure with a toothpick if needed. Place in a foil-lined baking pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake uncovered at 400 degrees for 35-40 minutes or until bacon is crisp. Drain on paper towels and serve while warm.
Yield:
3 1/2 dozen.

title: spiced hot tea
directions: Boil sugar, water, cinnamon, lemon and orange rinds for 5 minutes.
Remove cinnamon stick and add juices.
Pour boiling water over tea and steep for 5 minutes.
Combine tea and juice.

title: easy crawfish pie
directions: Saute garlic, celery, onion and bell pepper in butter.
Pour in cream of celery soup and half of the cream of mushroom soup. Do not add water.
Add crawfish (and fat) and cook on high heat for 20 minutes. Remove from heat. Add shallots and enough rice to thicken.
Heap into 1 pie shell.
Place second pie shell on top and crimp edges. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Butter 4 miniature muffin tins (12 each) on sides and bottom. Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs and shake.
Set aside.
Mix well cream cheese, sugar and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites very stiff and fold into cheese mixture.
Fill pans almost to top.
Bake 15 minutes in oven at 350°.
Remove from oven and cool (they will fall).

title: new villa chocolate pie
directions: Melt together marshmallows, milk and Hershey bar over very low heat. Cool, but not too long.
Whip Rich's whipped topping.
Thaw completely before whipping.
Fold chocolate mixture into whipped topping.
Put in graham cracker crust or baked pie crust.
Chill.

title: tuna noodle supreme
directions: Cook pasta.
Drain.
Meanwhile, mix sour cream, mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, milk and mustard.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add hot pasta, tuna, broccoli, red peppers and green onion.
Stir well.
Bake in 2-quart baking dish, covered, for 40 to 45 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: forgotten chicken casserole
directions: Season chicken to taste with salt and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour soup and rice mixture into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish and top with the chicken.
Cover and bake in a 250° oven for 3 hours.
I baked at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Have ready 11 x 7-inch microwave-safe baking dish.
Mix coating ingredients and coat chicken on all sides.
Arrange in single layer, thicker parts toward outside edges.
Cover loosely with wax paper and microwave on Medium-high for 12 minutes. Rotate dish 1/4 turn twice.
Pour tomato mixture over and around chicken.
Cover and microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: one hour round steak stew
directions: In a large stove top pot, pour in olive oil.
Cut round steak in bite size pieces and brown in oil.
Turn the fire down to low. Sprinkle powdered garlic over meat.
Cover and simmer for approximately 1/2 hour.
Add cut up carrots, celery and onion. Simmer for 15 minutes in a covered pot.
Add cut up potatoes. Simmer until potatoes are done.
Take beef bouillon, flour and 1 1/2 cups cool water.
Stir until lumps are gone.
Turn up heat to medium.
Pour bouillon mixture over the top of the stew.
Stir with large spoon until thickened and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box, except use 1/3 cup of water instead of 2/3.
After mixing the batter well, add the 3/4 cup of blueberries.
Cook according to directions on the box.

title: church supper dessert
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and oleo.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill 15 minutes.
Dissolve jello; chill until slightly thickened. Combine marshmallows and milk in a saucepan until almost melted. Cool completely.
Arrange bananas in a single layer on the crumb crust.
Blend Cool Whip into cooled marshmallow mixture.
Swirl slightly into jello.
Pour over the bananas.
Chill until firm.

title: jan hagel's crisp cookies
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar; add egg yolk, flour, 1/4 teaspoon of cinnamon and nuts and mix well.
Pat mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Beat egg white, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, water and vanilla until frothy.
Spread over mixture in the pan.
Top with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut immediately when removed from the oven.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: All ingredients should be room temperature.
Beat eggs until light and thick.
Add flour and 1/3 cup milk.
Beat slowly 30 seconds, gradually adding remaining milk and oil.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes.
Place 4 tablespoons hot meat drippings into a hot 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour in batter and bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve hot from oven with gravy.

title: coffee cake muffins
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients until moist.
Combine the next 5 ingredients.
Place 1/2 of the batter in muffin pan; sprinkle cinnamon mixture over top.
Cover with batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: raspberry mousse
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Make paste of coloring and cocoa.
Add to first mixture.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour and salt.
Add vanilla.
In separate bowl, add vinegar and soda.
Blend with rubber spatula into rest of mixture.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) greased and floured cake pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed and pour half of the batter in tube pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle 2/3 of this mixture on first half of batter.
Swirl this into batter just a little; next pour remaining batter over first half and sprinkle with remaining topping.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix Bisquick and water until soft dough forms.
Pat dough in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; spread evenly over dough.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.
Bake until edges are light brown, about 30 minutes.
Makes 9 servings.

title: frozen pineapple cranberry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon into an 8-inch pan or use a 1 quart refrigerator ice cube tray.
Freeze for several hours or overnight.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch chips on low heat.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir well. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper to cool.

title: speedy candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter together in top of double broiler.
Add flavoring.
Stir well and then add the marshmallows, stirring just to coat them.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
It hardens very quickly.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and make into balls.
Arrange them on a baking sheet and bake at 425° for 20 minutes (smells and tastes great).
You can eat them in anything, but to me they taste great by themselves.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Butter a
square or rectangular glass baking dish.
Peel potatoes and cut crosswise in thin slices.
Arrange overlapping slices in rows
in
baking dish.
Pour butter over potatoes and sprinkle with salt
and
pepper.
Bake, uncovered, in 500° oven until potatoes are tender, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle
with
cheese and bacon bits.
Return to oven until cheese is melted (about 5 minutes).

title: easy tamale pie
directions: In large skillet, cook meat and onion until tender.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Turn into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cut in squares.
Serves 8.

title: browned rice and pork casserole
directions: Trim fat from chops.
In large skillet, heat fat and use to brown chops.
Remove chops and put in rice and cook lightly in drippings.
Then add 1 cup water, gravy and carrots.
Stir, then place chops on top.
Place onion slices on top of chops.
Either cook in oven at 350° for 45 minutes or on top of stove for 45 minutes.
Put lid on skillet.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in chicken broth.
Make a white sauce with oleo and flour.
Mix well.
Add the milk and soup; cook.
Remove from heat and add cheese.
Stir until melted.
In casserole dish, mix chicken, macaroni and peas or corn.
Pour sauce over top and dot with oleo.
Put Ritz cracker crumbs over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: my mom's clear french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender or processor.
If you don't like so much garlic, just put garlic clove in the dressing whole and let it marinate overnight, then remove.

title: dreamy chicken stew
directions: Combine soup, 1 cup water, celery, onion and seasonings in large heavy pan; add chicken.
Cover; cook over low heat 1 1/2 hours and stir often.
Add vegetables.
Cover; cook 45 minutes or until chicken and vegetables are tender.

title: grandma's carrot cake
directions: Combine
the
eggs,
oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Add the flour, baking
powder, cinnamon and salt and continue beating until well blended.
When batter is smooth, stir in the grated carrots.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake
pans.
Bake at
for
40 to 45 minutes, or until a wooden
pick
inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool in pans
minutes.
Remove from
pans and let cool completely before
icing.
See
the recipe
"Icing
for Grandma's Carrot Cake".

title: potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes, cook potatoes in boiling, salted water until potatoes are soft. In large pan, melt butter, add flour, stir until smooth.
Add milk and stir constantly over medium heat until thickened and smooth. Add potato mixture and chopped parsley. Serve hot.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: In a saucepan, heat blackberries and 1 cup sugar until boiling.
Set aside.
In a baking dish (approximately 8 x 8-inch), melt 1/2 stick of butter.
In a bowl, mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour and milk to make batter.
Next, pour batter over melted butter, then pour the blackberries over the top of the batter.
Bake at 375° until brown and bubbly (30 to 45 minutes).

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Stir all ingredients together, adding flour to make a soft dough.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Divide dough into 1/4 sections.
Roll out a square about 3/8-inch thick.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Cut into squares (about 12).
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350°.

title: all white meat chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Heat 3 inches oil in large saucepan until 375°.
Adjust heat to maintain temperature.
Beat eggs and water in large bowl.
Add flour, sesame seeds and salt. Stir until well mixed.
Dip chicken pieces into batter.
Fry chicken a few at a time for about 4 minutes or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: creamy potato bake
directions: Prepare instant mashed potatoes according to package directions, omitting the butter.
After adding the potatoes, mix in whipped cream cheese and beat well.
Stir in egg, onion and snipped parsley or parsley flakes.
Blend.
Transfer to a well greased 1-quart baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Pour in a pan and chill.

title: texas pinto beans
directions: Soak pinto beans overnight; drain.
Place ingredients in a large heavy kettle.
Add water to cover beans 3 inches.
Cook slowly until beans are soft (3 hours).
Add salt to taste before beans are done.

title: easy chicken pie 2
directions: Layer chicken and eggs in a casserole.
Mix broth and soup; pour over layers.
Mix biscuit mix and milk and pour over all. Drizzle melted oleo over all.
Bake at 325° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: butterscotch zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 8 3/4 x 4 1/2-inch pans.
Bake at 350°.

title: fruit flan
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a bowl, combine eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
In a small saucepan, allow milk to barely simmer. Pour into egg mixture and stir.
In 8 small ramekins, sprinkle bottoms evenly with grated nuts.
Pour mixture into ramekins and put them in a baking pan with 1-inch hot water.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Test for doneness by inserting a knife blade in middle of flan.
The blade should come out clean.
Unmold the flans into glass dessert dishes.
Top with fresh fruit, such as small grapes, strawberries, raspberries, blueberries, sliced passion fruit or blackberries.
Serves 8.

title: instant double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix cheese, milk and sugar in bowl until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk and pudding mix in and beat until blended.
Mixture will be thick.
Stir in pumpkin and spices.
Mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping and/or nuts, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bean dip
directions: Put all ingredients into a saucepan and warm up slowly, stirring occasionally.
Use recycle containers.
Serve with corn chips; serve warm.
This dip is mild the first day, but gets spicy as it ages.

title: kim's sloppy joes
directions: First brown hamburger, then add onion and cook until onion is soft and transparent.
Add other ingredients.
Add enough water to mixture so it's soupy.
Simmer in an electric skillet until desired consistency.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole(one dish meal)
directions: Mix poultry, sour cream, soup and vegetables in a large bowl. Using vegetable cooking spray, spray a large 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle one cup stuffing mix on bottom of casserole.
Pour in chicken soup mixture.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix on top.
Dot with butter to taste, as desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until hot and bubbly in center.
Serves 6 to 8.
Is good with a salad.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain syrup from peaches.
Simmer syrup with whole cloves and cinnamon for 10 minutes.
Pour over peach halves; add lemon juice; cover and let cool.
Chill well before serving.
Garnish with a bit of mint.

title: spice tea
directions: Boil 1 quart water.
Add tea bags, cinnamon stick and cloves. Steep 10 minutes.

title: orange sherbet pie
directions: Mix sherbet with 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Pour into a chocolate graham cracker crust.
Top with the other half of Cool Whip. Grind up Oreos and sprinkle on top.
Freeze.

title: italian sausage and pepper
directions: Fry sausage, onion and bell pepper in oil.
Drain and add soup.
Serve over rice.

title: foolproof beef and broccoli
directions: Slice beef across the grain into thin strips.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook beef and garlic in hot oil until beef is browned.
Add broccoli and onion and cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of broccoli soup

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 5 hours.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add strawberries to jello mixture. When thawed and mixed (75% congealed), put on top of cheese layer. Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.

title: cathedral cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips with butter and allow to cool.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well and place on waxed paper sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Form into roll and chill well. Slice into thin slices.
Looks very pretty and are good.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown meat without fat.
Add salt and water; simmer 30 minutes.
Remove meat and pour off fat.
In skillet, melt bouillon cube in hot water.
Add Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce, pineapple juice, vinegar and mustard.
(I add a little brown sugar and a sprinkle of ginger.)
Combine starch and cold water.
Stir in skillet mixture until thick.
Add meat to sauce.
Heat and add veggies and steam for 5 to 10 minutes to get flavor but leave veggies fairly crisp.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: caramel corn
directions: Place popcorn in large shallow pan (turkey roaster).
Place in 250° oven to stay warm.

title: hamburger pie
directions: * Instant potatoes may be used but reserve the milk.
Add only enough milk so potatoes hold shape.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine soda and buttermilk.
Put all ingredients in a large bowl, except Coke and marshmallows; blend well.
Add Coke and blend well.
Stir in marshmallows by hand.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: haddock on the grill
directions: Place haddock fillet on large sheet of aluminum foil.
Rub top liberally with margarine.
Sprinkle on a good amount of dill weed. Wrap and seal well in the foil.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes on each side on hot grill.
You can substitute swordfish and use mayonnaise instead of margarine.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients (first 5 listed).
Stir together eggs, oil, buttermilk and add to dry, mixing well.
Pour batter into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: asparagus-tomato stir-fry
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together and set aside.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: apple crisp(serves 4)
directions: Place sliced apples in the bottom of an 8-inch square baking dish.
Mix raisins, water, sweetener and spice together.
Sprinkle over apples.
Mix vanilla flavored low calorie beverage, cereal and margarine together.
Sprinkle over all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be microwaved on High for 15 minutes.
Divide evenly.
Each serving equals 1 fruit, 1/4 milk, 1/4 bread and 1/4 fat.
tags: vanilla flavored low calorie milk beverage

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese and croutons. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; sprinkle with remaining cheese and croutons.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown. Great for leftover ham!

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in pie filling.
Turn into 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Chill until partially set.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in 1 cup boiling water. Beat together the cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Gradually add lemon gelatin.
Stir in pineapple and whipped cream; fold into lemon mixture with marshmallows.
Spread on top cherry layer.
Top with nuts.
Chill until set.
Serves 12.

title: congealed asparagus salad
directions: Bring first 2 ingredients to a boil; add to gelatin.
Add this to celery, onion, nuts, pimento, lemon and asparagus.
Can be used in individual molds or large single mold to be cut into squares. Very good served with turkey or ham.
Serves 12.

title: squash custard pie
directions: Microwave in covered dish squash, onions and water on High for 4 minutes.
Drain and chop.
Place in a greased pie pan.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Pour boiling water over soda, chocolate, vanilla and salt. Set aside to cool.
Cream together margarine, sugars and egg.
Add alternately the dry ingredients with buttermilk.
Add chocolate mixture and 1 more egg.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan 35 minutes at 375°.

title: spring delight molded salad
directions: Dissolve mixed lemon and lime jello in hot water and pineapple juice.
Add cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.

title: stir-fry green beans
directions: Heat oil in a wok or skillet.
Add green beans, ginger and garlic.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes at high heat.
Add soy sauce and water and cook, covered, for 3 to 5 minutes, until beans are done.

title: spiced oranges(dessert for two)
directions: Combine the ingredients and bring to a gentle boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until syrupy.
